reviews.text:
Absolutely loved our experience at Eastern Standard! From the moment we walked in, the service was top-notch—friendly, attentive, and just the right amount of casual. The ambiance was spot on too, with a cozy yet lively vibe that made the evening feel special.

As for the food, it did not disappoint! We started with the steak tartare and bone marrow appetizers, both of which were insanely good. The steak tartare was perfectly seasoned, and the bone marrow was so rich and flavorful—it was hard to pick a favorite between the two. For the mains, we had the salmon and shrimp entrees, and both were cooked to perfection. Fresh, flavorful, and just the right portion size.

Definitely a place worth visiting again!
Loved this place. Cocktails and service were top notch. The Jack Rose, Old Cuban, Whiskey Smash, Sazerac, and Spagett Drink were enjoyed by everyone. We did not have any food here, but I wish we had!

Great restaurant. Don't let looks fool you. It looks like a giant sports bar that wouldn't have great food, but you be wrong! The food is awesome and of high quality! Just beware if you go whent he Red Sox are playing. Its going to be packed and very loud!  Still a great spot. Will defiantly come again and would highly recommend.

Tuna crudo- large portion of tuna. Good quality too.  Came with waterlon that tasted like it was marinated with jalapeno. Great flavor combination 4/5

Corn soup- the soup was thick and pretty creamy. Had   bold sweetness to it as well. Would have been nice if some sort of protein was added to it for texture-like other places, but was still very good 4.5/5

Lobster gnocchi- this is a special they have each Friday. This was delicous. A good amount of perfectly tender lobster. The gnocchi was pillowy soft and came with a super savory brown butter sauce. There was some lemon in there to adding some nice acidity.  5/5

Butterscotch bread pudding-Delicious but  BEWARE! This thing is a beast. It's basically half a loaf of bread topped with butterscotch and ice cream. I can eat a lot of food but even I couldn't finish this. That being said the bread was dense, but also soft. Combined with the ice cream and delicious butterscotch sauce this this was soo good. 5/5

Our server Matt very knowledgeable on describing the menu ingredients. Very friendly service and provided my wife and I with speedy service.   At one point I wasn’t happy with my drink and he immediately recommended something and I really enjoyed it.
The food here is great.
We ordered Calamari, lobster cocktail, quiche.

My first visit to the new Eastern Standard! I remember fondly the old location and was eager to try the new iteration. I think there may still be some hiccups to work out but the bones are there for it to become the institution it once was. First of all the location is PHENOMENAL for anyone going to an event at Fenway. We made a reservation for our Monday night dinner before a concert at MGM & it was a smart move because the places filled very quickly! Our server was kind and capable, nothing that truly wowed but absolutely acceptable service. We enjoyed the lobster filled squash blossoms which were a highlight of the meal! The Caesar salad was perfectly serviceable but not something I would bother with again.

My friend and I were both looking forward to the bone marrow as it was a favorite for us at the old location. It was good but left something to be desired in the texture. Rather than being hot and melting into the bread accompaniment as you spread it the way we remembered the marrow was luke warm and still a bit gelatinous. The viscosity wasn’t offensive but wasn’t the pleasant, oozing, unctuous meat butter that we had remembered from days of yore. It perhaps just needed a bit more time under heat before being served.

We also enjoyed the Steak Frites which the kitchen was kind enough to split for us. It was a delightful entree, the steak perfectly cooked to our preference and the aioli on the side was delicious with the fries. It gave all the things you want when you indulge in steak frites.

The crème brûlée we chose to end our meal with was more than decent in flavor but slightly off in texture. It wasn’t fully firm & thus was a bit of a let down as the close of our meal.

Overall it was a fine first visit with a great view of the Boston skyline with Fenway from its elevated perch over the street. In time this may just be the dining destination it has the potential to be and I will certainly be back to watch its evolution.

This is our second time seeing a concert at House of Blues. The first time was to see James Blunt and most recently, Judah and the Lion.

The venue is intimate with decent acoustics. We didn’t notice any of the reverb or distortion we’ve experienced at larger or very small show spaces.

Wife and I are both disabled and opted for ADA seats.  The staff was very polite and we were escorted to our seats on the 3rd floor via a dedicated elevator.

The seats themselves were actually high-quality folding chairs with no padding. Luckily we anticipated this and brought our own cushions. The area was “guarded” by a staff member which meant we weren’t bothered by regular patrons trying to get a better view.

Our only complaint was that while sitting (which we need to do the majority of the time) the railing blocked our view. To see the stage we either needed to peek through the steel balusters or lean over the railing.  Notably, for those restricted to wheelchairs, it appeared there was an area (with a perfect, centered, unobstructed view of the stage).

If you can manage a few stairs, there were standard arena style chairs in the “stadium level.”

The aforementioned is less a complaint and more simply informational for those covered by ADA. Overall, we were very pleased with the care, courtesy and respect with which we were treated.

Without reservation, we recommend House of Blues as a concert venue!

Quaint theater with a good amount of bathrooms. Friendly staff. This was my first time there. And I'd see a show there again for sure. Sound was good, decent space for people that didn't want to be right up front. There was balconies but I'm not sure how people got to them, or if it was different tickets to be up there.

super cute venue, with a wraparound mezzanine on the inside and small bar! i love how intimate it feels, and that no matter where you are in the building (if you’re buying merch or getting a drink) you can still hear the music, unlike at MGM. note that they don’t allow electronics into the venue (they’ll hold it for you at their coat closet for $5) and the bag check takes a while so if you’re in general admission, maybe just go with what’s on your person.

Just saw Tori Kelley here last Saturday and it was amazing! The layout was great, the venue workers were all super friendly, even the security left to get the last of the stubborn visitors out at the end of the night were really nice. We stayed late buying merch and saw how thoroughly they cleaned the place after and all the workers did a really good job! Would love to go here again.

HoB is an excellent venue to see metal bands. Testament, Kreator, and Possessed put on a total metal thrash fest. I love the up-close and personal interaction with the acts that an arena can't possibly offer.

We came for dinner in a Friday night and got right in without a reservation. They have tons of beers, and you can make your own flight to try four at a time. The menu was substantial, about of things looked good. I settled on the steak bowl, with a chicken tortilla soup. Because of the large menu, I was expecting frozen food, tough steak etc, but I was pleasantly surprised.

The soup was delicious. Creamy, hot, and fresh. It had little bits of avocado on top and big chunks of chicken. Delicious. The steak bowl had some of the best cooked steak I have ever had. Super tender and perfectly cooked.

Beer was good, food was excellent, and service was great. And you can’t beat the people watching from the patios.

The yard house was great for dinner last night! We had the poke nachos for appetizers which was delicious! I had the mediterranean salmon, which was very good! Fiancé had the blue cheese and bacon burger which she liked a lot.
For drinks had the espresso martini which was great. And their dragon fruit Cosmo, which was really good! For dessert we had the crème brûlée and the bread pudding, we all loved the bread pudding, the crème brûlée was pretty good, but not our favorite.
Had good service for how busy it was, they still stayed on top of it. Inside and outside looks nice and clean, nice place for a date or night out with friends.

Great selection of beer (loved the build-your-own flights) and an eclectic mix of dishes. The food is surprisingly good -- I expected the mix of bar food and Asian seafood dishes to be odd, but we ordered a mix of everything and all the dishes were fantastic! The portions are huge, so order accordingly!

Excellent food and service! I love the Yard House—they have such a vast menu with plenty of options and I’m never disappointed with the quality of the items. Reasonably priced too. I ordered the seared tuna sandwich which was phenomenal. Very flavorful and would definitely order it again. The spinach dip appetizer was great as well—I just wish they gave more dip.

I also loved my drink! I got the Pineapple Express and it was tasty.

Great place in Boston for dinner and drinks with friends before a game or concert. The Baja shrimp tacos were surprisingly amazing. Our espresso martinis were made delicious and dark. Lemon pepper tenders were crispy and tasty. Ordering drinks on the tablet was extremely convenient and fairly hasty. I really liked that as some great spots take a while for cocktails.
The food was amazing! The waitress we had also was the sweetest person ever! We will definitely go back next time we are going to a game again. Thank you guys!
After a great time at Fenway we needed to address this hunger. Great location near the stadium. Very tasty food and atmosphere.   Servicev was a tad slow but we would return here.

I got the brisket. The flavor was good, but not cooked well, I had to use a knife to cut it. Fries taisted good, but were a little cold. The corn bread was just ok. I am picky on coke slaw and yhat was not my style. Service was very slow and the place was not busy. We rarely saw our waiter. The place was fairly clean. Lots of TVs all over. The staff was very short in conversation and were cordial, but not super friendly.

This fried chicken sandwich comes with a mango slaw, chipotle aoli sauce, on a sesame seed brichoe bun, it was so delicious! I didn't think I would care for the slaw, but I wouldn't get this sandwich without it!! The loaded tater tots though 🤤🤤. Topped with beer cheese, bacon, chipotle ranch, pico de gallo, and scallions, sheesh that's a great combination! Let's not forget this tasty Strawberry Lemonade as well that I had 2 of and wanted 3 lol. Oh yea and they had several college football games on. For great food, great atmosphere, all the good games playing on different televisions, stop by Cask'n Flagon. You won't regret it!

Went there for the NBA finals. The place is vast, with room between tables. Food is nice and there is a second menu for diner. The beer tap was not functioning on this night so only cans and bottles were available. Overall it's a good sport bar and the food is great but there are better options in the area.

ChIJG_7Z4_V544kRalvwsGSoZaI.address: 86 Van Ness St, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text: Tasty Burger is a great place for a quick bite before a baseball game. Burgers are great, staff is great and super friendly. Before a Red Sox game, be prepared to wait 25+ min for a table. Our group ended up sitting at the bar. Recommend getting the Big Tasty. They are also very accommodating with allergies. I definitely miss their old location though.

I got the Big Tasty and the 50/50 Onion Rings and Fries. A classic satisfying burger. The burger has the old school taste of burgers, so it had me nostalgic. I highly recommend!
The onion rings and fries were great too, crispy with right amount of saltiness/sweetness
Really hit the spot after doing a Fenway Park tour. Got a milkshake and crispy chicken sandwich. delish!
Being new to the area, a few friends recommended - if you are just craving for a good burger and beer, this is the place to be. I’m enjoying my late lunch… it is just hitting the spot!

I always see a massive line every time I pass by this place, so I decided to try them out one day with me and my friend.

My friend got: GORGONZOLA
Which is a burger with blue cheese and bacon. His rating was 8.6/10

"Unique flavor, but the blue cheese is overpowering."

I ordered: RISE 'N SHINE BURGER
Egg, bacon, and Tasty's spicy ketchup

I love me some eggs on my burger, and it was amazing. I'll give a rating of 9/10 (would order again)

We both ordered the tots with cheese and chili, and it was good, nothing too special.

Rating 6.6/10.

This location is always such a mess. A while back, I went and ordered a sofritas bowl. Despite it being labeled as such and me reminding them of that, they charged me for a steak bowl instead. Rather than refunding me when I noted that, they gave me $1 from the cash register. It’s odd service like this that has me baffled versus any other Chipotle location I’ve ever been to.
As others have mentioned, the workers are really rude and it’s usually filthy in here. Were this not right by my office, I’d never be back here.
The food is amazing. But surrounding sitting is unhygienic or unclean.  Staff is very rude.

Worst branch I have ever been to. Had a pick up order but I got there seeing employees arguing with customers and ignoring my existence for 10 minutes, stood there for another 5 minutes for another employee to check with my order. And got the food for almost half of the portion compared to Back Bay branch. Worst experience with chipotle ever and would never want to come again.

this place is terrible. they barely give you any of the toppings That you asked for. They’re very stingy and it’s To a point of just not wanting anyone to eat. This location is very dirty and Lacks a welcoming atmosphere. I would not recommend to anyone, especially if you’re very hungry because you will have to get charged extra if you want a normal portion.

Tables were super dirty and sticky and they preheat the tortillas in foil instead of giving fresh hot tortillas so I had to ask can I have a fresh heated tortilla. I get they're trying to save time heating them but those preheated ones are hard to unfold once they been wrapped and sitting in pan for however long

The place is HUGE and has many fun activities to do.
Good for chatting, good for playing, good for watching the games, I did not eat but my friends wouldn’t complain about the food.
I highly recommend it :)

Good place to hangout with friends for b'day parties etc. It has 2 floors. The first floor has arcade games the 2nd has pool and bowling.
The staff is not very friendly. She was not answering the queries properly and was making faces at times. Hope not all the staffs are like her. The bowling game is for 1 hour. But thet shut down the bowling game at the 55th minute only. We request for 5 more mins but they denied which wasn't fair at all.

I'm going to preface this by saying that the service inside of the building is great. 5 stars to them. They always make you feel welcome and are really kind and patient. They deserve all the praise.
However, I had an issue with one of the security personnel right before you enter. I carry pepper spray for self defense and they took it away from me and said that I wouldn't get it back when I left the establishment. I've had no problems carrying it at venues larger than Lucky Strike. In the worst case, security would confiscate it for the duration of the show, label it with my name, and then give it back to me on my way out. Secondly, it's fully legal to carry pepper spray in MA. I didn't put up a fight because I assumed a bouncer would know better. Turns out they didn't. I had to pick my battles because I wasn't going to be let in if I didn't let them confiscate it. This review is so other people know their rights and don't let this happen to them. I'm truly disappointed because I've had good experiences at Lucky Strike but that night ruined it for me and I don't wanna go back anymore.

Its a good place if you wanna play unlimited after 6. The price is reasonable. However, we spotted two mouse in front of the sofa near the bowling section. I saw it for the first time so idk how to feel about it.

So disappointed!!! Today we drove all the way from Salem. Me and my friends planned to enjoy the arcade as we saw on google that they close at 11pm and also we asked the staff there he confirmed that as well. But!! At 10.20pm the staff rudely told us that they'll be close now and shut all the games off. We don't think that we'll go back again.
If you like live music - you need to come right here! One of my favorite place in Boston . Such a great atmosphere
Food was decent for a pub. They tried to accommodate all our requests.  Live music was cool. Busy place, but we got seated right away.   Overall great place before an event at Fenway.

The bouncers here are on a disgusting power trip. They will yell at you, shove you, and give you a hard time any chance they can even if you’re being respectful. As a local i will never go back, especially with a $20 cover

So was going to see the sisters of mercy on the night of the ballgame. How much more American can I get. So had some time to kill and headed into this bar. There was a few people hanging around but was quiet as the game was in full swing. Ordered the tender, it’s a starter, just needed a snack. Oh my god they were a whole chicken. But worse than that they were really tasty. So I had to eat them all. So had a second Guiness and headed to the gig. Place felt like a rock club.

The chicken tenders are unlike any I’ve ever had. They were thick and phenomenal. The ranch is also homemade and so flavorful. The live music is so good and mixes with the ambience of the restaurant. Not overly loud.

Oct 2024:

Not bad overall. I enjoyed the dips—they grew on me—but the guacamole with warm chips was pretty good. The shrimp had great flavor, though the rice could have used more depth and seasoning.

🌞 **Sunset Cantina Review** 🌮🍹

**Location & Vibe:** Tucked away on Commonwealth Ave, Sunset Cantina promises an experience that's vibrant with a casual, sports-bar atmosphere. Known for its history as a gathering spot for BU students, my boyfriend and I ventured there hoping to relive some fond memories of nacho-filled evenings. The ambiance is laid-back, perfect for a lively game night. 🏈🍻

**Drinks:** The bar at Sunset Cantina remains its stronghold. With a robust selection of cocktails and beers, the drinks are crafted to kickstart any gathering. We found the cocktails to be particularly well-mixed, adding a refreshing twist to our afternoon. 🍸✨

**Starters - Chips & Queso Dip:** Our meal started on a shaky note with the chips, which were unfortunately stale, detracting from the overall enjoyment. However, the queso dip provided a slight redemption with its intriguing mix of grilled corn salsa and a dash of tajin, offering a zesty flavor that partially made up for the lackluster chips. 🌽🧀 Rating: 4/10

**Main Attraction - Beef Empanadas:** The highlight of our dining experience came in the form of their beef empanadas. Filled with tender, slow-cooked shredded beef and creamy Monterey Jack cheese, these empanadas were flavorful and cooked to a delightful finish, standing out as the most memorable dish of our visit. 🥟🌟 Rating: 7/10

**Salads - A Healthy Twist:** We sampled the Mexican Caesar and steak & avocado salads, aiming for something on the lighter side. While both salads were generous in portion, featuring a decent amount of meat, they lacked a certain flair and were generally average, failing to impress beyond their wholesome presentation. 🥗🥑 Rating: 5/10

**Birria Tacos - A Missed Opportunity:** As a fan of birria tacos, I was eager to dive into this dish, but it fell short of expectations. The tacos lacked the rich, deep flavor typical of birria, and the meat was scant, leading to an unbalanced bite where the taco shell overshadowed the filling. 🌮👎 Rating: 4/10

**Overall Experience:**
While the drinks lived up to the festive spirit of the place, the food struggled to match up, delivering a mixed bag of hits and misses. The setting and price point make it a reasonable choice for casual dining, especially if you're in the area to watch a sports event and enjoy some drinks.

**Final Scores:**
- **Food:** 5/10
- **Affordability:** 7/10
- **Ambiance:** 5/10

Hoping my feedback is seen as constructive. I love capturing and sharing food experiences and always root for places to thrive. 📸💖 If you're looking to watch a sports game with a good drink this might still be your spot!

I went to get a drink at a peaceful place. They were not serving drinks in the bar area. Instead they wanted me to drink standing at a club area. The bar could not hear me and was very mean and rude. So I went to grab drinks at a quieter place. One of the worst places to hangout. It's a waste of money, time and deal with an attitude. I have hosted few social gatherings there but pretty pathetic. They do not even deserve one star rating.

Can someone PLEASE TELL ME WHAT A KITCHEN APPRECIATION FEE IS? What a joke! Guess who’s not coming back to this establishment because of that? Me! Guess who’s telling the locals and friends and family not to support this business over that? ME!

If it's crowded expect to wait a long time for your food. My food actually came out before my drinks did. I was told  the bar was backed up but when I looked there was no one there. My waiter was new which I held space for but she was little forgetful and would forget to. Ome back to our table. Again she was new and it was her first day not in training. She was super nice and sweet.

Solid place for oysters. Nice and cozy vibe. The food was generally a bit salty (the fish in the smoked fish soup, in particular) but it was a good. Good service and nice, old school Boston vibe. Would go back.

Large restaurant at Boylston street with a lovely outdoor seating area. We had potato smoked fish soup, it was lacking seasoning and tasted bland! The Atlantic cod fish was okay-ish. Tablea at the outdoor seating area aren’t clean.

The irony is that all my companions tonight were not fans of either whiskey nor raw seafood, the two specialties of Citizen Public House, but thankfully all the other food and drink options were plentiful and very delicious! The spicy deep fried pickles were super addictive, the endive winter salad was so flavorful with a very nose-tingly horseradish dressing, cauliflower cream pan fried gnocchi was divine, and especially enjoyed the duck pot pie with root veggies. Our server was so charismatic, attentive and kind. Could not recommend coming here enough!
And would love to come back and try their raw seafood bar :)
Appetizers are incredible. Right next to Fenway Park! Everything was delicious. Excellent service.
A great place to grab delicious food and tasty drinks any time and very convenient before a game at Fenway!!

Came in with a reservation around 6pm which is kinda early for dinner but it wasn’t too crowded yet. The staff was very attentive and great at giving me a wine recommendation (cono 4). Croquetas were solid (they upsell you to get 4 instead of 3 but I’m not complaining). Goat cheese toasts were good too and worth it to share with more than 2 people because of how dense they are. Onto the shrimp, the oil they were in was phenomenal. Loved to dip the bread in there. Mushrooms were extremely yummy as well, and the classic spanish egg topping is always a nice touch. I look forward to coming back sometime to try more of their menu.

The food is beyond delicious. Reasonable prices, beautiful casual atmosphere as if you're sitting in a tavern in Spain. Absolutely scrumptious imported wines and cider - warm and welcoming staff, music at the right volume... The eggplant tapas MELTS in your mouth.

I can't wait to return to this lovely wonderful restaurant. Excellent job!

A friend was in town and suggested we eat Spanish food.  I had just visited Spain last month so I was eager to compare. We started with an order of ham croquetas and batatas bravas.  Both were very good, though I had better in Spain.  We shared a seafood paella and it was outstanding,  equal to any I've tried over there.  Truly mouth watering,  with loads of seafood.  Our server was super friendly.  I know that some restaurants like to dim the lights for atmosphere,  but it was too dark.  I recommend this restaurant,  but if you come,  bring a flashlight.

Excellent food! Excellent customer service! Fantastic atmosphere! This is the place for your next dinner reservation! The paella was incredible, generous portion as well. Our cheese plate and calamari was perfect accompaniment. All of this with such friendly staff and hosts!

Had dinner here with a few friends to share some tapas before going to a movie. The server, Bae (forgive me if that’s spelled incorrectly), was amazing. We ordered the meat and cheese board to begin, then have anchovies, frog legs, eggplant, and a few glasses of sherry. Everything was delicious. I highly recommend the frog legs. They were so delicious. Will definitely be back.

Tiffany truly delivers with her mad BBQ skills. Our group ordered a bunch of different items and shared it all for an amazing experience. The Bucket of Biscuits  was the best start to the meal
They were buttery and fluffy with a crisp crusty outside. We tried the beef riv, pulled pork, brisket and fried chicken with multiple sides. The meat was very tender. We did both spicy and plain fried chicken. The spicy is spicy, so, keep it in mind.

Went right when it opened before a Red Sox game.  Service was prompt and attentive.  Menu has a good variety.  Their biscuits were my favorite item.  Overall, I thought the food was good. We did not have to wait long for the food to come out however, the food wasn't that hot when it came. The broccoli casserole was my favorite side dish.  I think it's your average Texas style bbq.

This place comes highly recommended and I can understand why. The menu has good variety while still focusing on what they do best. The bbq was good… juicy and flavorful. The sides were even better (except the okra which was bland). Their biscuits are well made with good structural integrity and tasty butter to match.

My only gripe was how much upselling the menu and our server were doing. For example, she warned us the okra was pretty bland and offered some dips at an extra cost. I would have preferred they make the okra tastier instead of upselling dips.

Overall a good experience and I plan to return.

Staff at Sweet Cheeks Q was amazing! We went for a Friday lunch with our pups. Patio was perfectly shaded with great people watching!
The biscuits are a must! The honey butter and jam just melt in your mouth. We inhaled our brisket before I could get a photo but that was top notch as well. Loved the pickles. The staff was kind enough to get two bowls of water (one for each of our pups) and gave them lots of pets when refilling their water. Do yourself a favor and get the side of Mac and cheese

I had an incredible dining experience at Sweet Cheeks Q! The food was absolutely amazing, with each dish bursting with flavor and cooked to perfection. I must also commend their manager, Francisco, who ensured everything ran smoothly and made us feel truly welcome. Highly recommend for anyone looking for delicious BBQ and exceptional service!

The greatest surprise during our stay in the city. Just perfect food! Flavors were all there FRESH AND TASTY. The service was superb! We decided to purchase many menu items and ALL were superb! Absolutely delicious. Every single dish has its unique distinct fresh taste. We loved everything and will definitely return in the future. Highly recommended ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

I have ordered from here for years and typically had a positive experience. While placing a group order under my name, my friend put in her credit card information but forgot to add a tip. When one of the employees came to deliver our order, he called my phone and refused to leave until I either gave him a tip via app or cash. I explained our mistake and requested for him to leave the order down at the front desk. I told him that I would call the restaurant to add a tip. The employee continued to text and call my phone and only left when I called the restaurant and requested for them to contact him and intervene. I ended up having to block his number. I 100% believe that food service employees should be paid and tipped adequately for their services. However, I don’t think that tips are warranted after repeated badgering and refusal to have a civil conversation.

Chicken Caesar wrap made perfectly to order!  Clean construction, chicken tasty and tender, lettuce crunchy and fresh, just the right amount of croutons and light on the dressing as requested.  Cheesy fries are perfectly fine but wouldn’t write home about them.
Delivery was prompt and friendly!
Am told that it is a popular place to order by nurses and other staff at BID.  My nurse agreed the wraps there are very good.

Frozen yogurt Vanilla + Chocolate chip + Blueberry + Banana + Jelly Lychee

Recommended💯💯💯

I love everything, but NEVER get anything with CHICKEN in it. I’ve tried the chicken 5 times (in different dishes too) to give it a shot and it’s dry, chewy, and just horrible. I take it out every time; it just ruins it- that’s really saying something because I eat everything. I still go back b/c the ice cream is amazing. The staff are amazing. The rest of the food is amazing. It’s literally just the chicken that’s bad.

People that don’t give this place 5 stars are spoiled or have weird expectations. I give it  ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️I really enjoyed the food here. The fajitas are delicious and very yummy. Strongly recommend those. The vibes are chill and the service is great. The chips and salsa are really good too. I strongly recommend this place and will definitely be back. It’s also affordable and the food is delicious! Yum!!!!

Visited this place on a fine evening, luckily we got a table while most of the time you have to reserve one in advance. Enjoyed the outdoor dining and we got the combinations and steak. Firstly, their chips and salsa were amazing and really one of the best I have ever had. It was really fresh and delicious. Drinks were amazing with lot of booze in it. Steak, beans, salads, cheese, chicken, beef, tacos and everything was great and really well cooked. Definitely a great place to visit and customer service was fantastic  they were very polite, funny and friendly. Little pricey but it's in the busy Brookline Beacon Street. Will definitely visit again 😊😊😊😊👍👍👍🙏🙏🙏

BEST FRESH SALSA

This place has one of the best fresh salsas and guacamole!  The nachos are gonna makes you feel full. However it is best suited for a table of 3 or more. They drinks are good and the staff are accommodating with the customer request. I ordered a guava premium drink and asked them to make it spicy and they really surprised me :)

The enchiladas were great as well. Special mention to the in house spicy sauce. They are delicious and you won’t feel the spicy for a second. After you take a taste, you are gonna feel a burn down your throat. I like spicy and it was perfect for me.

Would I recommend this restaurant: hell, yeah. It is a good place for a dinner date :)

Sol Azteca is a classic Mexican restaurant where you can get traditional dishes and excellent margaritas. I’ve been here several times and I’ve never had a bad entree. I’ve had the enchiladas and the quesadillas and really liked them! One thing I’ll make mention of is the queso asada appetizer. It’s not like normal queso which I associate with a creamy thick cheese sauce. Ours was more like melted cheese that kind of stuck to the cast iron skillet it was in. It was still good, but it was more solid and greasy than expected.
Amazing food, big portions, nice atmosphere, friendly staff. This place deserves five stars! Delicious fresh salsa and tortilla chips are also served with your food.

The food at this restaurant is average at best. I tried their lunch special featuring chicken teriyaki with rice saturated in teriyaki sauce, a sad salad, a bland mushroom soup, and an unremarkable California maki. I requested a miso soup instead of the mushroom soup listed on the menu, but they don't allow substitution which is sad. Despite the steep prices, the quality falls short compared to other Japanese restaurants nearby that has lower prices and better food.

A good place for my seafood lovers 😋
I had the basho bowl and the kimono berry. The flavors were intense but delicious. Other things worth a try were the shishito peppers and the potato katsu!
Lovely place for a team lunch.

I Love it! Since I work in Fenway, my choices are limited sometimes. The portions are a bit small but tasty! It's pricey, but i treat myself some days. Finger food for lunch, lol
But I like it, the service is very professional, the place is clean. Fast with serving ur food, especially for those of us that only have a 30 min lunch break.
It's a nice go-to spot!

We came here for dinner with a large group and it was mostly empty. We had a great time and everything was delicious!

We got the Matcha Matcha and Mango Whisky drinks, both of which were super good, looked beautiful, but weren't very strong. For apps, the tuna tartare was the most tasty. We got an assortment of the special sushi rolls and honestly they were all super delicious.

The service was prompt and knowledgeable; the ambiance was hip. I would come back here again!

The best place to eat sushi in Fenway. It’s my go-to sit-in restaurant and we went on a Saturday night. Tables are spaced out so you’re not eavesdropping the table next to you, and food is amazing. For a packed Saturday night, service was a little slow at first to get our main course, but drinks and apps came on time. Highly recommend!

Great spot for drinks and burger.
Super crispy delicious bacon in the burger.  ❤️

Next to MGM, and convenient before any show.
Nice view of the stadium.
A must visit indeed.

The Bleacher Bar is a great spot for drinks and light snacks. One of its coolest features is that from certain seats, you get a direct view of Fenway Park! The atmosphere is cozy, and it’s a fantastic place to grab a drink. Friendly staff and a unique experience make it a must-visit for any baseball fan!

Such a fun place and you just gotta take it for what it is...an institution, a loud, busy, fun bar under the bleachers! Great beer and cider selections, reasonable prices. We did not eat there, but I saw regular pub-type food on a few tables.

Great place to go overlooking Fenway Park ground. Went here twice during our stay first time when a game was on and the second time when Pearl Jam was setting up. Buffalo wings were very good. Can get bust here but would definitely recommend it.
Definitely one of the coolest bars, I have ever visited! The views are impeccable! Good atmosphere in there also! A very unique experience inside one of the world’s most famous stadiums! ⚾️🏟️

We came here after a B.U. graduation, and everything was thoroughly enjoyable.  Food-wise, the fish & chips, grilled reuben, and turkey club were all tasty. Drink-wise, the espresso martinis were well received, and my favorite beer was the oatmeal brown.  Service was friendly and helpful, both at the tables and at the bar.

Great place to have private event. The food is so delicous, I love the turkey wrap & chicken fringers.
There are plenty tables & waiters are really helpful.
Exactly what they said it was. English pub atmosphere without any pretentiousness. Thick  chowdah lovers - this one is for you. Perfect spot to slug $8 beers before the $13 beers at Fenway.

We recently had a delightful experience at Cornwall's prior to the start of a Red Sox game.  The pre-game atmosphere was fun, yet not as crazy, rowdy as restaurants that are adjacent to Fenway. Cornwall's is an easy walk to Fenway, but I could easily go there any time! The food was fantastic and the service was really quick and professional.  It's a modern version of an English pub. Delicious selections of brews too!
Chill spot with delicious food. I got the shepherds pie and it was great. Good selection on beer. Service is great. The bar is chill at night too, if you're looking for a less clubby atmosphere

Great food, and the overall experience between the service, vibe, and little details make it worthy of a 5th star.

We ordered three dishes with lamb, chicken, and paneer and all were delicious.  Came with tasty basmati rice and the garlic naan was delicious.  Also they bring papadam and sauces free at the beginning.

Little details were surprisingly nice: folded napkins, well prepared table, mint chocolate at the end and guava candies by the door.  The staff were cool people and they provided good service.

First time there and the food was excellent. It was packed but our wait was only about 5 mins. We samosas and veg pakora for starters. I had goat saag and my husband had shrimp tandoori. And you can’t leave without dessert! The owner came over to talk to us. Very lovely staff.

Had dinner twice here. The waiters are talking to themselves most times in hindi but sometimes it makes you feel like they are talking about you.
Nostalgic Bollywood music is playing all the time, love it!
Masala chai is top notch and that too with free refills!
Got samosa chat - complex delicious flavors, good portion size, decent price point.
Bhel puri - the quantity is way less than I expected. Taste is okay. I would go for samosa chat over bhel.
Ordered kadai paneer both times. It comes with rice so its a full meal in itself. Filling and delicious and does taste like ready to eat tomato paste gravy which I appreciate.

I will visit every time i go back to Boston!

This gem is near the top of our Quality-per-Dollar index.
The place has a cozy yet elegant feel, and the staff are kind, attentive and dedicated - and the food is wonderful.
Northern Indian cuisine, like other cuisines of India, benefits from the incredible variety of herbs and spices available in the region, and India Quality reflects that. The experience of the food is in the taste of it, a result of the centuries of wisdom that go into the spice combinations, plus the care and dedication of the staff.
As cuisines go, Indian food's focus on the taste and texture, but not so much the look of it  (that's true of all Indian and Himalayan cuisines...photos of Indian food are never much to look at), and never the whole story. You have to experience the subtle explosion of textures and flavors in your mouth.
Another great feature of Indian cuisine is that they've created a wide variety of vegan and vegetarian options. It's possible to load up on supremely tasty plant protein here.
The most remarkable thing about India Quality is the pricing. It almost seems as if their menu prices froze in the '90s - there are appetizers for under $5, and everything is really tasty and great.
Go! You'll love it.

I’m not sure what these negative reviews are talking about. I’ve been coming here for years and have never had better Indian in my life. The coconut korma and lamb masala are outstanding. Literally never had a bad meal. Best Indian in Boston!!

I’ve been dining at Gyu-Kaku nearly ten times over the past year and a half, and each visit has been a wonderful experience. The quality of ingredients is always fresh and carefully prepared, and the flavors are truly authentic. Whether I’m enjoying the tender cuts of beef, the food has consistently exceeded my expectations. The staff are attentive and friendly, always ensuring that my dining experience is smooth and enjoyable. They are quick to refill drinks, adjust the grill if needed, and answer any questions about the menu, which I really appreciate. The restaurant environment is warm and inviting, perfect for gathering with friends or family.
However, I would definitely recommend making a reservation at least a day in advance, as the wait times can be quite long without one, especially during peak hours. Also, keep in mind that Gyu-Kaku currently doesn’t accept Apple Pay, so be prepared with an alternate form of payment. Overall, Gyu-Kaku has become one of my favorite places to dine, and I look forward to many more enjoyable meals here. Highly recommended!
In fact, if Boston were ever to lose Gyu-Kaku, I might seriously consider transferring schools just to follow this restaurant! It’s become one of my primary sources of comfort and motivation as a student.

The portions are small for each order so it was nice to try a lot of stuff on their menu. Sometimes the servers forgot our order/ order it would come out much later than previous orders, but that might be because they need to keep track of all the tables.
Great beef selection for an AYCE menu. (We got premium and it had so much already.) Will be visiting again during our next boston trip
Bee was a wonderful server! Had a great experience! Delicious food! We did the meal for 4. More than enough with smores for dessert!
Celebrated my birthday at the Brookline location with Arnold as our server and it was awesome!! Such a fun experience, and everything was delicious. Definitely coming back again!

Smaller than other locations but I like the decor of the place. Service was great and attentive to what we needed. The parking over here sucks, either have to do side parking or the garage. All the food was delicious but it did take a while to get the vegetables to the table, but no big deal.

Lots of bagel and drink selections. I got the lavender lemonade which was pretty tasty. It was a bit crowded when we went and it did take a while for our order to be ready, but overall a great place to grab a bagel.

coffee was surprisingly AMAZING? place was crowded though so that's tough but seriously?? The coffee was good??  Like???? i didnt expect that from this chain LMAO maybe im just used to overhyped over priced coffee but this one was legit?

The best coffee and bagels around. Bagels are legit, chewy but not hurt your teeth chewy and good flavors. Every sandwich is good but chicken salad is the best. The sweets are good too, not overly sweet like some other coffee shops...

i got the lox bagel. it was pretty salty, but still a decent bagel. my friends also got bagels — i don’t remember which ones, but they said theirs were pretty good! definitely very generous with the cream cheese. overall atmosphere was cute!

I love the iced mocha and iced matcha latte in this place. I used to love their almond croissant pre-covid but haven’t seen it recently. The vibe for sitting is really great if the cafe is not fully packed. The bagels are very delicious while on the pricy end. I like to have avocado and sprout with cream cheese everything bagel. I also like their lox bagel. It is my favorite for takeout since it is usually very packed though. The cafe used to have a point system that used to get connected to your phone number. Unfortunately that is gone now. It would be great if the owner could bring back the point system just like JAHO coffee shop does.
GRS school often also gives graduate students coupon for getting free coffee from this Pavement location.
Well, it’s near to school so it’s good for daily food. The service are nice and the food is average.

We had delicious fried noodles 🍝 for dinner and were impressed by the friendly staff and lovely atmosphere near Boston University.

Please note that at this full-service restaurant, it is stated that they reserve the right to charge a 15% minimum table service fee (Tip). You can of course choose to Take-Out if you don't wish to pay the tip 🙌 (it's written on the table, see the pic attached)

I've ordered from here quite a few times, always the same dish, Cashew Chicken. It's always pretty good, but the dish does seem to vary based on the day. Most recently I got it and there were a few chunks of pineapple in it, the dish was overly sweet with no hint of spice to it what-so-ever. Usually there's a bit of chili flavor and a zing of ginger, but this time it just tasted like soy sauce and pineapple juice, a little disappointing. Always quick service and friendly employees when I pick up takeout.

Lovely family restaurant vibe, sweetest staff with great service. Fast and attentive. Delicious and generous food, accommodated all requests. The drunken noodles are so comforting, flavorsome and spicy. They are much better than nud pob in my opinion in terms of both service and food quality.

I used to come to Noodle Street nearly 20 years ago with my friends. I loved their fried tofu and pad Thai with crispy noodles! These days it feels a little more run down than it used to, but I’m just glad they survived COVID. And the high quality food and exceptionally kind and friendly staff are the same as I remember! Being back here in 2024 brought back so many happy memories. Give it a try, you’ll be glad you did!

nah what is this chipotle. this place hasn’t made no effort to give regular size portions. my bowl is never full. look at how stingy they are with the portions. the workers are super lazy as well. the lettuce was basically empty instead of replacing. the worker  sprinkles the bottom scraps on my bowl. this bowl with extra rice as well. can finish this in a few bites

This is the best chipotle I have ever been to. The guacamole quality at chipotle can really range from location to location but this chipotle has perfectly made guacamole every time. They never skimp on portions. The employees are helpful and fast. There is never a line because they always work so quickly and efficiently. As an extremely picky eater I appreciate consistency in food taste and texture. For any one who loves chipotle, who is going to be in Boston for even just one  night, it would be a shame not to try this chipotle.

I love chipotle but the way the good tasted here made me never want to eat it again. Also I found something that looks like a skinny bone in my queso sauce. The sauce was very chunky and gross. The salsa tasted spoil. The chips was stale. The rice is watery. The chicken…the chicken was actually good, and the workers were nice. But I’ll never come here again.

When I first started going to this Chipotle, I asked if I could have a bowl with just chicken. They said yes. Since then, every night after 9 p.m., I've been ordering chicken and during the daytime full bowl. However, over time, some employees started being rude and giving me dirty looks when I order. One woman even asked me why I only order chicken.i don't mind being open worh people, but that question didn'tcome from a good place. If they couldn't do it, they should've just told me from the beginning. The manager even yelled at the only woman who was trying to be nice. The woman that apparently has a problem with me initiated a conversation in Creole with the friend in front of me. Which made me and my friend very uncomfortable.
I know things get very stressful throughout the day, but this whole situation was unnecessary and avoidable. Finally the only nice young woman kindly said that they can't do that.
Unfortunately, I won't be eating in this place anymore because of how poorly a simple situation was handled.

I’ve eaten at every Chipotle in the Boston area, and this is by far the neatest one! They didn’t just throw my bowl together like a grumpy middle school lunch lady. I ordered triple protein, they were placed side by side neatly, and the pico was spread evenly. First time experiencing this, definitely my go-to Chipotle from now on! The staff was also super friendly and smiling which makes for a great experience. I made sure to leave a nice tip they absolutely deserved it.

The food, both taste and texture, is on point, the portions are very big for what you pay for. The atmosphere is... really it's mostly a place to pick up the good food to go elsewhere but they do have cramped seating for roughly 20 people.

This place has a very casual and fun vibe. The staff greets you with a big smile. The menu is not too large but big enough to make you want to order everything!

I never heard of Mexican sandwiches but glad I tried it. It was amazing! Their tacos and plantains are blasting with flavors! So glad we found this place.

Let’s be real. Boston isn’t exactly overflowing with great Mexican restaurants, and when it comes to Fenway, it feels like a desert. El Pelon used to be the most decent one in the area, but its quality has gone down in the past few years. I used to order their Platos for delivery occasionally, but I recently had a bad experience with the pork and chicken platos. Both meats were dry, and the toppings lacked the punch of flavor you'd expect. Even compared to local chains like El Jefe’s, it fell flat. The Steak Platos I tried during lunch were a slight improvement, but not enough to quench my Mexican cravings.

It’s a shame that El Pelon is still considered the best takeout Mexican option near Fenway. Not sure if I’ll be going back.

This review is not to bash this small business, but it wasn't what I expected. My family is Mexican, and I've had good, authentic, Mexican food. This wasn't it. I ordered a steak taco, a chicken quesadilla, and a kids cheese quesadilla. Their tacos don't have the standard ingredients you'd find on a taco - raw onions and cilantro. The flavor of the steak wasn't great. The chicken quesadilla was overwhelming with the amount of chicken that was in it. The chicken also had light shades of pink, making me put it down. My child said their meal was good, but I didn't try it. You can't really mess a cheese quesadilla up. The kids' meal came with tortilla chips, which tasted stale and old. The vibe of the restaurant was cool and different, but food wise, it was not great.

Small burrito spot in Boston. Fairly expansive menu the torta was best, was complimented well with a flavorful sauce in every bite. The quesadilla was heavy on the meat but felt it was lacking in cheese and other flavor. Burrito was good, surprisingly fish burrito packed the most punch in every bite.

This location gets really busy but they're usually well-staffed which helps keep service fast. The employees are also very friendly. Only downside is that there isn't much seating. There's 5 two-person tables and a small bar that can seats 6. Food and drink are your standard Starbucks fare. Two single-stall restrooms in the back as well. Definitely more of a grab-n-go type Starbucks feel.
Some of the best customer service I’ve ever experienced at this particular Starbucks!
The employees are kinda loud sometimes when they were talking to each other. Not a very good study space. But the drinks are good.
I had some problems ordering coffee on the mobile app, but a beautiful lady (staff) was very friendly and patient in helping me out. I'll be coming back here to buy again!
Went 3 times to get a cappuccino, only 1 out of the 3 was it even decent. Other 2 times it was the most watered down flavorless coffee I've ever gotten

Always love having lunch in McDonalds.
The location is near my campus and the resto offers plenty discounts.
I recommend you to order using the McDonalds Apps and you will grab a bang from your bucks.
For example, I got the drinks, medium fries, & bacon burger for $7.5 (include tax)
Plenty tables to sit and there is clean restroom

The order I placed took over an hour although it’s a fast food place. I would somewhat understand if this was a typical restaurant but this is a fast food restaurant. The moment the order arrived it was cold, half the stuff I ordered were missing too. I’m pretty sure anyone could make food faster than these people

They provide insufficient and even worthless service to couriers. When there is an available glass place, they collect the couriers in front of the tiny window and keep them waiting. What they did was very wrong and ridiculous!!!

Their staffs are friendly. They are able to send food to your table, and give you ketchup. You can always find a seat, free refills (except McCafé), and rest room. If you know how to combine discount, deals and rewards on your app, the cost will not be high.

This McDonald's is my new location to get my iced coffee. Staff are extremely friendly. And I love the music they play.

Also please don't put liquid sugar in my iced coffee if I don't ask for it. I'm asking for splendor I don't need additional sugar

I had lunch with a friend at this traditional style diner in Brookline.  My friend ordered pancakes, which came out within 10 minutes of ordering them.  He said they were decent.  I ordered a turkey club with fries.  The problem was my sandwich didn't arrive until 15 minutes after the pancakes! My friend had already finished eating! My sandwich was okay,  but it shouldn't take 25 minutes for it to come out,  especially since it wasn't that busy.  The onion rings we ordered were also just alright.  I can't recommend this place although the server was friendly.

Super adorable place with incredible service! We came on a Monday afternoon, so there were probably four or so other people there. The service was super quick to bring out waters and our orders. We got a bagel and an order of french toast. The french toast in my opinion was a bit too egg-y and bland for me, so I will not recommend that. We did have to go back inside to ask for the check after a while which I'm sure is just the diner's attitude of having us sit around for as long as we wanted.

Purchased a breakfast sandwich for me, my daughter and husband. The sandwiches were amazing. It’s a little pricey for a sandwich especially on wheat bread but it was just so perfect this morning as we were out and about.

Was riding the C-Green Line - - saw this place out the window.  Came back for lunch.  GLAD I did!  Monday was 'meatloaf day'.  Excellent food, friendly staff - - "I shall return." - - Douglas McArthur
(actually - he was not with me - - and I did ask for extra gravy.)

SADLY - - I made a SPECIAL TRIP from Revere to eat there TODAY, Thursday, Sept. 12, 2024 - - - and was greeted with the SIGN that said they had FINALLY CLOSED the business PERMANENTLY - - - but - - hoping to get a restaurant to rent the space.

ANOTHER VICTIM of the BIDEN-HARRIS ECONOMY.

Was in the area and found this gem. Breakfast was amazing. Everything was cooked perfectly. My server was in a great mood. She got my order perfect. Some small talk. It was definitely the atmosphere that wanted their guest to enjoy everything.   Thank you for a great breakfast.

I sat there and unfortunately had to listen to one of the staff members (a man) bullying two other staff members (women). Whoever reading this from the Dominos, I hope you take necessary measurements immediately to prevent mobing in this branch.

Don't order from this place. Got 2 out of 3 items of my order wrong which isn't bad...but then the receipt is attached to my order. How tf does a Domino's drive unable to differentiate a box of paste from a box of chicken wings? Almost everyone I know who's ordered from here had an issue with their orders.

Had quick service. Was very efficient, no hassles encountered. The food tasted pretty good as well.

Had the five toppings pizza using the offer on the app.

I don’t know why the other reviews are so critical the staff is always friendly and yes they can be busy on weekend nights so expect a longer wait but you can fix that by ordering before the rush or place an order and pick it up after an hour! The pizza is regular dominoes pizza not the best but you know what you are ordering it’s what you going to get for the price especially in the city it’s great to get a medium two topping pizza for 5.99 instead of 20 bucks. They alway get my order correct and usually ready on time but I pick up never done delivery so can’t say much about that!
They refused to honor the coupon. Manager was extremely disrespectful and refused to remake wrong order. She claimed that they did not have the pan to make a large pizza

The slice will get it's job done, but it seriously was one of the worst and most expensive slices I've had in Boston.

Came in for a quick slice, chose two slices that looked better than other ones. However, was very disappointed - especially with the dough, which was really chewy. The bacon and ranch was really, really salty, too. The cheese slice was better, but still far from good.

The slices are not cheap (they start at $7 and go up from there), which I kinda get because of the location right next to Red Sox stadium, but it's still a pricey slice of pizza.

Sorry to give one. We order hotdogs here and the taste is terrible for $6 and the size is so small. Even 711 have a bigger size and better taste for $2. So sorry perhaps you guys need to improve the food quality instead of just rely on premium location near boston red sox.

I don’t like leaving bad reviews, but if it will save others time, money and a bad experience, I make the effort. I couldn’t finish the slice, it was so bad (and I was hungry!). It’s also outrageously overpriced at $11+/slice.  Opt for Joe’s in Cambridge; New York Pizza (various locations) or Supremes on Mass Ave.  All solid stand-bys.
Went in at around 11am and yet the pizza looked and tasted old with congealed cheese. Leaves me to believe it was left over from previous day(?)
Great canollis for $2!   Pizza is so good too.

We stopped by after Journey Def Leppard concert at fenway park.  Had a great experience.  Cheese pizza was excellent.  I asked for my pepperoni pizza to be put back thru and burnt.  They did it right away and brought it out to me.  Excellent as well. Then had the hot dog.  Asked for it to be burned on the flat grill.  Same thing.  They looked after us very well.   Thanks for tge great food and friendly service.

The barista Alex, he is very rude and mean. My friend ordered two drinks for us on the app ahead, when we got to the store to pick up the drinks, one of the drink was ready and the other one was not. Since she ordered ahead and the status showing the order is completed, she checked with the barista to confirm it is not ready yet(we have no problem to wait couple more minutes, just want to confirm no one else took it by mistake and the barista is aware of the drink is not ready). The barista Alex, he looked my friends up and down, said “no it is not ready, if it is ready then it is here”. We were so confused about his mean and unfriendly attitude, but we still said “ok sure” and wait. Then we watched him laughing with his other co-worker, talking about something, then pick up a cup asking his co-worker “hey is this with the xxx tea?” While he was working on that drink we felt the micro aggressive atmosphere that he intended to show and teach us “don’t ask and you have to wait”. We are not sure if he is a part time who is really young and lack of work experience so he don’t know how to work in retail or he is just simply intend to do so because he is not a nice person. Either way he is THE MEANEST PERSON I have ever met in a Starbucks. To the store manager, if you want to keep the location’s good reputation, employee training is essential, I guess especially for Alex.

I am generally easy going and really don’t like to leave reviews like this- baristas take a lot of abuse on the chin and deal with irritated and obnoxious customers all day long - I’ve been there and believe that they’re often doing their best and deserve better treatment across the board - from both Starbucks as an organization and the general public they wait on; unfortunately today’s visit was a truly terrible experience.

I walked in maybe 3 minutes after ordering, it’s mid morning and they’re busy so I expect to wait 5-10 mins, surprisingly there weren’t many people in the store - kale and mushroom egg bites were already sitting on the counter (okay wow +1, that was very quick!) - 15 minutes later I’m still waiting on two drip coffees. They finally show up and I walk back to my office. I just opened up my egg bites and am greeted by two dark brown shriveled hockey pucks that were lost in the back of the oven last month and were just discovered this morning - unfortunately not worth walking back 10 minutes to wait in line and request a replacement but hopefully this review is seen by management and used to train staff on what’s acceptable to serve.

I can handle food being well-done / “crispy” but these are inedible and completely unrecognizable from the product I ordered - if they were donuts or pastries I could have at least reconstituted them by dunking them in my coffee - to quote a well known Scottish chef, “What A SHAME!”

Hands down the best pumpkin 🎃 spice latte (PSL) I ever had. Everything was so right about it. Very polite and caring clerks and baristas. The order was taken care of in a very timely manner. One of my favorite spots in Boston University right in front of student health services. There are chairs available to sit. The music is right and the vibe is just great!

I ordered my coffee, the barista was polite and friendly. I sat down to drink it and watched the two baristas speak respectfully to each other about improving the cafe, resolving scheduling snags, all the while serving customers kindly and efficiently. I don't really like Starbucks coffee...but whenever I'm in the neighborhood, I'll be back.
Added some good food. I am getting food here as well as it taste fresh and it is not junk/

The food was edible, the decor was basic, the service wasn’t the greatest. We went to eat somewhere else but it was closed at 3 so we ended up here. We were the only ones. The waitress brought our menus right away and gave us time to review. She brought us room temperature water and sat on her phone. She came and took our order. The meals were made from scratch. I had veggie noodles and my daughter had dumplings. The veggies were bok choy, carrots, sweet peppers, scallions and onions. It was a little salty. We were hungry so we ate it. An older woman brought out our meals. She smiled. That was the warmest part of the customer service. We didn’t wait for our bill, we went to counter to pay and left. We were thanked as we walked out the door.

It's not gourmet, but it's simple home style Chinese cooking, served piping hot.

I dropped by and ordered Mapo Tofu, and it came out in just a few minutes. It was freshly cooked, piping hot, full of flavor, and really just hit the spot.

For a quick meal, if you're not looking for anything too fancy, it's a good spot.
$20 noodle in lamb soup with little lamb and a $4.5 pork bun with little pork. Not worthwhile at all. The waiter is ignorant to my feedback.

Bad food. This is the worst tomato egg I ever had in my life- they don’t even care to cut the potato properly! The whole food is weird and no favor. And the price is unfairly high for just vegetable and really small rice. Will never come back again. I regret I have to pay for their food bc this doesn’t even worth $19. I left half because it just can’t be swallowed. As soon as I put down my bowl although there are half of the food left. They gave me the receipt immediately. I don’t like that.

Oringinally it looks good and the size is big, but did not taste good, I only ate a little bit and asked to take out, first, the noodles look in a little amount in the container, I doubt the waitress did not take the entire amount from the bowl. Secondly, she did not take the sauce at all. Thirdly, she asked me to pay in cash instead of credit card to avoid paying tax. As a Traditional Beijing Person, I strongly recommend no one goes there!!!

My husband and I were so pleased with our meal here during our stay in Boston! Lovely service, and EXCELLENT food for the price. You can tell how much pride they take in their restaurant. Our meal was about half the cost of other sushi places, but better than what I’ve had in a long time! My husband got the chicken ramen (the broth was incredible) and I got a sushi combo, which came with a small salad, miso soup, and a drink. The sushi was wonderful, and the rice was seasoned perfectly and so soft and fresh. If we’re ever in the neighborhood again, we know where we’re going for lunch!

stopped by this place as i was walking by and dined in with a friend. we shared the sushi. valentines roll was really good, so was the cosmo. i could kill ten of the onigiris. super filling and tasty. service was very nice and everything tasted fresh. no major complaints, its worth a visit if you're nearby, hungry, and want something light.

Stopped in for a late lunch. Got a Hawaii maki roll, side of white rice, and the pork buns. The sushi roll was really good. Nice textures and flavors. White rice wasn’t amazing. Wouldn’t get it unless u need a good cheap void filler. Their soy sauce was good. Helped with the rice. I’d pass on the pork buns. The sauces used on them were the only good part about them. Service was good. Nice interior too, was well kept. Overall, I’d go here again for the sushi if I was walking by.
Excellent. Not overpriced, delicious sushi in a casual comfortable environment. Staff is very nice. Great lunch special deals!

This place is the best!!! It has been a sweet second home for me and my best friend since we moved here for college. The sushi always tastes fresh and so flavorful. Not to mention their great desserts. And the amazing waitress that always greets us is a plus!!! Definitely would recommend

ChIJrTfggfZ544kReYYJNxLgKx8.name: Au Bon Pain
ChIJrTfggfZ544kReYYJNxLgKx8.address: Harvard Vanguard Medical Associates, 133 Brookline Ave, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text: Au Bon pain used to be one of my favorite cafes but the location I went to was below average at best. The staff were least bothered when serving and the food was completely mehh. The coffee was just plain and the options were very minimal. I love au Bon pain in Dubai but this was a far cry. Will not be going again.

The lady in there was so nice to me she was very helpful she did an amazing job specially with the time that we're going through at the moment she did everything she took her time making my sandwich and on top of that she had to ring me up she was so clean and professional and I'm so thankful for her for what she's doing! Thank you Ana Duran !!!! She the best!!!

My daughter and i just ate the roast beef sandwich, although it was good and it was the only thing we both had eaten all day, when we got home my daughter got violently ill...she had avocado on her sandwich...i really would like to think it wasn't the avocado
Better than I expected, croissant was good, special order was fine, still a nuked egg can only be but so good
This place doesn't close at 3pm, so this should be updated to 2pm. And it's kind ridiculous that it closes so early. Can't wait for Panera to move in

This joint's got some serious culinary cred, tossing taro into the mix. It's a short stroll from my place, and curiosity got the better of me. Thankfully, the menu delivered. Only downside: the tiny space feels cluttered, earning it 3 atmosphere stars. And, seriously, that trash can outside needs some serious de-stinking action - a good cleaning and a discreet relocation, stat! On the bright side, the staff is fantastic - friendly, helpful, and totally on it. the crew's awesome -
Too bad the stench kept us from dining al fresco.
the plants 🪴 could use some love water them please 😅

Super busy on Friday afternoon and great service, drinks, and food. Got an ube milk tea which didn’t totally agree with my stomach solely because I got whole milk but still good, Also got the classic cold cut bahn mi which was yummy. I would love to come again and try other things on the menu. I would recommend this as a casual place for anyone in the areas.
Great place to work and eat some good treats. Ube latte sugar free is bomb, matcha is okay and the sandwiches as well. The crepes are great too

The owner and the staffs are really friendly and so kind. You will definitely enjoy this coffee place. Drinks and foods served quick and tasted great.“Iced Saigonese” coffee is so authentic. Cute spot for pictures and studying or even working. What more can you ask for?

The store is moderately quiet and a good place to study or read. When I went, there was no AC so it was a bit humid inside the store. I got the dragonfruit lemonade and a vietnamese iced coffee. The coffee was good but the lemonade was too sweet and we could not finish it.

Highly recommend!! I usually come here for their pad thai and other "dry" dishes which are always so delicious! I finally tried their soups which were, unsurprisingly, also so delicious! The service here has always been quick and the prices have always been reasonable for the past 4 years. Also the Thai milk tea is great - the flavor is not too strong and the consistency has always been very smooth!

Delicious Thai Food near Boston University.
The service was fast, and the food was delicious.
I ordered pad thai & tom yom soup, at least I could overcome my home sickness with the food ☺️

their pad Thai is my literal my comfort food
I love this place and put it in my budget to go here once a week, I love their pad Thai specifically, it’s never dry and has a good amount of peanut. I’ve had this pad Thai so many times. It’s just nostalgic and it’s pretty quick and very delicious, also they serve good amount of food!
The curries are also soooo yummy
Can’t really go wrong w what you get
Go here! Love it.
10/10 recommend

The Thai noodle soup is super delicious, u can go with either meat or veggies, I ordered the chicken one and it’s so tasty and yummy to eat, I’ve been here several times and even every time I got sick this soup noodle make me feel better. Highly recommended!

I think this was the best pad Thai I have ever eaten. The portion was big enough that I did not think I would finish but it was so enjoyable that I did. The dishes I saw others order looked just as good. I highly recommend stopping in.

ChIJAAAAAAAAAAAR_tDcTeRFMlQ.name: Panda Express
ChIJAAAAAAAAAAAR_tDcTeRFMlQ.address: 775 Commonwealth Ave DINING SERVICES, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text: I like Panda. But this new kiosk system allows for orders to stack up to a ridiculous point. I ordered and saw that the wait time was 70 mins and of course there’s no warning so if don’t see the time before you ordered I hope you don’t have class soon. Plus the quantity of food you receive is abysmal. I paid $7-8 for a bowl and received 4 pieces of chicken
THERE FOOD IS NASTY! I ordered beef teriyaki and chicken and that tasted like jail food. I almost threw up in my own mouth.
If you're in a pinch, you'll be in and out quickly. However, the food is somewhat mediocre and the service is pretty poor. There are many other options in this food court that are much better.
First time going to one of these. It was a fun novelty experience and worth it for a quick bite if you like chinese food. Rice was kind of dry...
It’s a good place to eat , good with treating people for them to be patient and wait for their food and drinks.

While heading to Harvard, we stumbled upon a charming little brunch spot. The crepes were absolutely divine, with a wide variety of fillings to choose from. The owner was incredibly helpful and recommended some delicious combinations. The service was efficient and the portions were satisfying

Found while staying in Boston. Crepes are my daughter’s fave so I was happy to stumble upon this establishment. Best one she has ever had and served by the nicest gentleman.Thank you Crispy Crepes Cafe…

Great crepes, both sweet and savory. Service was quick and very nice owner and son. Also great salad and entree options with Moroccan flare. Prices were fair. We parked on Comm Ave right in front of restaurant but it was a slow Sunday morning. Music was a little loud with heavy metal during an otherwise peaceful brunch.

Great crepes and great service! I got a sweet crepe, it was delicious and a filling breakfast. Other people with me got savory crepes, and loved them too. The owner was nice and made good smalltalk too :)

Cute locally owned Haitian bakery! We got an assortment of pastries which were delicious and definitely will come back to try some of the meat pies and juices. Staff are friendly and welcoming, limited seating but gets great morning sunlight
Pretty fast compared to other Subway's. One time my sub was toasted without asking me.
Amazing sweet onion chicken sub Thursday night! Amazing staffs to everybody! Shomaury the goat made this sub!!!

I specifically asked the person taking my order to use a clean knife as I saw some tuna remains on it from the previous sandwich. But they just shook out the knife without wiping and used it for me. Disgusting service!

You can tell when someone really love their jobs by the way they greet and take care of you. Robert is just awesome. Great employee, just made me have a great experience there. Keep it up! I’ll definitely be back!

Every time I've come here it has been a great experience. All of the employees are
friendly and specifically Robert has been great. He remembers my order and always provides some fun conversation.

ChIJZwlU3mt544kRmGFPgWuiGsU.name: Dunkin'
ChIJZwlU3mt544kRmGFPgWuiGsU.address: 775 Commonwealth Ave, Boston University Bridge, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text: This is a Dunkin’ donuts express inside a convenience store, not a full dunkin’ donuts. They just have a machine for iced coffee and some donuts. They do not have any of the seasonal donuts.

The place is very clean, the employee named John he is a standup fella who has an awesome conversation with you and still makes everything on time for you while working by himself. One thing though is that who ever owns this place should not be making their employees who are making food and drinks also clean their bathroom. Not very sanitary but, every else is great employees and they make a pretty good coffee. Thanks John!

I placed an on the go order 3/2/17. My order was so rushed it was not made the way I requested. The coffee was burnt with no sugar and was a hazelnut shot instead of the swirl I requested. I was extremely upset I shop at this DD everyday before work. I don't want to discontinue my service for this mishap please honor your customers request.

I’m tired of coming here and having my coffee made wrong every time. I spend easily 60/80 weekly every time I order my ice cofffee caramel swirl milk only and every time I get it looks like a milkshake. I’ll go to the location in Cleveland circle, Morton st, roslindale, and Jamaica plain and they make my coffee correctly. The manager is very rude and nasty and gives attitude when I bring my coffee back to be corrected no matter what time of day I come I can always count on this store to mess up my coffee

If solid DD experience is 3 star, this place deserves 4.

The food is the same as every other DD, so it really doesn't come into play too much RE:rating unless its lowering stars. Here the sandwiches come out hot, cheese melted, etc. As they should be. Coffee rarely tastes burnt, also as it should be.

The extra star is for the employees here, who work quickly to move the line along. This DD is in Kenmore Square, so its rarely empty. And yet the line moves faster than in other less-busy DDs. And that's all I can ask for, really.

The staff is attentive and friendly. We had a few minutes of waiting while our waitress did other things but another staff member was happy to pick up the slack! The food was incredible. We had beets, dirty fries and soft pretzels! Everything was perfect. My husband ordered an old-fashioned and he said it was too sweet. Would definitely go back!!!

Audubon is a super chill and mellow bar with great bar food and drink selection. I had an Oktoberfest beer and 'A sure thing' mixed cocktail, which were both great, especially the cocktail which left me tipsy a few sips in 🥴. For food, I ordered the grilled cheese dip, roasted beets and churros (secret menu item lol because no desserts are listed). All of which were awesome, my favorite being the roasted beets. It wasn't very busy (Thursday night), so the bartender was very attentive and it wasn't too loud.

First off, whoever manages the music at this place please be my friend as the vibes are ALWAYS on point.

This place is great to go out for drinks later at night, or dinner in the evening! They have a menu that's on the smaller side but their daily special is always amazing! There are great cocktails, and all the staff are super friendly! Love this spot!

Parked nearby and needed a snack. The menu is small and the place is very busy and cozy. Def a local hang out. Service was a little slow. Tight seating. We ordered the daily special flat bread. Brussels bacon red sauce with balsamic drizzle. For the price Def not worth it. Barely enough for one, let alone two (16.00) the Brussels where huge and not very tasty. The crust had a good crunch. Def would try the chicken Sammy or burger. Overall, just ok.

We popped in for a quick lunch and I was pleasantly surprised who delicious the food was. The staff were lovely and the space has a nice feel. They have an outdoor back patio that is surrounded by bamboo with string lights overhead that would be an amazing spot in the to eat when the weather is mild.

The food here is very tasty and fun. Went for a walk and got some snacks. He chicken pita was really good. I love chicken. It is my favourite animal. The pita was tasty because it had veggies and chicken and nice saus! The soup was a tasty tomato soup. It was good. Some of the best, big strong men with tears in their eyes came up to me and said, “Tatte has the best tomato soup, Sir”. To which I replied with a stern face, “Never eat soup uphill me boys, never!” As I proceeded to eat my food and drink my coffee.

Thought to try this cafe while waiting for the rain to settle. Atmosphere is bright white, crisp and bustling freshness. Vanilla Latte was simply perfect! Desserts all looked delicious! We noted the menu does have a few good and savoury vegetarian options available. BUT..
They forgot about our ice tea order and we were left waiting for more than a half n hour. Only to have it taste like WATER, literally! No flavour at all. It was quite the disappointment bcuz everything is on the pricy side.

My bf and I came here for breakfeast as we wanted to go to the location in DC but didn’t know they were a chain. We were so happy to come here for breakfast! It was cute and air conditioned. We got two meals. The breakfast sandwich on a croissant was so flakey buttery cheesy and delicious! He got a grilled cheese with goat cheese and beets I think. It was different and not my thing as I’m a picky eater. We got a raspberry muffin and a tart and both pastries were yummy! Will definitely be back!

Another overrated coffee shop in Boston. The pastries are always old and unappetizing, and it’s so crowded there’s no place to sit or even stand in line without getting bumped. It’s not as good as it looks, and the place itself is quite unpleasant. I admire the employees for their patience.
The staff was pleasant. My Smoked Salmon And Avocado Tartine and cold brew were delicious however my honey’s House Breakfast Plate was delivered cold. They were very busy, nearly every table filled.
