My daughter told me about this place a few times before visiting. She missed the fried rice so much that she shed tears as she took her first bite. I must say, though it looks bland the food is quite delicious, well seasoned and flavorful. I'll definitely be returning
I ordered Bangkok beef large size. I wished the rice was more but the stew was a lot even for two. It tasted really good and not so spicy

This has been my go-to thai place for years now, and I stopped by again recently to learn that the food and service are still as amazing as ever! I've tried most of their menu and the food is very customizable and flavorful, and I always order a thai tea too. Overall great good and speedy service (also a bit frustrating to see poor reviews based on delivery issues that the restaurant has no say in)

I had to leave a review because the dishes we ordered through Uber eats were mostly inedible.

I like to start with the positives. The Tom Yom soup and Honey Chicken Wings were pretty good. Good flavor and cooked well.

I ordered the chicken Pad See-U. This was completely inedible. The chicken was dry and overcooked. It tasted old. The whole entire dish had zero flavor. I couldn’t stomach it and ended up tossing it.

My partner ordered the Khao Pad Thai Jungle Beef. This had very mild flavoring overall. He had to add a bunch of soy sauce to make it more edible.

This was the worst Thai food we’ve ever had and worst overall Uber Eats order.

Do yourself a favor and order from Rod Thai Family Taste or Thaitation in Fenway.

I've been standing there and waiting for additional more than 45 minutes for my takeout, which I expected to be done in after 30 minutes I placed the order, and the app says done. All other 10+ non-customers (app deliveries) were standing there and starring at those cashiers and waitresses, and they hided inside the kitchen. We saw all the food were well packed on the desk, but just turned to the other side, unable to see the name. We are attempted to ask could we check the name, they refused, we have to wait to be called. After another 15 minutes, they eventually came out, and started calling the name. Everybody who been standing there were freak out and exploded! WHY DIDN'T YOU LET US CHECK THE NAMES???!! So we don't have to wait while you're all hiding in the kitchen!

ChIJu68FA_h544kRFZ4pbYQVLcI.name: The Fresh Food Company at Marciano Commons
ChIJu68FA_h544kRFZ4pbYQVLcI.address: 100 Bay State Rd, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text:
BU Student here! I honestly love going to Marciano Commons (Marcys) every day!

I will say that basically the same food is served here, with the exception of a few departments. That being said, I don't mind that fact! I will eat literally the same thing every day and be fine! It is very predictable what Marcys will and will not have.

Also the bakery is AMAZING. They are always churning out new creative sweets that I like to sample!

I absolutely love coming here for breakfast, lunch, and dinner!
One thing to watch out for is what I call "rush hour" which basically is weekdays from 11am to 3pm where it is really busy there. If you go before or after those times though it is so nice!

I love the views of Kenmore from the back side of Marciano, that is my favorite place to sit.

Also like, unlimited ice cream? Yes please!!

To sum up though the enviornment is pretty upscale, food is yummy and consistent, and the bakery is amazing.

Easily the best Dining Hall here at BU.

Its better than most dining halls, but  most of the food served is honestly just a garbage attempt at making "upscale" food for university students. Most of these experiments fail miserably, leaving poor students to find alms at restaurants near by. The omelets tend to be rubbery, but the breakfast food is decent.  The lunch service is a hit or miss- and in general, the burgers are overcooked and the entrees are under seasoned and bland. Dinner is normally terrible. It's still better than most dining halls though.

Some of the staff are genial, polite, and nice. Many members are apathetic, but that is normal with most food service jobs. I do have to say that the plates and cups are not often very clean.
Best dining hall at Boston University. Sometimes the food options are very good and some are not so good.

This is a literal garbage dining hall. The staff has egos bigger than donald trump and they don't know how to clean the cups at all. Asking for anything outside the normal "everything" that students usually ask for is meant with at least an eye roll and look of disdain. I can't even ask for fresh eggs without fearing for my life. They have no respect for cultural foods and believe putting pickled cabbage on a dish makes it "korean". The ice cream is alright most of the time though, so 1 star.

This place has really gone in the dumps since coming back from online classes. The plates and cups are really dirty and you really have to stand around for a while trying to find a clean fork or cup. The food upstairs is usually all dry, unseasoned and tasteless.
I had the honey habenero wings, which are fall of the bone delicious. The atmosphere is lively on game day.
Great service and great food, but be aware, the nachos are super, super cheesy. Almost too cheesy... something I never thought I would ever say in my lifetime.

Service here is awful. Hostess couldn’t be bothered to stop reading her book, told us to sit and she’d grab menus. Never got menus, and were promptly ignored for 15 minutes. We got up and left. Never again

We were waiting for them to open so we could eat and were waiting under the awning outside, it started to rain so a few people rushed over to get some cover. The employee then came outside and retracted the awnings so no one could stand under them to stay dry… immediately decided we do not want to eat here. Absolutely disgusting behavior and refuse to support this establishment.

It was nice to be able to stop in someplace so close to Fenway Park!  Their menu is on the smaller side, but for what they do offer the quality and portions are good!  They offer seating both outdoors and indoors, outdoor seating is a bit less crowded and noisy, all in all a good place to grab a bite before the game!

Walked right in and seated immediately on a Sunday afternoon. Merch, NFL games, bar, delicious food. Everything is charged separately. The burgers, fries, sides, and drinks each have a price. Coke products, thick, delicious milkshakes! Outside seating with a fireplace. Meat is cooked to requested temp. Walking distance to Fenway and colleges. A few parking garages around. Crew are really nice and chill.

All I need to say is YUM! The food was on point! Everything came out hot, fresh and delicious. They catered to my son’s Gluten allergy with care. TOM is amazing! He didn’t just give customer service, he gave us a guest experience to make us feel as if we were a guest in their home. He blessed our family with an experience we won’t forget.

We might have visited a bit outside the run of the show but we don’t care. This is a must visit.
The staff works hard for the customers, you can see it. There were plenty of ungrateful individuals that clearly treat restaurant staff as less than. I hope, it’s our hope that as customers we are pleasant and clean up after ourselves.
We love the staff at Wahlburgers and want you to know you are appreciated.
First time visitors and the food was delicious. Especially the onion rings, seriously delicious. My wife had a veggie burger and she loved it. I’m a big boy and had a double cheeseburger outstanding.
Service was superb especially since a rude table of 7 snuck in and stole a table.
If I had the money I’d have tipped more.
Yes I took pictures of Wahlberg’s movie posters especially “Shooter” in the bathroom hall. Which by the way, bathrooms very clean.
Thanks again for all you all do and making this a great experience.
No wait on a Saturday at 3. Food was good but not hot. The guy that waited on us wasn't good or bad. Not friendly but did give us refills.

The our burger is delicious first time trying the burger and it was melting down my throat!! The tater totes were great plus the bbq and walhburger sauces were good for the burger and totes!! I would recommend this to anyone who loves burgers happy Halloween!! Plus we got the truffle fries which were outstanding!!

I love sweetgreen and it is always my go to when traveling being vegan - reliable, quick, and healthy! The customer service at this location was awful, they could not be moving slower, so disinterested, and understaffed for the amount of customers. The bowls are always great though once you can get past the inconsistent service!

One more time this location disappointed me.
The veggie not fresh, some are very dirty. Broccoli and meat were overcooked, very bitter, the meat was very hard to chew, like a stone.
I give this location so many chances. It’s the worst
Really healthy food 🤗really affordable 🫶🏻❣️ such a nice people working there
Absolutely love sweet greens. The staff was so nice and so was the food! I ate everyday there and I miss it already!
They truly make the best salads! I always place an order through online and they are always so quick with it. A must try!

Chill vibe relaxing cafe with delicious eateries. Wonderful choices at bakery and coffee(I had cold brew) was above average taste. Staffs are nice and friendly and the tables were clean. They have some goods of their own brand. High ceilings provides comfort. It will be my 'to go-place' whenever I come to Boston.

Iced americano was teeeerrible, tasted like wood. I couldn't finish it. But we got the seasonal orange rosemary cupcake and it was really moist and well made. The orange frosting didn't taste of much when eaten along with the cupcake though.

Highly recommend Flour!!!
The banana bread was top notch! I can’t wait to go back soon to snag some to-go!
The cauliflower naan was one of the yummiest things I’ve eaten in a long while! So much flavor!!! Another notable item was the Boston Cream Pie!

Only down side to this location is the lack of seating. We had to wait a bit for a table and we already had our food so we were just standing around until a table opened up.

By now it’s a known place to get a good snack and coffee. But I was pleasantly surprised. I think I discovered the best donut in Boston so far.
Filled with vanilla cream (sorry, I’m not a fan of raspberry jelly) it was perfect. Not über fancy (although bacon does sound good) just a perfectly fried piece of pastry with its genius filling. Not too sweet and very satisfying. And no point I felt that I wanted to share it with anyone.
Guys… don’t ever change the recipe! And thank you!! It will be my ‘goto’ place when I have to explain to anyone what a donut should taste like.

The food was really good. Staff were friendly and nice. However, cleanness of tables, not much.
Highly recommended regardless.

Felt a little let down after eating here. The lobster roll was good but the bun is not toasted which gives it kind of a soggy feel and it was filled with shreds of lobster that were mushy with very few chunks of real lobster on top. The real winner was the brown butter soft serve,  that was very welcome surprise.

Eventide was a great dinner stop before a concert at Fenway park! The atmosphere was very trendy and the food was delicious!

If I could only recommend one thing, it would be the Bangkok Derby cocktail. It was so refreshing and overall delicious! I also got the Summer Sangria which was also fantastic, and my friend really enjoyed the No Way Frosé!

The food was also great. I got the Fried Calamari, which was a good amount of food. My friends got the Lobster Roll and Clam Chowder. They said both were super flavorful! Be aware that the lobster roll is very small, but that is reflected in the price.
Randomly saw this place while on a walk and decided to try it out. So glad we did, friendly staff and amazing food. Highly recommend the lobster roll, oyster roll, and calm chowder.

Grab a delightful oyster martini before a game at Fenway?  Absolutely! I highly recommend Eventide for anyone looking for fast casual before a Red Sox game. Reservations were a must. Food was fantastic. Didn't engage much with staff but food came out fresh and hot. Atmosphere seems a bit cold. We sat at a counter along the window and it wasn't the greatest. Overall, super satisfied with the food and would definitely go back the next time I'm in Boston.
Fish sandwich was food, fried fish is made in house. The oysters were the BEST, horseradish slushee was interesting! Clam chowder was good, not heavy.

It’s a pity that I can’t rate the service as zero star.
And the coffee in Pavement Coffeehouse tasted like pavements indeed. The cashier/barista is the meanest person I’ve ever seen. The way he talks was like I owed him a two million pay check.
The floor is unbelievably dirty (basically a frat house)

This place wants 14.99 for a loaded breakfast sandwich and on the weekend their cute little store can’t even handle a 10 am rush. I waited 20 min for a bagel and ice tea. The bagel was barely warm when I got it and the ice tea they didn’t even follow what I asked for. Do better especially if you’re charging those prices in the Fenway area
Nice big, bright open space. We both had toasted everything bagel with cream cheese - delicious and generous! Terrific double shot cappuccinos! Taken care of by sweet counter staff.

The coffee shop is very busy and semi-chaotic. I love the decor and the atmosphere of the shop, the bright colors for the tables and the dim lighting is very comforting. I highly recommend doing online ordering instead of ordering in store.

Good coffee, bad experience with the service.
I bought a bag of coffeebeans and a big coffee (was charged full price for the coffee despite a small being included, that's what it is). The lid wasn't fully put on the cup so the cup collapsed in my hand, scalding it with coffee. I should have been more carefull no doubt, but it frustrated me how ignored I was by the employees when I asked for the toilet to put on cold water and made them aware. The way I was looked at, apparently frustrating them immensely. I have never experienced such a bad treatment before. I'm sorry to say it and it's too bad as I have satisfactorily bought coffee beans from them before, online.
My take home, buy their beans and coffee online or elsewhere, not in the Fenway coffeehouse.

A great lunch spot or cheap take out. Can’t say much about delivery, but ordering in person we have had good experiences. Pizza is so crispy and the ingredient choices makes the experience so fun. Salads kinda suck, half half option is healthy but the salads honestly are not great. Pizza is delicious at a great price, never disappoints.

Because this is the second time I’ve had this type of experience with this location…I’m writing this review.

Please do NOT order online from here. I’ve had no luck with accuracy of orders. The first time, the toppings were incorrect. As of writing this review, my ENTIRE order was incorrect. The drink was wrong (diet coke instead of coke zero) — this wasn’t bad, and is understandable.

BUT, my pizza actually didn’t even have sauce. It was just cheese and pepperoni, and it was missing the condiment. Seriously though, how do you forget sauce on a pizza?It’s even specified in the order. Granted, it’s almost 2 hours until closing, and the work staff might be tired (as someone who used to work in the food industry, I get it), but this location has some serious quality control standards. I’ve attached images, as well.

NOT an experience you want to have when getting home from work late.

Worst experience ever! I had ordered vegetarian pizza cause I am a vegetarian. They sent chicken pizza with mushroom toppings that I didnt order for and this was not even the first time they have done this. They suck! This would be the last time I would ever order from them!

This is paradise for pizza lovers, I’m really tuff about giving someone 5* but this place blown me away.
The way off preparing, baking, making your own pizza, baking speed and the most important thing is the Flavor and the taste!
Lots of flavors equally stretched out tru whole pizza, it was like the harmonized note of the symphony orchestra and that Note was touching my soul with every bite!
Employees were so nice, fast, communicative, polite and really helpful, service was impeccable

My bestie and I had veg out! And Oh Boyyyyyy! I can’t stop braggin about it! The best Pizza I’ve had in 25 years of my life.
Really set the blaze! We literally topped our pizza with all the veggies. Perfect price point and perfect place.

You ofcourse have to wait on game days but hey it’s worth the wait!

Cheeky Monkey is actually a hidden gem in the Fenway Area to me. There’s a pool table location in the back on a quiet night it makes a great chill date. Food is good but little pricey. I order wing got about 6 pieces for 18 bucks. But other than that it’s a great time and different atmosphere than most bar in the area. I recommend checking it out.

This is a partial review. I arrived 20 minutes before closing. Unfortunately, they already stopped serving. There was nothing they could do. Still, the waitress sold me some cans to go. I promise to be back in September to check your tap. The cans were excellent.

Great atmosphere and fancy interiors. Got more lively as the night passed. We had drinks and food and enjoyed everything. Their garlic bread which came with the pasta I ordered was a bit chewy and felt rubbery in texture and wish it was crispy!
Service got a little slower as the place drew more crowd in after the Redsox game but with the music and the vibe we didn’t mind waiting.

Great place to pregame before a ball game. The food was great, many drink options, but we only saw our original server like twice. Someone else brought our food (and immediately left- he seemed to be running all the food from the kitchen) and another person brought our check/took out payment. It wasn't a bad experience, but we would have ordered more if there was someone to order with. It was busy so longer wait times were expected, but she seemed to disappear.

Pretty large space and great location however once seated it took 20 minutes for someone to check in on us. It was pretty empty and many servers/bartenders standing around. Once a waitress spotted us, service was great from that point on.

We went with their Spinach Artichoke Dip and Fried Calamari and it was great. I’m still craving the fried calamari!

Beer Selection - Sour Batch Kehd and we would drink that again!

Entrance felt like legit Japanese Restaurant and then inside was a different bar/modern Restaurant feel. Service was great. Waitress was kind and checked on us often. They also gave us this pill-tissue/hankerchief where you dip in warm water and it blows up so you can wipe your hands. Apparently a welcoming gesture in Japan for guests. Pretty cool.

Started with drinks and I tried one of the two frozen cocktails called Pina Colada. It was like a slush and with strong alcohol. I liked it a lot, except it would melt if you drink too slowly 🥹. It was one of my highlights though - would highly recommend.

Food was overall decent. My favorite was the brussel sprout - oooh that was yummy. Sushi + fried chicken + fries were decent/normal, nothing eye-opening. Kimchi fried rice felt a little 'wet' for me and a little too salty (especially for someone who cook the stuff). I felt the portion size was on the smaller end for the price, especially as a shareable. It felt more like appetizer, size-wise.

Dessert: honey cake was good, though I prefer it cold than warm. The home-made ice cream felt more like gelato. It was sticky and not my favorite kind. A little too sweet. Was unique texture and shape. I think it was like peanut butter-sesame-matcha flavor for the sundae?

Overall, great service and atmosphere for a get-together. Personally would recommend the Brussel sprouts and the Pina Colada. If you are looking for something truly Japanese this ain't the place, but if you want something more casual, pub-like, something-for-everyone type of place, give this a try! Cheers 😊.

Our meal there was fantastic! Our server JJ was so amazing she was so sweet and gave great recommendations for food I had the spicy salmon roll it was quite good! The atmosphere is very nice and fun food came out pretty quick and well prepared! I would definitely recommend you go to Hojoko it was great!

Hojoko is a very hip izakaya connected to the Verb hotel, with rock n roll music playing over the speakers and trendy dishes that are interesting and tasty. I had a japas matsurika beer because they were out of Sapporo unfortunately. I had the snow crab California roll, the shiitake mushroom tempura roll, and the traditional Japanese honey cake. All were good, but not knocking my socks off. The shiitake roll was honestly weird because of the truffle foam on top, not my thing I guess. Prices are okay, I spent about $80 with those four items mentioned plus tip. It was also very dark inside and not too busy, but maybe there's more people on the weekend.

Amazing! Attached to The Verb and so delicious!! The bar tender was friendly, made great drinks and our meal was excellent!
The fried chicken I added to my salad was the best ever!!!

creative cocktails, amazing food, and cool interior!The karaage chicken was crispy and well seasoned, and definitely try the shiitake mushroom tempura roll—the foam looks kind of strange, but it tasted incredible. Can’t wait to come back!

I purchased 2 pizzas on gluten free crust. People rave about Otto pizza, but I must have caught them on an off day, because while I love the array of toppings I can choose from, it was just good not great. It did arrive nice and warm, which is more than I can say for my last pizza delivery that was from a location much closer.

One order was wrong, and the other was not right either, and one side of the bottom of the pizza crust was charred- and not the nice pizza char, but had a burnt taste.

What was supposed to be a 4 cheese pizza with extra sauce butternut squash and roasted garlic instead had ricotta and parsley.

The pepperoni pizza had the mushrooms, but almost none, and only one one side really when it was supposed to be the entire pizza. I was wondering if they ran out but didn't think to call and tell me and ask if I wanted something else.

The delivery driver also went to an address down the street. All he had to do was keep driving straight down the street as he was on the street. Told me it took him to another address on the same street. I told him to keep driving straight. It was super weird. I felt like he was filling in for someone else, maybe?

I emailed about what happened and haven't heard back from them.  Variety is the spice of life, so go, but be mindful what you paid for may not be what you get.

Meatballs and pizza slices are fabulous!  My favorite pizza is the butternut squash.  The sodas are the best; the flavors rotate often.  Try the blueberry or root beer.

July 7, 2022:  I noticed that the special sodas are gone and have been replaced with more commercial sodas.

Ordered half-and-half mushroom manchego & herb and chicken & basil, two-cheese garlic sticks, and tiramisu. Everything tasted ok. For the pizza, the crust was crispy on the edge, but a bit soggy in the middle and the chicken lacked flavor. The garlic sticks didn’t taste like garlic at all. The tiramisu was delicious.

Ate during a campus visit. Was able to get a GF and vegan cheese pizza to avoid allergens. Also had a slice of regular pepperoni too. Taste of both pizzas was good. The allergen free one was particularly good.

We ordered take out. The pizza toppings are very eclectic! We ordered a pulled pork spicy pizza and green onion, as well as the mashed potato and bacon pizza. Also for good measure, a pepperoni and sausage. Excellent taste, nice thin crust, and good flavor. The pulled pork was also nice and spicy. Most places around here make their pizza really thin for some reason, must be a north east thing. Would recommend, the pizza options are great.

GO GET YOUR FOOD HERE!!!

I absolutely love this place!! I first came here when I was saying goodbye to my mom when she was dropping me off for college and this was the best place I could've chosen. First off the service is amazing! Anytime I walk in I'm greeted with a smile! For someone who gets anxiety when ordering food, they are so patient and sweet when taking your order! I've come here about 5-6 times now in a span of a month, alone and with friends just for their food and for the vibe this place gives. My favorite is sitting in the middle table eating my baked pasta with meatballs and catching up with my besties or sitting by the window and people watching those who walk by. When I feel like I need to eat something else other than dining hall food, this is my place to go due to convenience of location, quality of food, and service. Plus I never finish the food so I get to take this back to my room to heat up for later eats! (Bang for your buck🤑🤑) If you're looking for a place to eat around BU's campus I totally recommend!
Great eats. Honestly my favorite Gyros next to Zo’s. Good selection, fresh n hot slices, and incredibly friendly staff.  A must if you’re a BU student!

This was the best pizza in the world I go there all the time now they made me stop going to my other pizza shop I used to go too I love the customer services ce too they are such nice people too love all the food

Someone told me to try out this place. I walked 30 min. I walked in.
Modern look of an old school Greek fast food place.
How do I know I worked in some of them.
The man on the counter was very polite, took my order. Great.
I ordered 2 large subs, 2 slices and French fries $50!!!

The receipt they give is the total without breaking down all individual items. I said to myself if the food is delicious I will not be mad if I paid so much money. I tried the food.

The two slices were ok. The crust of the pizza was wrinkled l, which means was left out for a long time uncovered and during baking have this type of crust. The tomato sauce was good. The slice itself was on the thin side, hard to eat it directly, needs to use a fork and a knife.

The 2 subs tasted very blend. No salt no black pepper on the steak bomb. The bread could be a better quality.
The French fries no seasoning at all. Bland tasting.
My discovery, someone then they packed the fries put salt and pepper packets on the bottom of the bag. On top put the plate and the French fries. How the hell you can go to the bottom of the bag take salt and pepper and season your fries?!

In conclusion. This is a typical low quality fast food place. They can do much better but prefer fast money and lacking details.
Incredibly kind staff/owners and excellent grub. Gyros are great!

Delicious and affordable bagels in town
There are plenty tables in the resto, and u won't need to wait too long until ur bagels are made.
Really love the Nova Lox.

The resto is located underground near the art & science school.

Whoever was hired for T/Th mornings recently, what the hell?? Twice my order has been missing items or not scanned through. These are college students who are trying to get to class, and you waste people’s money by not putting in any effort. This is such a hassle and you lose business.

Hidden gem in the GRS building. Back in Spring 2020 (before covid lockdown) I was teaching in basement of GRA building and discovered this hidden gem right inside the university. I love their bagels and cream cheeses and the vibe there. Recently, they are also using a very seamless system for ordering through your credit card or BU ID that connects to grubhub. Orders are fast. Staff are very helpful. Great vibe for studying. Doesn’t feel like a basement. Highly suggest all BU students to try it. I ordered lox bagel and it was very delicious. The ordering menu allows you to customize the ingredients.

Update: sadly, this place is closed during Summer 2022 semester.

Amazing bagels and fast service. If you can't settle for the bagels at fast paced, commercial coffee shops, this will definitely hit the spot. The texture and flavor is perfect and they have some classic but also unique choices of cream cheese. Personally, I have not tried any of their sandwiches, but I've only heard good things.

I come here for breakfast at least three times a week. The staff is friendly and helpful, and though the lines seem long they move incredibly fast. The food is delicious, filling, and cheap. I normally go with two everything bagels with egg and jalapeno salsa cream cheese, and I'm normally full until dinner. Every now and then they bring around specialty chocolate muffins- go for it. They're amazing and just as filling.

ChIJ3fZRDB1644kRJ3DO4tHvExE.name: Foundation Room Boston
ChIJ3fZRDB1644kRJ3DO4tHvExE.address: House of Blues, 15 Lansdowne St, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text: Great intimate space for a concert. Just a few couches and bar tables, otherwise standing room only. Bar has limited selections.  Cozy and beautifully creative space.

If you're willing to buy a ticket to a show, you mine as well get the Foundation room if it's available. It is expensive to become a member but sometimes you can add it on for $20-$30. I find myself wanting to spend as much time in the Foundation Room as I do the venue floor while there.
The decor is phenomenal, psychedelic, and the pictures are just a fraction of the splendor. Theres plenty of space to settle in with a large or small group here, and there's even a deck! There's TVs throughout the rooms with stage on display.
Also separate bathrooms and bar from the main show. (drinks are cheaper downstairs though)

Love the bar/nightclub before and after concerts. The menu is pretty good and the dj’s in between are pretty cool. Love the classy, upscale vibes while at the bar. Being able to grab a drink 10x faster than folks inside of the venue during concerts is an incredible perk. One of the best parts about going to House of Blues in Boston is enjoying the foundation room.

Waste of money. They tell you that you’ll get early access to the venue and then you end up being let in AFTER people who didn’t purchase The Foundation Room. Had I known this, I would’ve never wasted my money on it. They shouldn’t false advertise or have their staff lie to patrons if they’re just going to have security hold you up.

I went with my girlfriend to dinner before a show. We ordered different drinks but neither drink had any alcohol. My drink cost $15. It was supposed to be a rum and coke but there was no rum. My girlfriend had a cocktail with gin. I strongly dislike the taste of gin but when I tasted her drink I could not taste any gin. Then we ordered food. My girlfriend ordered the cajun pasta . It tasted good but barely had any chicken or sausage. I ordered a burger. I requested it be cooked medium. It was barely cooked so I had to send it back. It took several minutes for me to get our waitress' attention. My girlfriend finished her meal before my second burger arrived. This burger was cooked medium rare. It was still undercooked but I ate it anyway because the show was starting soon.  The undercooked burger tasted fine.

The build your own bowl is excellent with lots of options! Normally I'm intimidated by the custom "custom" menu items, and just default to a usual, but not here. You order off a tablet but it's relatively straightforward, and vegan options are clearly marked.

This place is great! The first time coming here, my family dropped in while walking by. The staff was great with my food allergies. They double checked their readily available allergen guide for the sauces and made sure to cook my food in a separate wok. Portions are generous and the food was delicious. High chairs are available. The next time we ordered online and did store pickup. The process was super easy. I will definitely be back!

Delicious stir fry noodles! Kids and adults can create their own bowls 🍲. Portions are quite generous and the food tasted delicious! The cheesecake cream based dessert topped with pecan and cookies crumble was super delicious too!
Love the outdoor patio area “when it isn’t raining 🌧️”

This was a great meal! I was able to custom build a rice noodle bowl with all the add ins.
Worth the price for the food and service. They do disclose about possible cross contamination with Gluten, so go at your own risk of allergies.
Oh my goodness! I ordered the Spicy Garlic Noodles and wow. It was amazing with adding shrimp in it. Every bite was a delight. It’s like a food orgasm from start to finish! Well done.

The food is really good, the people that prepare it are very very nice and they take the time to make sure that the food is well cooked and they are very polite!!!!

The atmosphere would be excellent if the “money man” wasn’t condescending…. He referred to me as a “kid” when I’m 37 years old plus a “kid” is a goats child and I am proud to say I am not that but am a Son Of The Most High GOD!!!!

My first time here was awesome! We choose this place to eat because it didn’t scream “we charge tourist prices” for two tuna subs and two pizza slices it was 30 dollars. I would have paid $100.00 for that $30 meal. The shop is owned by a father and son duo. I met the son and he was cracking jokes with us and making us want to stay longer. I was with my landlord and I made a joke while my landlord was paying. “I just paid my rent and now he is spending my rent money on me” as we were getting ready to leave the young stud said “are you sure he is your landlord he kinda looks like your dad” my father died a month ago and my landlord has tried his best to be a positive older roll mode in my life and that comment made my day. I love the food, atmosphere, and the outstanding customer service. I will stop by for a sub every time I’m in the area.

This place like one of those old school pizza shops I used to go to when I was younger, Small but cozy feeling with friendly customer service. Since they didn’t have whole wheat subs I was lucky enough that they offered whole wheat wraps. So I got the whole wheat steak and cheese wrap, the French fries and a ceased salad. Everything was pretty good not like crazy over the top good but just right and if you are in the area it’s also perfect for a quick bite on the go, whether that be a slice of pizza or a sub with fries.

Typical small pizza joint. Really fast service, pizza was delicious. Kinda felt like I was bothering the guy making the pizza tho, due to the fact he is talking to someone on a Bluetooth headset the whole time.  We'll be back next time we are in the area.

Look, the pizza is covered with thick cheese, with a rich taste and a crispy crust and soft inner layer. The cheese pizza from this restaurant is really delicious, and I recommend everyone to come and taste it.

A warm, ‘kozy’ restaurant that I would absolutely recommend for authentic Chinese food! This no-frills restaurant was still busy with deliveries when I arrived with my party, but the person working (which we learned was the owner) there was so welcoming and friendly. When we arrived at around 7 at night, it was pretty easy to find street parking on the side streets.
When my table with some elderly had some trouble with the QR code scanning for menus, she handed us actual menus without asking which I was very grateful for as many places don’t do paper menus anymore.
We ended up ordering the beef noodle soup, cumin lamb, juicy pork buns aka soup dumplings, chive and pork pan fried dumplings, fish filet with sour napa, and chive pockets. All of these items arrived so quickly and were so delicious! One of my friends said it was the first time he had something this good since he left home. The 红烧牛肉面 beef noodle soup came steaming hot with chewy 好弹牙 ‘QQ’ texture noodles and the beef had the perfect amount of chew and soft tenderness. The 孜然羊肉 cumin lamb was amazingly spicy with all the classic garnishes including onion and cilantro, while the 韭菜水饺 pan fried (pan fried is an extra +$1) chive dumplings and 韭菜盒子chive pockets were crowd favorites for sure! When we were chatting with the owner, she was so sweet and let us know that all the noodles, dumpling wrappers, and baos are handmade! The pan fried chive dumplings and chive pockets had that perfect 酥皮 flakey crispy outside but super flavorful, fragrant, steamy hot inside. The 小笼包 juicy pork buns is now one of my favorites in the Boston area as the skin was thin but buns were super juicy and meaty. Tip—ask for their homemade chili oil for an extra kick on all your dishes.
I personally am not a big fish fan, but I tried a bit of the 东北酸菜鱼 fish filet with sour Napa and as a new dish to me, I would describe it as tasty but quite sour. My table found the fish quite good and the sour Napa to be fresh especially as soup with white rice. We also tried their handmade buns at the end of dinner and it was the perfect end to a 10/10 dinner. Our total came to around $80 dollars before tip.
I will definetly be back to try out the rest of their extensive menu—which has something for everyone from lo mein to dumplings to fried rice!

ChIJzWP0yvB544kRsdRj8-SyKYk.name: Basho Express
ChIJzWP0yvB544kRsdRj8-SyKYk.address: Warren Towers, 700 Commonwealth Ave, Boston, MA 02215, USA

reviews.text:
Tried my first ever sushi burrito/wrap here today. Loved the concept, but this place doesn’t do it well. The wrap was large, but lacked in the flavor department and as people have stated in their reviews, the burrito was overstuffed so it didn’t fully close which made eating messy (although I did appreciate the extra food). I paid $15 for the wrap, however given the minimal flavor and poor presentation, I feel it was very overpriced. Not to mention, customer service could be better.

Also, since when does lettuce pair with sushi??
Very tasty and customizable burritos or bowls. Fast service (ordered and left within 5 minutes). Would recommend a bowl as the burrito broke. Milk tea was good but the boba wasn’t well made.
Found a toenail in my eel roll the other day. Asked for a refund and they cussed me out in another language

Somehow this place is not what it was before. The food is only limited to bowls and wraps. The ingredients are different. I used to have the beef bowl a lot. Now the beef bowl is small, only has three ingredients (beef, lettuce and ginger) all looking being stored for a while. The beef quality and taste is really poor. There is no sauce added any more. This is a joke for a 15-16$ meal.

The place used to have special drinks and snacks and sushi boxes. Now all shelves are empty and the only drinks are water and coca. People working there don’t show much excitement running the place. One of the entrance doors is broken/locked and they didn’t bother to either fix it or post a sign to let the customers know they shall use the other door. I won’t come back.
This is my 3rd open sushi burrito this year. If the workers are taught how to close them properly that’ll be great. 🥲

Disorganized. Tons of staff but they all looked confused about what they were responsible for. I waited 30 minutes for an espresso before leaving without it.

Organization of staff by a cafe manager and better communication about wait times would go a long way to reduce staff stress and improve the experience for customers.
The pumpkin latte wasn’t really pumpkin spice flavored or filled up all the way. The three cheese grilled cheese was relatively good and a nice place to use dinning points.

i got the matcha berry daiquiri with no ice. it was really really sweet, but if the sugar level was okay it would’ve tasted so good. it was on the more expensive side though. the workers were nice and relatively quick.

My new favorite coffee shop in the area! I used to love Saxbys back home, and so it was great to see another Saxbys make its way back into my life. The vanilla bean cold brew and steak grilled cheese are great go-to’s!

After opening the new building on BU campus, the lines were long, yes. But besides that, this place has the best black coffee. The first time I asked for black coffee, for some reason they made me a latte. But these are students working here and I don’t think they want to be baristas for the rest of their lives. Everyone makes mistakes. I’m not going to expect an exquisite meal from students who are directionless and are barely adults. I expect decent service and not a long wait. And that’s what I get nowadays here!
Great Thai curry, I had the vegetarian one with tofu. Flavors on point, good portion for $14. Service was also good, and plenty of tables in their restaurant.

Very nice Thai restaurant.  Central location on a main street (hard to find parking). Pleasant interiors and atmosphere, authentic and fresh food in generous portions. Great service, reasonable prices. Very good experience 👌

Very good restaurant I frequent when I’m in town and looking for Thai food. Beyond the usual fare, they give some nice surprises, like this beautiful presentation of Brown Sugar Hawaiian Fried Rice (pictured, on left), along with what’s left of the Mango Curry, the taste of which we all loved.

The vibes are so good in here, super clean and the decor is rlly cool! I got the babe ribs and the meat was SO JUICY AND TENDER a bit spicy for me but just right… get with rice and you will def have leftovers. Thai tea was good too and the fresh spring rolls were super yummy. Everyone is very friendly and it was v good

Brown Sugar Cafe is my favorite Thai restaurant.  The food and service are always impeccable.  My favorite lunch order was the chili duck rice plate with the lunch special of the side salad and chicken spring roll.  I would ask the server to omit the onions.  For dinner, there was a pork dish on the Thai special menu -- last item on the pork dishes page, that I liked, but didn't know how to pronounce.  Brown Sugar is beautiful inside with high ceilings and pretty decorations.  The ribs appetizer is addictingly good.  The Thai iced coffee and Thai iced tea are both wonderful, and I ask for little ice.

This definitely hit the spot for vegan Asian food! The woman at the counter provided excellent service and checked on us multiple times to make sure we were happy. The No Name dish was so good and reminded me of my pre vegan order. We also got the lo mein and pepper steak. The lo mein has room for improvement but the pepper steak was really good too. Would definitely recommend and come back!

Super sweet staff. Relaxing environment. I’m still blown away that this place even exists. A VEGAN Chinese restaurant? Right here in Boston? Wow! I really enjoyed the No Name -especially as leftovers, however I was disappointed that the Wontons didn’t have a creamy interior, it was just “meat”. I was expecting to bite into a warm, gooey filling but it was just dry “meat” stuffing which wasn’t very seasoned. The chick’n fingers would’ve been absolutely perfect except they were too sweet and lacked in the flavor department. I would recommend going! It’s not often you come across an all vegan Chinese restaurant and their menu is extensive. They even have lunch specials (only valid on weekdays)!

Been there repeatedly and tried several different things on the menu. But, my favorites have always been "Grilled Vegetarian Chicken" appetizer and the house special "Sweet and Sour Sensation". I did not like the House fried rice though. Plan to return to explore the rest of their menu and perhaps the buffet option that they offer once every month.

I love that this place exists! The atmosphere was quiet and the service was good. The food was tasty. I thought that maybe the vegi-chicken was just like tough tofu though so that was a bit disappointing. I would probably order something different if I were to come again, but I got the veggie tempura and vegi chicken vermicelli noodles and it was alright. Good prices!

Everything we had here was delicious! I would highly recommend the tempura, scallion pancake, and sautéed spinach for appetizers. For mains, everyone liked the No Name best and the Grasshopper Special. It was really delicious and I’m so glad it was all vegetarian and mostly vegan!
They were so attentive and accommodating for our big party. Thank you! We appreciate you all! We’ll definitely be back!

Just as good as the Chinatown location. Great place to bring a date our a large party of people to enjoy shabu.  The meat is of great quality and the appetizers are great too. The smoothies are amazing here too, don't miss out.

This place is one of the more popular hot pot restaurants in the Boston area. There is a small parking lot off the side street if you are lucky. The restaurant is huge with bar seating having individual pots and tables with shared pots. Service was attentive and quick.

The house broth is included and any flavor is an extra charge. I got the A5 beef regular combo and it came with a choice of noodles and assorted vegetables. The udon noodles and beef were fresh and not frozen. It did give an impression of higher quality than other places. The flavor broth is really good and the portion for the regular meat combo was a good size for one person. You should get a regular combo for each person.

I loved this place!  We came without reservations relatively late (8:30 ish).  While we did have to wait a bit to be seated bc they were short handed and looked like a couple larger parties.
Our food came relatively quickly.  They were able to accommodate a party comprised of a vegetarian + a meat eater.  The pots are divided nicely to support this.  They also were happy to make a few broths vegetarian.  The veggie plate was amazing and the meat was far more than one person could eat.   The vegetarian in our party complimented the vegetarian fish included on the veggie plate. The broths were delicious, the meat was high quality, and veggies were fresh.  Our server was friendly and checked on us frequently.

Went to Shabu Zen for hot pot as a delayed Chinese New Year celebration. On a Saturday night unless you come really early like at 5pm, be prepared for a wait of 30-40 minutes. The service is a little slow and the chatter from patrons can be loud and fills the room. On the positive side, once the food arrives, things move fast. We ordered 3 of the meat combo dishes. The beef, lamb, pork and chicken were of high quality and there were lots of vegetables with each order. They have a good selection of sake and beer and the coconut sorbet was a great way to top off the meal. Parking was hard to find and the small restaurant parking lot fills up fast. All in all it was a very good experience.
This shabu shabu place in Boston tops the list with its wide broth choices, fresh and tasty meats, and great service. It's a great spot perfect for any meal, making it a must-try for everyone.

I come to this hookah lounge very often from miles a far but I keep coming because of the food, smooth shisha and great customer service. Juan makes perfect shisha and Mario is amazing too. He has the best customer service and he treats us with respect and kindness . Thank you Mario

Great shisha lounge!
Authentic feel, with a complete menu, Their house tea is very nice and comes with refills. Most importantly, their shishas/ hookahs are well prepared. They have a very nice selection of smoke flavors and combine them upon request. They are regular with changing coal.
They use Al Fakher smoke, which is my favorite. Really enjoyed the happy hour from 2pm. -6pm.
I enjoy going there to relax and study, the people are friendly and very professional 👌
Congrats! Keep up the good work!
P.s. Sundays, they have live music, and they also serve food throughout the week (Mediterranean food).

From the moment you walk-in the door until you leave , this place treats you like gold ! I’ve felt so welcome by so many people ( Manager , host , everyone working there ) I can’t imagine going anywhere else for hookah , best food , best hookah and BEST LIVE MUSIC EVER ( Friday and Sunday) . Everyone should goooooo there I highly recommend this beautiful place .

This place used to be good when I came ten years ago but now is very expensive for the things they offer, hookah isn’t even highest quality. additionally they limit only 3 people per hookah, even if you have a fourth person who orders food and drinks they say if it is more than three people you must get two hookahs which is ridiculous, so if you go as a group make sure everyone smokes. otherwise you’ll end up with a hookah that is just sitting there. Last time I went was my last draw here, for ONLY twenty minutes, three people one hookah (only two people smoke) and four spring bottled water final bill came to $60, how idk…also be aware they have 18% gratuity”COMPULSORY SERVICE CHARGE”, which they don’t tell you about upfront just automatically added to your bill, and there isn’t any obvious hung up signs that says that. So you get that service charge added regardless of the quality of service you got.

First time here, and it did not disappoint! The place provides a cozy and inviting atmosphere, with great service to match. I could totally hang out here all day. (By the way, it's fine to go alone!) I know I'll be stopping in again

Outstanding! My son and I checked it out before a BU hockey game and  went to our "go-to " Italian subs, and we agreed that they were one of the best ever. Loaded, and there's a ton of meat under there. Rolls are the key, and they were very good.
Nice job. Have to confess that the wings left a little to be desired, but they were ok.

T Anthony's Pizzeria is a must-visit for pizza lovers in search of a late-night bite. Situated in a cozy corner of the city, it offers a laid-back atmosphere with ample seating in booths. The star of the menu is undoubtedly their thin, crispy NY-style pizza, which is served with generous toppings that hit the spot every time. What makes the experience even better is the friendly owner and staff who always make you feel welcome. And don't miss out on their super crispy curly fries – they're the perfect complement to any pizza order.
Great Italian sub and they had a lot of space to pick a table and eat it very convenient and the service is always above and beyond
Really hit the spot with the late night slices but never have I seen ham being thrown like that in any other place, kinda wild 😂 but hey, it was good, not saying otherwise!

My experience is only for take out and I have done that multiple times. the pizza is HUGE and one of the best I have had , (My first ranked pizza is on my profile) Nonetheless it is good for a slice or the whole thing. Also mozzarella sticks are great but what makes them even better is the awesome marinara sauce that they give !

A simple yet solid everyday to casual date sushi place. For a good price, you can enjoy a fairly decent meal with sashimi (premium raw fish) and mouth-watering specialty rolls. The environment is relaxing yet still proper, and the hostess is personable yet attentive.

Their Volcano Roll has become my boyfriend’s favorite dish here for its giant serving size, variety of ingredients, and deliciousness.

I vote this place for a weekday/Friday dinner with an intimate, peaceful dinner with your close friends/loved ones.
Delicious sushi and amazing & patient staff. A must try if you’re in Brookline!
We got a few rolls for a quick lunch. The miso soup was okay, but the rolls were great. Super fresh and with a lot of fish. Good rice to roll ratio.

Hidden gem for sashimi!
Genki Ya is pretty unassuming on the outside. It is equally unassuming within. Staff are friendly, but it looks like most sushi places you may have been to around Boston. However, one should only judge sushi on the quality of the fish and this is where Genki Ya shines. Their sashimi is some of the most tasty and freshest that I have tried in Boston--at any price point. The fact that they are relatively inexpensive is a bonus. Maki rolls are mostly of the standard variety, but are well made, but some of their special makis will surprise you. However, I always go for the fish. Highly recommended for a pleasant surprise.

Great food that is slightly more expensive than other sushi places I've been to but it's also in Coolidge corner which is notoriously more expensive. Service is fast and friendly. There are tables inside and out when's it nice outside

Shockingly bad service which made for an awkward and inadequate experience. I ordered food and 15 minutes after it arrived I hadn't been checked in on, hadn't been offered another drink, had no water, et cetera . . .but the server and another worker came and stood across from my table talking about video games for several minutes. Did they think I was going to dine and dash? Why would 2 workers ignore a customer actively dining, but stand chit chatting facing them? If they have 5 minutes to talk video games, surely they can offer a customer water or other items to order. At the very least, someone could have asked once about my order and/or offered more. I worked as a bartender for a decade. I can't imagine acting this way when my livelihood depends on tips, or even just being so rude to another human. I expected to buy a somewhat overpriced meal, and that's what I signed up for. I did expect at least decent service, or just basic courtesy. Food was good - not great, but I read the reviews and was on board for that. Side note: the atmosphere inside seemed nice, and the bartender also seemed friendly and competent in contrast. It's a VERY rare occasion where I tip less than 20%, even for mediocre service. I tipped 15% which I'm sure is most than most people would have in that situation.

It's noteworthy that the bathrooms are tiny and hard to navigate for an ambulatory person of any size. Anyone requiring a cane, chair, or other ambulatory needs would be unable to utilize a restroom.

In summary: When serving patrons, a few moments make the difference in your pay. Pretend to care for 3 sentences worth of interactions at least.
Perfect place for a game!  We enjoyed great food and lots of TV's.  Add a dash of friendly service and we were highly satisfied.  Dessert was a Celtics win with drinks.

Food is decent, I really liked the burger and wings. A lot of fried food here but it has a good vibe and it’s a great spot for sports. Our waitress was super inattentive however which definitely lessened the experience here

I’ve been a regular here with my stepson, both for dine-in and takeout, and it’s usually great. But tonight was a letdown. We had two servers who were clearly not communicating—one brought the wrong food, didn’t take our order properly, and never brought a second drink. When I tried to clarify things with the second server, he was condescending and dismissive. We ended up leaving and dining elsewhere. Disappointing experience for a place we usually enjoy.
Great bar with many beers on tap.  The French Dip sandwich was perfection and the onion rings were amazing.  Service was fast and friendly.

I loved the decor of this place. A koi fish pond next to a gurgling waterfall and a Japanese waterwheel are among the first sights to greet you as you walk in. The waiter was very friendly. The food was cooked to perfection.

I recently visited FuGaKyu Japanese Cuisine for the second time, and it was just as impressive as my first experience.

Located at 1280 Beacon St, Brookline, MA, this restaurant offers a stunning ambiance that truly captures the essence of a traditional Japanese establishment.

The design and decor reflect a meticulous attention to detail, showing that no expense was spared in creating a beautiful and authentic setting.

I ordered a sushi roll, sashimi, and a friend selected two other items from the menu. The yellowtail I had was exceptionally fresh—so much so that the fish practically melted on my tongue.

It was an outstanding culinary experience. Overall, I would give FuGaKyu five stars for its setting and the quality of the food.

The only area for improvement was the communication with the female hostess, which felt a bit less welcoming, possibly due to a slight language barrier.

Despite this, it did not detract significantly from the overall experience.

I look forward to returning and enjoying more of what FuGaKyu has to offer.
Delicious Sushi, great drinks and overall nice atmosphere. Be prepared to spend 💰.   Great date night spot!

Beautiful restaurant, Japanese interiors, coy pond and fountain, waitresses wearing kimonos, private booth. That adds a lot to the experience. We went there for dinner on a winter Saturday night, two couples.

The food was good and nicely plated, the prices were high but fair, considering the quality of the restaurant.

The main downside is the rush. It started with the revolving water fountain in the vestibule. Instead of flowing slowly to create a relaxing atmosphere, it revolves fast and gushes water loudly. Then in the booth, the waitress was in a hurry to take orders, to remove dishes even when not fully eaten, and to bring us the bill at the end. We paid and then stayed a bit longer to talk, we did not order dessert or tea since the check had been closed.

I did not appreciate the wipes they serve with the meal. Those are very bad for the environment, not biodegradable. I'd rather use the napkins and wash my hands in the restroom.

I understand they need to make money and clear tables, but when paying around $50 pr person- you want to enjoy and take your time.
Perhaps it's more relaxed on weekdays.

Good restaurant, enjoy !

I can't wait to go back here! It was an amazing time to spend with family. It reminded us of the time we spent in Japan. The food was perfect, and the atmosphere really transformed inside the building.

I've been going to Korean Garden for several years now, and their service and experience never disappoints.

There isn't much music that plays at the restaurant, but the restaurant isn't too loud. The tables are nice and there is a big walking space to move around.

The service is quick and good. They exchange the water bottles quite quickly, and the food comes out pretty fast.

The prices for the food is decently priced. The Korean BBQ does run a bit on the expensive side if you are a big eater, but the tteokbokki and appetizers are reasonably priced, even lower than other restaurants. The quality of the food is pretty good, and tastes quite well with the banchan. I would recommend the hot pot bibimbap, it isn't too hot when it arrives at the table but keeps the food warm, and it can form scorched rice at the bottom of the pot when done. The portion sizes for the korean bbq is good for a party of around 4-5.

A majority of the tables are suited for parties of 4-6, I probably wouldn't come here with a party larger than 8.

Solid Korean food, every time. I've had their BBQ and mul nengmyeon before, so good. This time I got their braised short rib soup and my goodness is it good. Comfy soup with glass noodles, flavorful soup, and soft beef. it so soft that even the tough part closest to the bone is soft. The side dishes are good too. Their seafood pancake is great. It's such a solid place every time I go. The owner is super nice too!

Overpriced and Disappointing Kalbi

My boyfriend and I visited Korean Garden on a Wednesday evening and were disappointed with the $37.99 Kalbi beef (kitchen-cooked) The portion was extremely small, with thin, chewy pieces that tasted nothing like short ribs and were intentionally stacked to look more while leaving huge spaces on the plate to make it even emptier. When we asked about the portion, the server said it was their standard size due to the cost of short rib, but we’ve had better quality and larger portions in other Boston Korean restaurants for less.
While the rest of the food tasted good and reasonably portioned and the service was fine, the Kalbi beef was a total letdown.

My favorite spot in Boston for Korean comfort food.

For the past few years, I’ve been trying to find a reliable spot for Korean comfort food. Early last year, I finally settled on this place and have been ordering from here at least once a month.

This isn't the place for the most extraordinary Korean cuisine you'll ever experience, but it reliably satisfies cravings with just the right balance of spices and authentic flavors. Although they specialize in Korean BBQ, I find myself drawn more to their Garden Specials and soup-based entrées. The Gopchang Bokeum and Kimchi Stew are some of my favorites. These dishes capture the essence of Korean cooking with well-balanced spice levels and rich, satisfying sauces.

The portions are also quite generous for the price, so if you’re looking for a good value Korean comfort meal, this is the place to go.

I lived in Korea so many years and I had a so many Korean BBQ in Korea and also entire different countries like Asia/Europe/America, this place was one of the best one, the servers are all professional and friendly, main server lady is completely controlling all the tables like a orchestra conductor, she was the best! Thank you so much and I will definitely be back soon!

I recently moved to Boston and found my new go-to spot for North Indian food! The Mattar Paneer was flavorful and rich, perfectly balanced with a creamy mango lassi. To top it off, the Rasmalai for dessert was just the right amount of sweet to end the meal on a high note. If you're craving authentic North Indian cuisine, this place is a must-visit!
A very nice cozy place for the people craving North Indian food. Must order methi matar Malai , cherry naan and mango lassi!

“Absolutely loved this place! The ambiance is warm and welcoming, and the staff is incredibly attentive. Each dish was packed with flavor and beautifully presented. A must-visit spot for anyone looking for a memorable dining experience!”

Ordered through Uber eats worst Dahi Papdi chaat ever eaten the papdi had some weird aftertaste.No mint chutney provided with the chat. The chutney provided with it was so bad. The paneer naan barely had any paneer in it. The daal makhni was super watery. Very disappointed since I have ordered  here from before.

Recently I visited Punjab Palace with my friends for dinner. I had a wonderful experience not only with the food but also staff are very professional and well-mannered. I ate Sahi paneer, Dalmakhni and Paneer tikka masala. In Sweet, there are many Indian options like Gulabjamun, Mango lassi, and Sweet lassi.
If you are Indian and miss Indian taste in the USA, must visit Punjab Palace with your kith and keen.

The seafood was fresh. I was so impressed by the server Maria. I didn’t know how to crack the lobster and crab and she really took the time to give us a mini tutorial. Thank you again.
I will definitely come back!

We ordered Sicilian style seafood pasta and squid ink pasta, and they were amazing! Super fresh clam and tasty flavors.

They serve the pasta with the hot pan together, which is the similar style I had in some restaurants in Sicily. This makes the dishes keep warm and retain the flavor longer.

Also, their service is also friendly and quick. Very impressive dining experience there.

House made ink pasta.

Fried calamari- good, I like the warm marinara sauce
Littleneck clams- delicious!
Monkfish Marsala- delicious, the lemony sauce was lovely
Calamari ink pasta- a little pungent, good textures

This is my 2nd time having dinner at the Daily Catch. The taste of the food is consistent with their branch in North End, but the difference in serving size was quite distinct.

They serve a small loaf of bread as a starter. You can top it with parmesan cheese or dip it in olive oil, both of which are present on each table.My wife and I shared 2 half portions of Alfredo and Aglio Olio.

The aglio olio was fantastic. It comes with ground calamari. I recommend asking for the spicy vinegar and that to this dish.

The alfredo was good, but nothing mind-blowing. Make sure you order it with protein because it's a bit lacking without it. I wish we ordered it with scallops.

Overall, it was a good experience. The server was great and accommodated special requests from a family of 4 that dined while we were there.

Just ate this fine establishment last night. Waited about 30 minutes to get a table. It's first come first serve and I absolutely respect this. I was able to stand back and watch this jewel of a place be ran. Felt like I was at my late Nona's house watching magic happen. When you can witness the hardwork and heart being put into a family owned buisness makes you want to jump in and help. The only issue I would just disrupt the play. I will make it a habit to visit this resteraunt every time I'm in town. Mad Mad respect to you guys!!!
Also, got the Lobster fra diavolo and Ceasar salad. Watched all the tables around each dish looked, smelled, and by their own words were awesome.
So real simple you in town go get you some Daily Catch.

I orderd k meal to go for 6. It comes with  12 wings and 6 drums with the house  fried rice  and fries .  The chicken flavor I choose was yangnyeom, this is a new flavor for me I  really enjoyed it. The other flavor was spicy and I really enjoy the heat as well. The fries was very crispy and delicious. The fried rice was very flavorful me and my family enjoyed it all . The really special thing here is the fry chicken, the way they cook them is very unique I honestly don't know how they do it . I love it. I highly recommend this place especially for the Chicken wings..

Since the owner changed, EVERY DISH HAS BEEN A TOTAL DISASTER! I love sweet soy garlic chicken, but now it’s overwhelmingly SALTY. I'm so disappointed and will not order here again. If you want to taste the real BonChon's chickens, then you'd better to go to BonChon in South Quincy.

Food Quality: 🍽️🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟
Bonchon never disappoints. The Bulgogi Fried Rice was an absolute delight, bursting with savory flavors that left us craving for more. The Chicken Wings, (half and half) were equally impressive, with their crispy perfection and delicious sauces.
Service: ✨🕴️🌟🌟🌟🌟
The staff was attentive and made sure we had everything we needed. It added to the overall positive experience.
Ambiance: 🎶🏞️🌟🌟🌟🌟
The restaurant's ambiance was inviting and its relaxed.
Value for Money: 💰😄🌟🌟🌟🌟
In terms of value for money, Bonchon is on point. The portion sizes were generous, and considering the quality of the dishes, it was great!
Overall Experience: 🌌🔮🌟🌟🌟🌟
The Bulgogi Fried Rice and Chicken Wings were beyond amazing, and the Tteokbokki was a delightful surprise- it was my first time trying this dish. I would wholeheartedly recommend all the dishes we tried.

Would you recommend this restaurant to others? Yes! Without a doubt.

Ordered takeout with the family for my cousins birthday. Got a large order of drumsticks, large order of wings and mini drums, and a medium spicy combo. Also got some japchae and some pork buns. Been here a few times before. As always, the chicken is GREAT. Balanced between moist and dryness, soy garlic is flavorful. But the spicy one… I’ll tell ya is where it is at. I have a high spice tolerance but this place always will make ya sweat. The thing is the taste of it is so addicting and you want more spice! The spice level is definitely much higher than the one in Lowell I’ve been to. The japchae was decent. The pork buns were a bit dry and overcooked. The seasoned fries were a bit cold and mushy as well. That and the fact we didn’t get the sides of radish, etc with our meal is the cause for the 4 stars and not five.

Chicken is hard and dry. Spicy sauce is better than soy garlic. Bathroom is dirty. Lighting is a bit dim inside. Just go to bbq chicken few minutes away. It’s better quality and experience with similar price.

Kaju is the best! The people who work there are so incredibly nice and they do a great job of ensuring that every visit is amazing. The food is always great and the wait is never too long. The prices are super reasonable too. I love coming here and I will always come back!

The kimchi was perfectly fermented, and the spicy pork was tender and flavorful. The staff was attentive and knowledgeable about the menu, making great recommendations. I also loved the variety of banchan served with the meal. The silky tofu and rich, spicy broth were perfectly balanced, with just the right amount of heat. Each spoonful was comforting and packed with flavor. This place is a must-visit for anyone craving delicious Korean food!

I was excited to try out this restaurant after seeing long lines outside at nighttime, but was sorely disappointed in my experience at an off peak lunch hour. The banchan (pictured here) was incredibly basic. Despite asking the waitstaff twice for a refill on the banchan, none was provided. Good luck getting any service here - besides dropping off the dishes and the check, no waitstaff came by and it was nearly impossible to get anyone’s assistance.  The tofu soup was passable, seafood pancake was soggy, and beef bulgogi was too sweet. I would not come back. I’d recommend you look into the many other great Korean restaurants in the area for better food and service.
We were in the area and found several Korean restaurants and decided to go to this one for the tofu soup. We ordered a mushroom tofu soup and seafood clay pot. Both were very good flavor

We were seated quickly, though the small space can get busy. They're famous for their variety of tofu soups—seafood, beef, vegetarian—with customizable spice levels. My boyfriend and I tried the kimchi and beef; one of us ordered a combo plate, which lets you choose a tofu soup and a KBBQ plate. We went with the galbi, and it was perfect. The service was fast and friendly, and the meal was delicious!

ChIJSTbQAOF544kRx-QSCbfJlcM.name: Scullers Jazz Club
ChIJSTbQAOF544kRx-QSCbfJlcM.address: 400 Soldiers Field Rd, Boston, MA 02134, USA

reviews.text: We saw Gerald Albright her and let me say he did not disappoint us.  He is still  as amazing as the first time I saw him many, many years ago.  The food and bar service during the show was phenomenal, and the staff was very attentive.   I found the food prices to be a little on the expensive side, but I guess you're paying for convenience.  The drinks were delicious.  Will definitely be back, but just for the show and drinks, definitely not for dinner.
Fabulous time listening to Saxophone player Jackiem Joyner.  His music is soulful and mesmerizing. Check him out if he is coming to perform in your city.

Great Jazz performance. Had close up seats but looks like there isn't a really bad seat in the room. Enjoyed having a beer and tasty crispy truffle fries during the show. Would continue to go back for other Jazz shows.

My only complaint is the high price to self park in the attached garage for the Jazz shows. Should be at least half of what they are charging now.

The space was a bit tighter and service a bit slower than expected. Your only parking option is in the hotel's paid parking garage.

That being said, all in all the wonderful live music experience made it all worth it 🎵 The musicians and the crowd had great energy. I would consider coming back again.

The space is cozy and the acoustics are fantastic.
The only thing that I didn’t like much was the chairs as they are uncomfortable.
Also, the tables are too small for 4 people.

Best Italian Food I’ve had in Boston by far. It was surprisingly interesting how this hidden gems 💎 is standing and making delicious food among other Korean and Asian restaurants in Allston!
The atmosphere is homey and very casual just like a down to earth mum & pup shops that’s been there for a very long time. Standing right in the mid of all Korean and Asian food.

Foods were all fantastic, tasty and delicious! Even the starter come in larger plates than we expected. Highly recommended. Would definitely coming back for more!

Best rack of lambs. It was cooked to perfection. Tendered, juicy, tasty. The whole experience was awesome, we also ordered chicken Marsala and the special mussels and haddock over linguine. The sauce for the Marsala was so good, it goes so well with the chicken. The portion was also huge we were so surprised. Would come back to try other dishes.

I recently dined here during my vacation, and it was an unforgettable experience. I thought I had Italian food before, but nothing quite like this. "Delicious" doesn’t even begin to cover it.

Our server, Chris, was exceptional. He was very helpful and friendly. He took the time to help me find the perfect dish, accommodating my restriction of no alcohol. I ended up with a chicken dish stuffed with prosciutto, spinach, and red pepper in a Alfredo sauce paired with the best mushroom risotto. We also tried the gnocchi in red sauce, which was delightful. The texture of the gnocchi was soft and well balanced with the sauce.

As bonus points, the parking in the area was much more accessible than other parts of town where we found it impossible to park at during a holiday.

This place did not disappoint. We would 100% return to eat here again. If you’re looking for an Italian cuisine and excellent service, this is the spot!

Great food at a little unassuming place. I’ve lived in Boston for years and passed by this restaurant a million times without much thought. We don’t really eat out much anymore as we’ve found food in Boston to be pretty lackluster, plain, and unseasoned, but not this place! We went after hearing a million recommendations, and it did not disappoint.

We were seated fast, and our server was friendly and on top of everything (she even switched to Spanish after hearing us speak it). There were people coming and going the whole time, so it’s clearly popular, but not crowded or loud.

Everything was so good, yet the definite highlight of the night was the Lasagna (it was the day’s special, I’m not sure how often they have it), it was heavenly from the very first bite. My husband is somewhat of a lasagna snob/aficionado, and he declared this lasagna as the best he’s EVER had, and said it was the best meal he’s had in Boston all these years. So that paints you a picture of how much we enjoyed our food.

Would 1000% recommend it!

Nestled in a neighborhood with a plethora of Asian cuisine, this tiny restaurant is worth visiting to dine. The wait was just about 20 minutes for three ppl, after call-ahead wait-list (not reservation). It is extremely loud in the space, as well as cramped tabling, so if you’re not a fan of a high decibel of ppl talking or being close in proximity to other patrons dining, you may wish to inquire about take-out. Server was friendly. Establishment was clean. Prices are insanely lesser than other restaurants that offer authentic Italian cuisine: $107 was our check for three entrees and two glasses of vino. Two in my party had house-made gnocchi with a red sauce. I had Veal Vitello Carlo, which is veal stuffed with artichoke hearts, prosciutto and Fontina cheese, in a plum tomato sauce with onions and mushrooms. Came with a couple potatoes and steamed broccoli. Was delicious! Highly recommend.

As a frequenter of Coolidge Corner, can’t believe we didn’t know about this place until yesterday, but now we’ve found a favorite American restaurant/bar in this intersection. Their low key storefront is easy to be overlooked, but should you have the mood to try them out on Friday night, you’d be instantly hooked by their vibe, service, drinks and food.

Too many highlights but in a few bullets:
- tapas actually in good serving size
- their fruit punch beer is so delicious
- white table cloth in a relaxing setting!
- attentive and thoughtful servers
- bar, high tops, table—options for different groups
- their food quality is top notch.
- Steak tips with mashed potato—LOVE.
- mussels with jalapeño—LOVE.
- all veggie dishes are cooked to perfection too. See my photos.

So glad we found this restaurant that I want to write about it and share it with the community on a Saturday morning during my brunch. Okay, now I gotta eat or my food will get cold.

Food:
We tried the bulgogi empanadas, birria steak tacos, bourbon steak tips, and tandoori roasted cauliflower. Everything was about average, and nothing stood out as being great or bad. The empanadas were alright, but I personally didn't think the flavors were a great combination so I didn't see it as a great fusion dish. The steak tacos and steak tips were decent, but just didn't stand out in any way. The cauliflower had great spices, but the odd thing was that we only got five pieces of cauliflower, which feels like a small amount for a relatively cheap ingredient. Perhaps some of the other food or drinks I didn't try is better.

Service:
The service was great. We were checked on frequently and never waited very long for anything.

Another Google find. Our server Isabella was great to work with. Very attentive. We shared the Farmers Salad with (very dry) falafel and amazing citrus vinaigrette dressing plus a few delicious olives. I had the super tender and tasty bourbon steak tips with yucca fries that we both really enjoyed. White tablecloth on every indoor table. We also liked that all staff were wearing their masks. We can highly recommend Hops N Scotch.

The food is so good!! Everything came out fresh, hot, the home fries are the best!!! I highly recommend the Tres Leches French toast as well.

Came in at prime brunch time on a Sunday and was seated quickly, the waitress, Alex, was amazing, timely. I never felt rushed, great brews on tap. The vibe is very cool, if you’re in the area stop in for a beer on tap, and if you’re not in the area go check it out anyways!

The drink selection is extensive, the bartenders are knowledgeable and courteous, and the food is fantastic. Every small and large plate has clearly been fine-tuned over and over, with generous portions of delicious food.

Pizza and service were great! Tons of options for toppings when you make your own personal pizza.

Meatballs to start were also amazing!

A cute pizza place on the corner of a busy street, Otto is a great place for dinner after a Coolidge Show! I went after a book talk and they had plenty of seating (although it does get busy at 8 so make a reservation!). They mainly serve pizzas, both custom and with delicious toppings. I loved my hot honey, pepperoni, goat cheese one. They have tiramisu and cookies for dessert. Other than pizzas, they serve some entree options but it’s not a place for diverse foods.

Overall, the staff were very friendly and nice, albeit a little slow during dinner rush. Overall, I would come again!

Pizza was put of this world.  The Spicy pulled pork was yummy.  The one with pineapple was outstanding.

Service was spot on and so friendly.

Vegan gluten free pizza! I love food that is both accessible to people like me with food allergies and restrictions but also food that is delicious. This was both. Thank you Otto’s! Please open up in NYC.

Great selection of beer as well as of course pizza.
Very unique ideas for slices.
We showed up at 10:30 PM and they were happy to serve us.
As I was writing this review, they gave us the last slices left over before closing for free. What a surprise!

Came in for an early morning breakfast. I ordered the “Kenmore” a double egg sandwich with cheese, tomato and onions. I also ordered a croissant and a chai latte.

I don’t really know what I was expecting, but raw onions wasn’t it.
