Luckily they were extremely easy to remove, indeed the biggest problem with the sandwich was that the eggs and the tomato were so slippery that both halves of the sandwich were basically constantly sliding around and threatening to fall apart as I ate it. I had to squeeze together the bagel and it was definitely an extremely tricky sandwich to eat.

The eggs, as far I could tell weren’t seasoned, and neither were the tomatoes. That being said, the bagel was knockout and the sandwich overall left me satisfied.

The croissant tasted much better than it looked, very buttery (almost too buttery), but it was just clearly underbaked. I’m not sure if that’s always how they make their croissants but there was no flake, no golden brown crisp, anything. But again inside it had layers and the flavor was there.

Chai was better than average, though overly sweet.

There’s barely any room in the shop itself so I enjoyed my breakfast outside. The service was also not great with another customer coming and bringing me my sandwich because they barely call out the order so even though I was standing feet away from the pick up counter I hadn’t heard when they were finished. Same with the chai.

So I know that sounds like a lot of quibbles and they are. So why the four stars? Why not lower? Because this place is a bagel shop and it was clear that the bagels they offered were handmade freshly made and definitely the everything bagel I had was the highlight of my meal.

If I were to go back, I would only order a bagel with cream cheese, or grab bagels for a morning meeting. I think in some degree the restaurant should be judged by what they primarily do, and as a primary bagel place I thought the bagel was great.

What a gem of a place! I had to go to Brookline for an MRI and I had never been there before. Kupel’s caught my eye as I was driving by and I had to go check it out. I got an egg and cheese bagel and a blueberry muffin to try and, wowzers, they were absolutely delicious! Staff was friendly and fast in service and I can’t wait to go back again!
Had great bagels here! Lots of different options to choose from and a nice sitting area outside.

I had heard from friends that Kupel's is one of the very few kosher restaurants in Boston, so I was looking forward to trying their offerings. The bakery was bustling around lunch time on a Sunday. The menu is quite fun -- each sandwich is an MBTA stop name colored as its respective MBTA line. But, as I experienced, perhaps the fun naming scheme leads to mixups in making the orders.

I ordered the Hynes, which is supposed to have egg salad, lox, tomato, and onion. I ended up having tuna salad in my bagel sandwich instead. The tuna salad was pretty unremarkable. I liked the lox (wish there was more of it), and the bagel was fine. When we went back to ask for the egg salad, they kindly gave us a small tub of egg salad as a replacement. However, I didn't enjoy the egg salad either -- it was not creamy and the egg white pieces were very tiny.

I also got the elephant ear pastry, which had some weird discolored speckles on it. One bite that I had tasted like mold, so I ended up tossing it. I wouldn't try their pastries again -- it doesn't seem like they're guaranteed to be fresh.

Overall, Kupel's is a very affordable option with a wide array of bagel sandwich combination options. Perhaps too many options...my friend's order got mixed up as well -- it didn't have any of the ingredients it was supposed to have -- and I've heard of more mixups in the past. I think Kupel's is a very important establishment that caters to many dietary restrictions at a reasonable price, and the employees are very nice about making up for wrong orders, but based on my experiences, I probably would not come back. I definitely do not recommend trying the pastries...
Ordered delivery from here, it took a while so the bagel was not as warm but still tasted perfect. Would definitely try again

That restaurant was our biggest surprise of our US trip.
We need to eat something on Friday noon and we tried it.
We took the lunch special for 11.95$ and it was great!
all was delicious and generously - best value - highly recommended!

WOW the LUNCH portions have significantly and Rapidly Shrunk to a FRACTION of the size

More so kid like portions you will need to Upgrade more food to offset the LESS volume as the container is tiny

What I used to heat up and fill my bowl plate is NO longer Full

The bag of food is lighter the Soup Container NOT full all the way for both of the lunch specials and LESS meat in the soup

Very very basic for that very reason I will be going LESS and less as $13 for lunch with tax is a fair deal but the portion itself is a JOKE!
Solid place for authentic Kosher Chinese food at a very reasonable price point. Our delivery order arrived surprisingly quick and was very well packed. Will be back!

The food is amazing. The wontons were the best I’ve ever tried. The man that waited our table was quick and efficient.
But women mashgiach NEEDS to be replaced. She is scary, rude, and unfriendly; putting a damper on the great service and atmosphere.
This place would be PERFECT without her.

The food wasn't bad, but I'll be honest, it wasn't mind-blowing. The chicken schezuan was the best dish we tried amongst others. We also ordered the Mongolian beef, king pao chicken, vegetable fried rice and plain rice, along with some greens and hot and sour soup.

Walked in on a weeknight to a completely empty restaurant - no idea why it wasnt jam packed !! The food was amazing and was a typical price for what we got. The drinks were great as well. Our server offered to cook our meat for us and was attentive throughout the meal.

One of the not so many places in Boston that opens late.

Good taste, moderate price. Cozy atmosphere for gathering.

We came in for an early dinner at 5: 30 on a Wednesday and the restaurant was empty. Since we had the whole restaurant to ourselves, the service was top notch. Our server grilled and cut our meats into bite sizes and was very attentive.
Everything was delicious. We ordered fried oysters, which were crunchy on the outside and juicy on the inside. For the main course, we went with the 2-person combo, which came with 2 meats and 2 side orders. We chose pork belly and marinated short ribs to be served along with kimchi stew and soybean stew. Taste-wise, everything was perfect. However, I wished the pork belly were thicker cut. This restaurant serves them bacon-thin. We also enjoyed all the side dishes which were well fermented and seasoned. We will definitely be coming back.

You get a good feeling going into the ambience of this restaurant.

The server also did a great job in understanding our needs and taking the order quick.

However, the taste of all the food we ordered, WAS SUBPAR.

Chicken was rubbery, rice cakes were harder to eat than usual and we just couldn’t enjoy the whole meal. They did a good job with Scallion pancakes though.

I honestly feel the chef here needs to check on the chicken in their food. It tasted little stale and rubbery like I mentioned.

For location, service and ambience: I feel it was good.
Overall 3/5 stars

Good option for a quick Korean meal or a late night K-BBQ near BU.

Initially perceived as a typical Japanese restaurant, I was surprised to discover its Korean focus during a recent late-night visit. The restaurant, with its clean, traditional Korean BBQ layout, exuded a welcoming vibe. While restaurant serving Korean and Japanese food under Chinese management might not sound appealing, the dishes I tried weren’t too bad.

Among the menu I ordered, the Chicken Gizzard, with its mix of peppers, garlic, and sesame oil, stood out. The Kimchi Fried Rice, while slightly Americanized lacking that extra kick of tanginess typical in Korean cuisine, was still quite enjoyable. The prompt service, with all the dishes arriving in under ten minutes, added to the positive experience.

Kayuga might not be my first choice for authentic Korean comfort food, but it certainly is a reliable option for those seeking a quick Korean meal or a casual K-BBQ experience in the BU area.

Edited review:
I believe this is my last time ordering from this establishment. For $5.50, this is the bagel and cream cheese I received. It’s a very steep price for effectively just bread, and this has been happening consistently as I come here frequently. I’m disappointed, I used to love this place

Great staff! Though I’m never super impressed by the coffee here (somewhat watered down, but I’m just particular) I love the bagels and sandwiches!! So grateful for all the vegan options :) I’m sad there isn’t more seating but they do the best they can with the small space

Great coffee house with lots of convenient locations throughout Boston! My usual coffee order is the Maple Iced Latte with less milk which is not overly sweet or syrupy, has the perfect taste! It looks very light but doesn’t taste overly watered down or milky. They roast their own coffee and it never tastes burnt. My favorite sandwich is The Fix on a plain bagel which is super flavorful and has a sweet and slightly spicy pepper jam that’s made in house! Super flavorful and always flavorful. Service is quick and always friendly. On the weekends it’s convenient to order ahead online because there’s a line sometimes. They also offer delivery. Much more satisfying experience than at larger coffee chains!

The only issue here is that it is a small location.  Nice, clean, bright, with good coffee on tap daily. There is some seating if wanted, but being so close to the T, most folks seem to grab coffe and excellent food to go. We did sit a little and it was quiet - I would have been happy to spend more time if I hadn't needed to catch the T. The bagels were very good
The cashier was incredibly friendly and made me feel welcome right away. The atmosphere is cozy, and the coffee was delicious. I’ll definitely be coming back!

This place will not last long. I paid 21$ for a small hot latte and a bacon egg and cheese. Coffee very average and the bacon egg and cheese was literally cold. Place is bunk trust me don’t do it. Better off going to McDonald’s at the corner

Went there on 8/29/2024 after 11pm. Asked for a Vanilla ice cream with cone. A short lady handed me the ice cream. I said, this is small. Several workers said that the Owner advised them to only add 3 lines. The owner didn't advise them how many inches were each line. At all other Mc Donalds, people are given the same vanilla ice cream for $2.99 plus tax a tall vanilla ice cream. Since the owner of this location cares so much not to have its own workers give everyone a tall ice cream cone. I am going to add other Mc Donalds locations in Boston, what other people get vs others, plus there mc donalds advertisement of 3 tall long ice cream cones for 2.99

This McDonald’s restored and instilled in me a new and rejuvenated love for McNumpkins.
I had the pleasure of receiving a $25 gift certificate to the restaurant from a sympathetic friend earlier this month.
You see, I tragically lost my job earlier this year and have not been able to find sustainable full time work. I haven’t had take out in a hot minute.
Best gift ever.
Best friend ever.
Best McDonalds location ever.
Can’t wait to turn 30 in June and celebrate with some fries and The Best Diet Coke I have ever had.
Only Real Ones work at this McDonalds, anyone who says the service is bad has issues or can’t read a room. The employees at this McDonalds work tirelessly and they are also extremely cute.

I ordered McDonald’s thru UberEats at 2AM on a Sunday (9.30.2024). It was the most amazing McDonald’s order I have ever had in my life. Fries were HOT, burgers were good too. I’m so satisfied. Thank you

Mobile order for a caramel iced coffee, waited 10 minutes just to find out they never made it, after 15 minutes I finally got a plain iced coffee with no sugar or caramel syrup and had a burnt taste as if the coffee were made hours ago and left on a burner.

I came in ordered a Bacon McDouble and barley got any bacon on the burger they gave me one bacon strip cut up in half and that’s it I’ve been to so many other McDonalds and got a fair amount of bacon on my burger this is just ridiculous and the staff are very rude I noticed them laughing and talking about the customers

สุภัทร ธนบดีภัทร

reviews.text: This is by far the worst place I have been to in Cambridge. It was disgusting. I did not touch any of the food served. The restaurant was dirty, tables very sticky, floors not being cleaned for a while. I have no words for this. In the end your choice, but personally I would not have any food that has been prepared there.
The staff was friendly and the show was fun but pretty similar to every other Japanese steak house. Good but nothing special.

The avocado sushi was excellent and the veg noodle soup is not a ramen, but very flavourful, filling and soupy. Service could be  slightly friendlier but it's efficient and that's what counts. Other diners enjoyed the teppanyaki service at the table cook top.

OMG, this place blatantly lies to your face. I ordered the "surf and turf" which in the menu the description says "lobster & filet mignon", and I specified medium rare for the steak. What comes to shock me was this. The steak was chopped and pan fried and way overcooked, and the seafood was several shrimps mixed with chopped lobster meat. This is blatant misrepresentation and deserves a more official complaint/report. To make matters worse, a 18% tip was automatically added to the bill without my consent. I've never experienced something Iike that for a 2-person dinner. I'm sure this place would die pretty quickly if it weren't for the hotel vouchers which could only be spent here.

The Boston area has many delicious sushi restaurants...Bisuteki is not one of them. After a long day, we decided to try this restaurant as it was conveniently situated in the hotel we were staying in.

The restaurant is large with 4 or 5 hibachi tables at the center of the room and standard seating around the perimeter. At 7pm on Friday night, we were one of three standard tables seated. Our waitress seemed to be in a rush to turn over our table and get us to leave. I will say that the other staff we encountered were delightful.

The food and drinks were disappointing, to say the least. Most flavors were off-putting, especially the dressing included with the house salad. It had a strong vinegar taste which overpowered the rest of the ingredients. Unfortunately, the drinks were very weak. One thing I really did enjoy was the Black Widow Roll; it was beautifully presented, tasted fresh, and I loved the added crunch of the sweet potato. Our bill was high and while I don't mind paying for good quality, I think Bisuteki was overpriced for what we were served.

I would recommend dining at another sushi restaurant in the area as they are easy to find.

This place is my go-to whenever I’m in Boston. Their Buffalo chicken pizza is incredible, and the Döner calzone is amazing! The staff are super friendly, and the cozy vibe makes it a perfect spot to relax. Plus, parking is easy with spots right in front. Highly recommend!
Beautiful experience, i love their buffalo chicken pizza. Cruz is a great chef.
The best restaurant to enjoy delicious food and excellent service with very good prices. The restaurant is modern but most importantly, is very clean. Very recommend!

If you're a pizza enthusiast, Inbound Pizza is an absolute must-visit. This local Allston gem consistently delivers outstanding pies with fresh ingredients and bold flavors. The toppings are always generous and high-quality. The friendly staff adds to the welcoming atmosphere, making each visit a pleasure. Whether you're a fan of classic margherita or adventurous with toppings, Inbound Pizza has something for everyone. Highly recommend for anyone craving top-notch pizza in the area!

Ziti was something I'd get in a microwaved dinner from the frozen food section. The question is always: can I make something better myself for the same price or with what I have at home? In the ziti's case, absolutely. $20 for the buffalo chicken pizza, which was under-spiced, was also not worth it.

This neighborhood pasta shop is a hidden gem, serving up homemade pasta with rich, flavorful sauces. The cozy atmosphere and friendly staff make every meal a delight. Perfect for a comforting, authentic Italian experience. One of my absolute favorites during my college days in Boston.
This is a wonderful experience, the orders are made really quickly, and it’s the best choice to stop by if you’re in a rush. Thanks, for the beautiful food!

We were staying at a hotel close by a wanted some pasta, not pizza. There are several pizza places around Coolidge Corner. The Bottega is just that, a bottega, and it might work for lunch but not really for a cozy dinner. So carry out it was and the pasta dishes were terrific. Bread a little stale tasting but the Cesare salad was crisp. Easy to warm up meals in the microwave. Would go back for more pasta!
First time in since I was in college years ago, a nice renovation and they offer breakfast now. Really nice guy working the counter. Reasonably priced and good coffee. Thanks!

$15 roast beef panini with slightest slice of meet on the white soft supermarket bread…
that’s beyond my understanding
Italian by name only

What’s not to love? Terrific falafel, fresh ingredients and friendly folks. The pita bread has spoiled me from purchasing anything store bought. Outside seating is good in theory but too close to noisy and stinky car traffic.
Feels like I’m in Israel in the best way! One of the best falafel pita in Boston! Also love the beef kabob. Great for dine in or takeout. Definitely recommend trying this local spot!
Been 20 years since I used to come in college. Falafel pita was everything I remembered and more. Was able to bring my teenage daughter to enjoy as well. Great spot!!

Another great Google maps search find. We are in the area and Rami’s was one of the choices we had. I had the Rami special that had a little bit of everything and my wife had the falafel, hummus and salad plate with super fresh pita bread. We both really enjoyed ours meals and suggest if you are in the area, have a delicious meal at Rami’s.
Whenever I want a fresh and delicious hummus and falafel pita, I try to go out of my way to get one here. So good! Falafel is fantastic, everything is balanced well. I’m never disappointed.

My first time trying Korean food, and what a feast it was. The broth with the pork spine was amazing, the pork was juicy and tender and the broth rich and salty. The seafood pancakes are now one of my favourite things ever: they were incredible. The meat was tender and juicy. Service was quick, and the meal was quite cheap considered all we ate.

Hanmaru Gamjatang – A Hidden Gem for Korean Comfort Food Lovers

Tucked away like a little secret that locals know to keep, Hanmaru Gamjatang is the ultimate spot if you’re craving authentic Korean flavors that hit you right in the soul. The star of the show? Their gamjatang—this pork bone soup is pure perfection. The broth is rich, deeply flavored, and has this amazing slow-cooked vibe that speaks of hours of dedication. It’s spicy but balanced, with just the right amount of heat that warms you up rather than overpowering the flavors.

The tender, fall-off-the-bone pork is the real treat, and it’s worth every second of the work it takes to savor it off the bones. And let’s talk about the sides! They serve an array of traditional banchan, all fresh and with unique flavors that complement the main dish beautifully. Each bite feels like a complete experience.

But it’s not just about the food—Hanmaru has that cozy, welcoming atmosphere that makes you feel like you’re sitting down to a meal made with love. The staff are attentive and genuinely friendly, eager to make you feel at home. If you’re on the hunt for authentic Korean comfort food that’s generous in both portion and flavor, Hanmaru Gamjatang is a must-visit. This place isn’t just a meal; it’s an experience you’ll keep coming back for.

Also, Himang was our waiter and he was just an exceptional human being, answering all out questions and recommending us truly the best food.

Seafood Pajeon and Tofu Jigae are so so good! the pajeon was thick, crispy, and extremely flavorful, and soup was so comforting and filled with seafood and soft tofu. We really enjoyed the bulgogi too—the marinade was so flavorful. Loved the side dishes as well. Service was extremely attentive, and the waiters were very kind!

We have been coming to this restaurant for many years, and the pork bone soup is our favorite. This time, we tried the grilled squid, curry rice, and the seafood scallion pancake, all of which were very delicious. The service was also very good, making us feel very warm in the winter.
Love it. Two of us got the medium signature pot and the classic pork feet, which was plenty for two people. Will surely come back to try other things on the menu.

I passed by this Starbucks last week and was a bit busy before leaving a comment. It's definitely the best Starbucks I've ever been to, with a lot of aroma in the store. My friends and I are all praising it, and we'll come back again next time.

Bad quality drinks.

I like the baristas here a lot but I face a scenario of having to either ask -- almost every time -- to have my drink remade, or to accept a cappuccino whenever I order a no-foam or low-foam latte. Again, nice baristas, but the amount of foam I get within each beverage is enough to make this place a two-star establishment at best. When you're paying $7+ for a drink and tipping multiple dollars, but only getting about 50% of the drink actually in the cup, over and over again... Really frustrating! I genuinely don't understand why these baristas don't use the foam spoon like every other Starbucks in the country.

EDIT: As nice as the owner was, and again, as nice as the baristas are... This just keeps happening. Attaching a new pic of my tall no-foam oatmilk latte. This is a cappucino: half foam. I am going down to 1 star because I was once a former barista myself at a Starbucks for years and I know how easy it is to just use a spoon to hold back foam when someone orders a no-foam latte. This is legitimately robbing customers of 50% of their beverage or more, and it happens almost every single time to this day.

EDIT 2  to add that, 7 months later, this problem is still occurring and may have actually gotten worse. As a former barista for years who worked at a Starbucks on Newbury St., I know what it's like to work in a very busy store. There's no excuse for repeatedly giving me half a cup of foam on a no-foam latte.  Am I going to have to resort to Dunkin full time!?

Let's be honest, unless you beat the "laptop army" this place really didn't have any available seating before the renovation. Regarding quality and ambiance, it's a mega chain coffee shop that delivers the intended experience.

Very poor quality of ice! I’m drinking iced latte,and testing ice water in my coffee,ice cubes are so small,looks like half melted.I asked the staff if there’s something wrong with the ice machine and she says that this’s a new ice machine,really???!!!! Quality of coffee not worth it the money! I’m buying a coffee everyday!

Bought my cold sandwich 8:22am and I asked them to heat it up. It took them 17min to do it.

Lady said there were 19 items ahead of me but I came in before the other people came in. Please make sure to serve customers by the order they come in.

Been going here for years, but recently they upgraded their systems and decor.

Staff here is friendly, but may appear menacing. They are just very direct, but mean well.

Food here is superb, got a bunch of different dishes and they were all delicious.

Victoria's Seafood is a late night spot open until around 1 AM on most days, meaning it is a great place to grab a quick bite or dinner after a night out. It's near BU and sees a lot of international students on the weekends or during late nights.

The service is very quick here and fast-paced, which may turn people off if they're expecting a fine dining sort of service. It definitely helps if you speak Mandarin or Cantonese, as most of the other wait staff do not speak English or have trouble with the language.

I have ate many things off this menu, ranging from the Beef Kebabs, Lobster Sauce, Fish Maw Soup, Salt & Pepper Squid, Beef Satay Chow Foon, and much more. The prices have risen over the years, but it is still a good portion for the price. The food quality has been very good, and whenever I order take-out the food is still fresh and not soggy by the time I get it.

I would recommend this place for catering as well, as the portion size is pretty good and price is decent for larger parties. Overall a wonderful place to eat at or order takeout from.

Food is substandard. Dry fried beef chow foon has too much bean sprouts and is too light on the flavor.  Sizzling beef tastes alright but lacks any feature that tells me to come back again.The chicken is very dry. Service is standard without anything to note. The atmosphere is also what a typical Chinese seafood restaurant felt like without any distinctive feature. Every aspect of this restaurant is like any other Chinese seafood restaurant, hence an average rating.

We got pork intestines with preserved vegetables,stirred fried pea leaves,salted and pepper soft shell crab, and fish maw with crab meat soup. Everything came out well-cooked and tasty. Fast service even when the restaurant was packed. We moved away and once in a while when we crave Chinese food we would go out our way to Victoria.
Second time visit this restaurant, I love the shrimp and duck! Their foods are always good!

This restaurant is close to my house and I frequently pass it. Whenever I do, it is full of happy guests and fabulous food. My friend and I decided to try it ourselves yesterday and it was the best decision of my entire Friday! The food is fresh and delicious, I got the Tempura tteokboki and my friend got the kimchi stew. Everything was gorgeous and the service was attentive and impeccable. We had the best time ever sitting here drinking beer and watching music videos, and my only regret was that I got too full to finish my food!! I highly recommend Myung Dong.

The vibe of this place fun! Extensive drink menu, K-pop videos, and really really good food. Service was attentive and helpful. Great for groups, this place is spacious. We walked in, two adults and a toddler, on a Friday night and at first was a little hesitant like, hmm this is kind of a drinking place. But we had a great time! It was fun to people watch and reminisce about our college days! And our toddler enjoyed the videos and the waitress very kindly gave him a treat on the way out. Great place all around!

Two large pots: the military bowl and the beef intestine bowl. Not being a fan of animal intestines, the reviews from other patrons gave a 3.5 🌟 for that bowl; but the military bowl was pretty subpar, no much veggies, the spam was over cooked, and missing some ingredients I had in other Korean restaurant with the same bowl. The rice cake and tofu was tasty, that earned a 4 ⭐️.

One more thing, this is the first Korean restaurant where we only received 3 small dishes accompanied with our dishes. Usually it’s between 5-10 dishes per order. Much improvements can be done on that front.

Staff were friendly and place was clean. I wouldn’t be going back for the second time given the pierce competition of Korean restaurants in the area.

Have gone here multiple times over many years and I love the vibe and the food is always good. I got the short ribs this past time and they were SO good. The bibimbap was good, but I’ve had better and the soy wings were good as well. Will definitely return, though looking to try some of the other Korean spots in the neighborhood first.

Good service and food, but they should include more pictures on the menu so I know what are those dishes...They play Korean music all the time, but sometimes I felt it’s kind of noisy, my stomach is vibrating along with the beats, I’m not joking!!! Maybe lower the volume a little bit and that’ll be better.

[Okay so here’s the update. I went there 3 more times after I wrote this review and found they did adjust the music style and the volume so it’s comfortable now.]

The prices match its value, hot pots are good for cold winter. However, the seasoning of many dishes are quite the same style, you may want to have some refreshing drinks to refresh your tastes.

Definitely coming back again food was delicious! Don’t let you self be fooled by the bad reviews, this is definitely one of the few places where they actually sell halal food and you can taste in their flavors. So many vegetarian options. Love to see different cuisines coming together.

My recent visit to Azama was a letdown. I ordered the mix shawarma over rice, but the dish lacked flavor and the beef shawarma was dry. Service was sluggish, and the ambiance couldn't salvage the experience. Azama has room for improvement. I can't recommend it in its current state.

Ordered several items from Uber eats as part of a bogo deal including, veggie wrap, grape leaves, Egyptian fries, and baklava

The wrap was great and def one of my favorites in the city so far. The sauces were very flavorful and it was stuffed. I also ordered some sauce on the side, but it looks like I got all three as part of the fries or wrap. The garlic and spicy garlic are amazing but the harissa seems to have too much black pepper in it.

Fries were a large portion and baklava and grape leaves were what you'd expect. Thought the delivery was fast and very well packaged.

This is not the old Azama I'm 90% sure the Egyptian family who owned it sold it. The lamb shawarma and kofta kebab were bland and had half of the meat that they had last time I was there less than a year ago. I noticed a lot of new Latin American food dishes on the menu too. Very confusing if this is now a Latin American restaurant and or under new management that should be made clear so people don't waste their time and money.
Everything in my plate tasted as if it was prepared a week ago. The pita bread was old and crumbling, the veggies were old, rice was dry, and the BBQ skewers were burnt.

I usually come here for a slice or two and the pizza is pretty darn good. The crust is bit thin but also very firm and flavorful. They usually have a solid slice selection, usually 4 to 6 options. The slices are enormous so one slice can get the job done. The Upper Crust is way better than OTTO. Take the time and go across the street to get pizza.

Super polite and friendly staff. 9pm came out of movie, hit up the Upper Crust sat outside where the weather was amazing and they served us food. Buffalo Chicken calzone was delicious and the baked ziti was perfect. Very reasonable cost, clean all around highly recommended

The upper crust pizza is definitely the best thin crust pizza in Boston❤️My favorite is the Margherita pizza🏆There are enough seats in the store, and the freshly baked pizza is the best! If you don’t finish it, take it home and reheat it in the oven, it’s still delicious👍🏻I’ll try other flavors next time.

Never order a pizza for delivery here. If you do, there will be no attempt to make it right when they fail at it.

We ordered a pizza. They could not deliver for cash, so I agreed to pick it up. They called back to say the choice I made was not available. I changed my choice, and gave them a credit card number and they agreed to deliver it in 30 minutes.

60 minutes later, I called because nothing had arrived. I was told "it's not my fault" but the fault of Doordash, who "didn't come." I pointed out that since they offer pizza delivery, it WAS  "their fault." They said they could call Doordash again. I said I wanted a hot fresh pizza. They said I could get a refund instead, 75 minutes after the original call. I said I wanted a hot pizza, and was told several times "I want you to see MY point of view."

Fed up, I asked for a refund, and asked to speak to the manager. I was on hold for several minutes, as had happened at least 3 times already: ("just give me a second"). Finally, I called back, and was told the manager was not there until tomorrow, and would refund me then. "Why didn't you tell me that to start with?!" "We are busy."

Then I was on hold for another two minutes, and gave up.

Don't try delivery from here!

This used to be my go to pizza place, but over the past year or so it’s been going downhill while others are getting better. Ordered some garlic parmesan wings and it was just wings with minced garlic on it. Not in a sauce. Not roasted garlic. Nearly raw, minced garlic, sitting on the side of the wings.  And no cheese. The Pizza was OK but a little sad. It was definitely more floppy and a little bit wet than normal. The buffalo wings were alright if not a little dry, somehow like the garlic parmesan. Oddly enough the best thing was the salad. Maybe this is just kind of a one off. But for 50+ dollars can’t say I’m thrilled.

Good food as always but the places was disappointing. They were out of half the soda and didn't even tell us when we ordered. The ice machine was also out of ice. 1 of the bathrooms were out of order which made the line back up. Kids almost didn't make it.

Saw Canes on Tik Tok with influencers raving about it. First off. It’s not worth driving 45 mins to get. It’s just chicken and French fries. It was good but not 5 star good.  The service was fast and friendly.

A BU classic, you can’t beat canes for fried chicken in the area. Great place to hang out, very laid back atmosphere. Also awesome after hockey games or a day at the fitrec. The chicken is crispy and the sauce is undefeated. Only tip is to switch coleslaw with toast so you get more Texas toast.

I came in at about 11:30 AM. It wasn't a full house but there was a decent number of people present to know that this Raising Cane's is popular. I got my order just minutes after I had ordered (with the way the menu is set up I figured they make sure to have enough of the different components of the various combos ready to plate).
The chicken was crispy and pretty moist but if you feel that it is a little dry the cane sauce more than fixes it and it's the bomb. The fries aren't half bad. Texas toast is really good. And if you ordered something like the box combo you should definitely make a sandwich(I had seen a YouTuber do it and they were not kidding) with the toast, a chicken finger, coleslaw (I liked that the vegetables were minced and works well for a mini sandwich), sauce and even fit in some fries if you can.
I suggest going here if you want something that is a step up from fast food joints like McDonald's or Burger King

Raising Cane's is a fast-food restaurant chain that specializes in serving chicken fingers. The restaurant was founded in Baton Rouge, Louisiana in 1996 and has since expanded across the United States and internationally. The chain's menu is simple: they offer three different combinations of chicken fingers, fries, coleslaw, Texas toast, and a signature Cane's sauce.

The quality of the food at Raising Cane's is consistently praised by customers. The chicken fingers are made with 100% premium white meat chicken tenderloins, and the fries are always crispy and well-seasoned. The Cane's sauce is a fan favorite for its unique flavor that perfectly complements the chicken fingers.

One of the standout features of Raising Cane's is their commitment to customer service. The employees are friendly and efficient, and the restaurant's atmosphere is welcoming and lively. The restaurant always has a clean and organized appearance, making for a pleasant dining experience.

Overall, Raising Cane's is a great option for anyone looking for a quick and delicious meal. Their focus on quality, simplicity, and customer service has made them a popular choice among fast-food enthusiasts. If you're a fan of chicken fingers, fries, and good vibes, you won't be disappointed with Raising Cane's.
Holly Crab is fantastic! Amazing Korean-run clean restaurant with delicious seafood, great service, and a cozy atmosphere. Highly recommend – five stars!!!

I haven't had crawfish in 2 years and this definitely satisfied my cravings! They had noodles with their crawfish (optional) OMG the idea was genius! They were so delicious and the crawfish itself was the best. The corn with the sauce as well was just soooo good.

I ordered the Calamari and Cajun fries today. Very tasty. Which I can appreciate because a lot of Calamari served in Boston is either too rubbery or the breading falls off the bland unseasoned Calamari when you pick it up. I would just say that my Calamari was slightly over fried not by much for my liking though. I'll be back to try other dishes there.

Not crowded at all, prices very reasonable, and service was very attentive! My friend and I thoroughly enjoyed our meals and they were very flavorful. The specialty lemonades were especially good. Will be back soon!

We ordered  three different orders with different sauce:  Sauces had no flavor.  The waiter was the worst.  Never came back to ask if everything was fine or if neeed anything.  Brought the ck and did not ask if was taking anything home or needed anything else.  We had lots of leftovers.  Asked to bag it home.  He just brought a brown bag & dumped the food as is.  Left the fries unpacked.  Had to re-ask for a box.  I do not recommend this place or waiter on Saturday night 8/17/24.

On my first visit to Geido,  I was sorely disappointed.  That was about a year ago.  I found the sushi flavorless.
I was craving sushi for lunch today and decided to give them another chance. I'm glad I did.  I had the spicy salmon / spicy tuna combo and it was fresh and tasty. The cashier even saved me a few bucks by suggesting I get the combo instead of ala cart orders.  It takes a little while because they make your sushi to order, but this time it was definitely worth the wait.

I guess we tried almost all the sushi places in Allston and this one is the only one where we order now. They have a nice selection of combos for a very good price.
Usually we'd just call them and order take out for a pickup, so no idea about delivery.
A couple of times we got a gift from them together with our order: complimentary sushi and rolls, which were as always delicious!
Unique selection of sushi and more. Very good price for the food and delicious

Wonderful place, extremely nice people here. Sushi were awesome and tons of option to choose. Quick, fast, and grab to go was seamless. Definitely a must come when you need something quick and on the way to your business.
Below average sushi for an average price. Unchilled rice, not enough crabstick in cali roll, poorly rolled, not much flavor. etc. Sketchy raw fish.

Great dry mala pot! You can customize what you want to add in your pot and choose the spice level. I recommend mild spicy (小辣) for people who don’t eat that spicy! The portion is big so you can share with the others.
Their bento box is okay. Delicious and authentic but since every dishes were premade for you to choose sometimes it’s not very fresh.

One of the best dry mala places in Boston! Their mala is very rich and flavourful aka spicy, so it is advised to get medium. Overall the selection for meat, seafood, and vegetables were plenty and it was also cooked well.

Meanest cashier ever. I ordered a large size for vegetables, and was told to order another set when I requested to get some additional green leaves. I made a complaint about the size at the counter and guess what? this is what I got for ordering mild! I had to wash everything with water twice. As you can see the water looks crazy hot. The craziest and worst experience ever.
Some of the menu items come with a soup of the day, and my soup was just cabbage water. I was able to fish out 2 slices of napa cabbage with the rest literally water.
Used to be one of my favourite places. Staff changes were detrimental. Food and service are not what it used to anymore.

They had so many options in drinks and food—we ended up getting the mango sago, dolphin bay Boba, and honey grapefruit boba for the drinks and they all tasted amazing other than the fact the mango sago was a bit artificial. We got the basil chicken, the appetizer with seaweed, egg, and tofu, the popcorn chicken over rice, the braised beef soup, and pork and bamboo. They were literally all equally delicious, and amazing! We finished almost everything. The waiters were so polite and apologetic when they forgot the rice. They checked on us during our meal and the atmosphere was great overall. I would recommend their chicken.

The food was very authentic and everything we ordered was really, really tasty! The staff and owner were so kind and even treated us to their milk tea which was also really good! The service was also very fast and we highly recommend!!!

5 stars for this authentic Taiwanese restaurant! The food is amazing and great portions, the owner is very friendly and great service! They also served us some Taiwanese milk tea. We had crispy pork, salt and pepper pork, beef noodle soup and pig feet noodles. Would definitely come back and try other dishes!

Amazing. A taste of home!

I’m so happy I found out Dolphin Bay was here. I frequented Dolphin Bay back when they were in Southern California and was so sad when they closed. I had no idea I’d find them here! What a stroke of luck and a crazy coincidence. There’s only one Dolphin Bay, and they’re family-owned. So if you’re in Boston, definitely check it out for some authentic Taiwanese food!

Now onto the food!

The pork chop bento was a classic. It was pricey, but for the amount of pork chop you get, it makes sense. There was so much they even put the extra in a paper bag with a handwritten note, which I appreciated.

You can also buy the lu rou (braised ground pork) in bulk on the side! It makes an amazing topping for rice.

I ordered to-go and I was very impressed with the packaging. They bagged everything separately to ensure nothing would spill and put the extra pork chop in a paper bag to prevent it from getting soggy. I appreciate them being mindful of how to pack their food for maximum freshness. Not many restaurants have learned to do that.

The milk tea is solid. Nothing out of this world, but it tastes like nostalgia and satisfies my craving.

This has been a comfort spot since I was a kid, and I will definitely be back.

This is a solid local Taiwanese restaurant. It's nothing fancy and a bit run down looking on the inside, but the food is solid and the drinks are good. The servers are very nice, but very inattentive. You have to call them over to your table. One was on her phone, while eating dinner. The other was in the back for a while. We got their popcorn chicken, beef rolled pancake, taro tapioca drink, a few rice plates and their noodles dishes. Everything was tasty. The rice dishes come with some steamed egg and cabbage. The popcorn chicken could use a bit more flavor, but it's still a tasty bite.

Super delicious and affordable food - great for take out (maybe not so much for dining in)!

This place has a really nice selection of Korean fusion dishes. The food, for what it is (elevated fast food), is great value for money - it tastet delicious and hits the sweet spot, at least for me. I also like it way better than Coreanos or Kimchi Papi.

Would highly recommend for a quick bite or a take -out. Only went to sit-in once and it was not super pleasant inside.

Small cozy space with good Korean food. As someone who is not familiar with the food, they were very kind to explain the dishes. Food was really quick and it was delicious and the portion is very generous. Will come back for sure. Also, ambience is simple and welcoming. I had the fried rice kimchi bowl with chicken.
I had the tacos and a burrito  every thing came out right flavors were good. I would come back and recommend them to any 1 that's wants a bite to eat. In the area
The servers were very nice! I don't think people usually eat in here since the seating is limited but it's a cute space. Food was very good and portions were generous.
When I picked up the owner was here too. He was taking photos for some food and eventually, he gave me all of them for free! Thank you very much!
Food was very good. I'm a Pad Thai snob and really liked theirs. Large portions, not overly oily like many others in the genre. We ate in, but got the sense they mostly do take out.

Food was gross. I ordered a chicken pad Thai, the noodles were soggy, I couldn't even eat it. Also ordered the BBq chicken wings, they had a weird taste like they were going bad, they were to salty too. Just gross.

My boyfriend eats lunch here ALL the time and I was just dying to try it! I was fully satisfied with this place, loved the food! Taste as good as it looks, super delicious. My son had shrimp fried rice and it was also delicious, the crab ragoon are amazing! Will be visiting again soon. Great stuff!

I've been here a few times and was never really disappointed. We ordered a few dishes drunken noodle(my fav), house fried rice orange chicken and they were all good taste wise. I think the noodles is small for price but everything else seemed reasonably priced. This is 1 of the top 3 go to in Brookline.

We ordered from Jumbowl by Basil Rice.  I got the grilled fish with sweet sauce and rice. I liked that the sauce was not over drizzled over the fish so the fish was still a bit crisp by the time we got our order.
It was good enough portion for a lunch.
Overall it was decent. Nothing crazy or wow.

Excellent lunch buffet value. Food is very fresh and flavorful*. Service is attentive and friendly. Interior is clean and tidy, though not fancy. Small off street parking is a bonus if you can get a spot.

*Flavors do come through very well but if you prefer strong spices then order off the menu. By their own admission the buffet is designed to appeal to a wide range of tastes.

The restaurant has a nice modern interior with a tasteful and welcoming vibe. It's located near a busy neighborhood and has a few off-street parking spots with plenty of street parking.

The service can be a little slow, but I think they just don't want to be too much of a bother. The portions are very good and each dish had good flavors. We had quite a bit of leftovers and are looking forward to it!

If you are an Indian you might not like their bland food. I went for a lunch Buffet. They had gobi manchurian (fried gobi in some ketchup and other sauces and spices) chicken and paneer tikka masala, aaloo choley (chickpea), plain rice,  carrot potatoes, sambhar and masala dosa, chiken tikka, kheer, gulabjamun, chai. (The garlic naan are not unlimited, you have to pay after the first one)

Everything just looks good but lacks flavor. I checked the images of their food (that look good) but lacks flavor on the contrary.
The chai had spices that were overpowering. Sambhar tasted nothing but lentil daal with water and boiled veggies. (See image)
Gobi Manchurian is not good either.

On top of this, their manager was so rude. (The waiting staff is kind though). We entered 20 minutes before the buffet was closing. We took everything at once because the manager informed us about closing buffet. But he was very uncourteous and eager to wrap things up. One of the waiting staff was heading to us to ask if we want something more (he asked the same on other table). He was stopped by the manager saying “they are done”. The food isn’t nice, the manager is rude. I am not going there again just for the atmosphere.

I ordered take out from them so I can only speak on the food. I ordered the Shahi Navritan Korma and a samosa. And I gotta say… it was great! Really delicious! Great mix of veggies. I ordered it spicy, and I found it perfectly seasoned. My friend also really liked her meal as well.

I have no complaints. I really enjoyed it!

I personally love this place. I know nothing of Indian culture or cuisine more than the average person does. But what I do know is, if I’m hungry and craving some of what American calls “Indian food”, this is the place I’m going. Tastes delicious, they always ask me what spice level I want my food. They used to have a buffet, and then shut it down during the COVID-19 pandemic due to obvious sanitary precautions and for the safety of all their customers! Every time I’ve come to dine here, I’m either the only one there or there are one or two other dining parties, which again, I’m not a bit fan of experiencing that, but that doesn’t change the truth of how good the food is! The portions are relatively small. I can handle a lot of spice when I ask for spicy food, they still have never crafted that much of a spicy dish for me, I hope one day they do, but that’s a personal preference! I also absolutely appreciate the kind service the staff provide. They are welcoming and hospitable and make it comfortable enough to not make it feel like they are all watching you eat as your the only one there! Try it. You find out you will be pleased! You’ll find I posted two pictures! One with food in the plates/bowls, one shows empty plates/bowls. Yes! Every single bite is delicious! You won’t want to leave a single grain of rice behind!

I love the food here. I was recommended by a local friend and if I didn’t have self control, my bank account would be empty from the amount of times I craveeee Anna’s. It is delicious, offers HUGE portions, and very reasonable price.

Zero transparency with pricing, charging people $2 for adding “elote corn” or veggies but no indication of it in their menu. An $8 burrito ends up being over $14. Don’t play with customers money, price transparency goes a long way and won’t make you seem shady

When I stood in line, there were 2 customers ordering. They ordered and got their food but I wasn't acknowledged. I made eye contact with the cashier but she started working on a doordash order. There were other people working and they were speaking with one another. I tried to ask for assistance but I still was not acknowledged. One of the workers came to the register to take the order (10-15m later), and said "hey, what would you like?", thinking she was speaking with me but it was a white customer that came in after me. I ended up leaving. It was late on a weeknight and did not seem ad busy but I still wasn't helped.

Went to this Anna’s yesterday. Ordered  quesadillas because we were going to an event and needed some thing quick. We were super disappointed. The only thing warm in the quesadillas was the shell and sliced cheese (😭) she put in it. Imagine cold vegetables inside that? Not good at all. I asked her to put the vegetables inside prior to heating up and she said they don’t do it that way. 🙄😳 Won’t be going back. And to boot, she rolled it like a burrito. Seeing this transpire in front of my eyes at the counter, I don’t even know why I paid and ate it. 🤷🏻‍♀️
Annas will always be my favorite burrito but why do they only ever have one line open? It’s completely inefficient and wait times can quickly become close to 20-30 mins just to order.

I was pleasantly surprised by this place. The food was quite good: the spicy tuna kimbap had a nice kick, the bulgogi rice was flavorful and tender, and the dumpling soup was both hearty and satisfying. The cold chewy noodles were refreshing, and the bibimbap sauce had a good level of spice. While it may not be the best Korean food I've ever had, it's definitely a solid spot for authentic Korean cuisine.

Got the seafood pancake and army stew. Portion sizes were very generous and prices were worth. You are also allowed to take leftovers and u basically get two meals out of one. I think it’s great for people looking to dine in or just get food when they’re too tired to cook. Flavor was good and pancake was crispy. Army stew was very hearty and filling.

A wonderful place that's a hidden gem located in the heart of Allston.

The place has a lot of seating and was able to seat us nearly instantly. The servers are quick and are very knowledgeable about the menu, I believe it is a family business so they understand all the parts. The food comes out quite fast, within 20 minutes of us ordering.

The food is really good, one of my favorites in the area. I got the combo meal, which came with the soup, tteokbokki, and kimbap. It was priced reasonably and came with good portion sizes. The kimbap has a nice consistency, and for the price you get a lot of it. The tteokbokki had a nice kick to it but wasn't overly spicy, and the fish cake soup had a nice healthy and clean taste to it.

A great place that I will return to again.

Authentic Korean food! Everything was so good. Coming from Japan, I really enjoyed the food and felt at home. The staff were very welcoming and recommended trying the pu dae chi gae next time. I will definitely come back!

Me and my friend ordered the Dak-Galbi and tuna gimbap. If you order the "hotpot serving for two," it is actually quite a lot. I think it's good for 3 people too, especially if you order other dishes like gimbap.

I absolutely love their kimchi pork rib hotpot and I mostly order it whenever I come. The budae jjigae is also pretty good.

I've been to this place a lot because they have been making consistently good food. I enjoy the space and the music they have. I highly recommend this place, especially for a nice hangout! The price is also affordable and worth it. Please try this place out!!

You can never go wrong with these monstrosities of meat and cheese in a burger, not to mention their fries are always overflowing out of the cup into the brown paper bag.

I can just imagine the training session for Five Guys.

Manager: Add fries!
Trainee: But sir, the cup is full...
Manager: ADD MORE FRIES!
Trainee: ...now the bag is full...
Manager: Perfect.
Definitely the best burger in town. Sadly, I water in the fountain soda machine is not filtered and tastes metallic. Please fix please!! ;-)

I have been to Dubai and Barça in Five Guys restaurants. I like the fries there! More than the burgers - a portion of fries for the small hunger always goes. The customer experience is always awesome, the staff here in Boston was super friendly and helpful.
People, or rather women, who work at night do not cooperate and start talking instead of doing the orders as quickly as possible. For them, work is a joke.

The service is fast in this branch, but please be careful with the trash can . My brothers and I were injured when we threw the trash inside the branch, as the edges of the trash can are very sharp and caused injuries to our hands. We did not know about this until after we left the branch and one of them said, “I suddenly injured my hand for no reason.”

I've been running around the city looking for good sushi

Oppa has some of the best I've tried in the area. Their sushi is not weighed down with seaweed and you can taste the fish. (For the norms)

Everything they do is perfect.

Fish is properly done, you will not find their quality anywhere in Boston. This is fact, with over 600 sushi restaurants across the globe, it no longer becomes an opinion.

So how they do it? They work and massage the fish. Most restaurants don't have time or wages to do this. They marry the taste correctly, really better than anything I've ever tasted.

Their employees are friendly and comfortable. They come to work to serve amazing food. You don't need to look amazing to do this. They do a great job at keeping the importance of the food.

Enjoy their hot sake, enjoy their food.

One of my favorite sushi places in the Allston area. It’s almost underground and they’ve recently expanded so it’s not tight and uncomfortable. Staff is always very friendly and it’s a great place to go as a group. You can try multiple rolls
Without breaking the bank. Also, if you do go alone the rolls are reasonably priced as well.

I’ve tried most of their menu and they never disappoint. Checkout the photos below and ask for the flaming sushi, it’s great for show!

Fresh fish and hot sake = great time and happy bellies

My friend and I came here looking for some Korean style sushi. While their menu was limited than I initially expected, we were able to find the spicy fish bowl soup which is a popular dish in Korea during the summer. The bowl came with an icy cold broth and vegetables that enhanced the refreshing aftertaste. The classic combination of thinly sliced squid and the sweet and spicy broth was nice, but the broth was too sweet for my taste. We also had the regular sushi and the scallop yaki, but both were unfortunately mediocre at best.

Without AC, the restaurant was extremely hot and humid. The servers tried their best to provide us with a table closest to a fan, but it was pointless. Humidity and temperature are also critical factors in maintaining the quality of the sushi, so it was a bit concerning. We were also hugely disappointed when we found out that some items on the menu were more expensive than what was indicated. The fish bowl soup ended up being $10 more expensive, and we didn’t realize this until we got out. Although I would love to give a higher rating for their superb service, the overall experience wasn’t worth what I paid for.

I feel that this place is underrated. Oppa is great and it has the potential to be more! This is hole in the wall authentic. Don't come here thinking it's a grandeur building because it isn't. It's small and homey but the sushi is worth it. Service was good - didn't hover and explained which rolls were placed where on the plate. We did have to ask for a water refill but it is one person serving/greeting/seating and he had a lot going on between others dining in and picking up take out so, give some grace! Miso soup is given complimentary when you are seated. It had a great flavor, a little room temperature but the tofu was cooked just right. We had the Red Dragon, Oppa Maki, Tornado Maki and Rainbow. The Tornado and Rainbow were our favorites! Their sake was light and mild, which I really liked (and I'm not a Sake fan). Reasonably priced sushi for being in Boston, averaged $30/person for our meal. If you're looking for somewhere low-key and has quality, check out Oppa!

A bit of a hidden gem in the Allston area! Walking past this spot for almost a year, I had no knowledge of this restaurant, nor how good it would be. Right when you are sat down they bring complimentary miso soup for the table, and as someone who is normally not a big fan, i thoroughly enjoyed it. I got the Allston roll and the Pink Lady Maki, and both were very good. The food was all great but the price was a bit higher then I would have thought. Will definitely try again in the future.

ChIJw-xam79544kRIgnwpyJn7y4.name: Jin’s fine Asian cuisine sushi bar

reviews.text: Food is cooked fresh and is reasonably priced. Good serving sizes here too. The service is top noch and the food comes out pretty fast. I recommend coming here for the lunch specials, which are available Mon-Sat until 3pm.

We loved everything about this restaurant -- the ambiance is relaxed yet visually elevated, the staff was attentive and courteous, and the food was delicious. I had the spicy cumin lamb, and my wife had the house fried rice. We shared some pan fried dumplings as well. Everything was tasty, and the prices were super affordable especially considering the enormously generous portions. We can't wait to come back again or even grab to go at the end of a long day!

Excellent food and equally good service. We ordered the hotpot with potatoes and asked to have some extra veggies added. Our server gave her honest opinion regarding which veggies would be better left out and what worked with the potatoes. The hotpot was delicious. The veggie dumplings and the sushi was also very good. My favorite was the hot and sour soup. It was delicious, very tasty and comforting. I would definitely recommend this place!

The service and atmosphere of this place is excellent. I would recommend the lamb spicy pot, mongolian beef, and string beans. As with duck, it's always a hit or miss, and personally I thought the duck was a miss. That being said all the other dishes I mentioned are absolutely delicious!

If you’re looking for a solid, tried-and-true Chinese and Japanese spot, you have to check out Jin’s.

Jin’s is a modern and upscale establishment that offers a massive menu filled with Chinese and Japanese Food. The menu is massive, so be sure to take time to soak it all in.

If you love Chinese food, they have you covered. You’ll find a huge selection of starters and dim sum. They have a large selection of soups- such as Wonton, Hot and Sour, Miso, and more! They do have salads on their menu as well!

For the main course, they have a massive selection of Chinese favorites. You’ll find classics like beef and broccoli and happy family. They have multiple preparations of dishes made with shrimp, beef, and/or chicken. There truly is something for everyone.

The portion size is LARGE. You can easily split an entree. Otherwise, the rest makes solid leftovers! Be aware the entrees DO NOT come with rice if you order delivery.

If you are leaning more towards Japanese, you won’t be disappointed! You’ll find a solid selection of starters such as edamame, shrimp and vegetable tempura, spring rolls, gyoza, and more!

Jin’s has a solid selection of fresh sushi. You’ll find a wide selection of fresh sashimi and nigiri. If you like maki rolls, they’ve got something for you! They offer everything from a basic California roll to an exquisite $20+ maki roll.

They offer multiple sushi combos, sushi plates, and samplers. If you plan to dine in with multiple people, they do have a “boat” of sushi with sashimi and other assorted sushi.

We stopped into Jin’s on a late Sunday afternoon before the dinner rush. The atmosphere is modern, relaxing, and peaceful. You can dine in the main dining room, or you can park yourself at the sushi bar if you’re coming solo.

We started with an order of the Wonton Soup. The soup came out piping hot and the aroma of the broth was incredible! The wontons were incredible as well. They were the perfect size.

Next, we decided to order some steamed edamame with lime and the “Beijing Ravioli”. The edamame were steamed and salted perfectly. I strongly suggest a generous squeeze of lime over the top!

The Beijing Ravioli is some of the best I have had in a long time. I would compare them to a traditional pork “potsticker”. They were pan-fried to perfection, not too greasy. The dipping sauce served with it hits just right!

After the Beijing Ravioli and the Steamed Edamame, we decided to order the Seared Ahi and the “Snow Mountain Maki”. They both were incredibly fresh and flavorful.

The Seared Ahi tuna was seared perfectly and served in a mustard sauce. The portion size was phenomenal for the price! The “Snow Mountain Maki” is a shrimp tempura roll topped with king crab and mayonnaise.

I’d highly suggest Jin’s if you’re a fan of Chinese and Japanese cuisine. The sushi is phenomenal and reasonably priced for the portion size and quality of ingredients.

I’d recommend dining in if you can. The service is incredibly attentive and the food does come out QUICK. If you like to eat at a slower pace like I do, just stagger your orders appropriately.

They do offer delivery in-house and via UberEats/DoorDash. I noticed they do a TON of delivery and takeout orders. Everything is always packed incredibly well and all the condiments and accoutrements are in the bag. They always get it right!

My only complaint would be the dessert menu. I found it to be very disappointing. I would suggest they offer mochi or something more fit to the cuisine.

One of my favorite spots in Allston for lunch specials.

Been coming here for lunch whenever I’m running errands in the area. While trendy new Chinese restaurants are constantly popping up in Allston, Dumpling Kingdom offers classic Chinese lunch specials that transport me back to simpler times. Forget the flashy newcomers. This unassuming restaurant consistently satisfies my cravings at unbeatable prices.

Their lunch specials feature over 20 items, each accompanied by a complimentary side of egg drop soup and white rice. Some of my favorites include the Mala Spicy Flounder Fillet and Twice Cooked Pork. The flounder fillet, with its perfect balance of heat and tender meat, is one of the best I've had in Boston. Other dishes I've tried, like Beef with Scallions, Salt and Pepper Pork Chops, and Taiwanese Pork Belly, were also solid.

I've also tried two of their dumplings and particularly enjoyed the Mini Juicy Buns with Pork & Crabmeat. While the umami of the fillings wasn't completely satisfying, these buns were packed with a good amount of pork juice—so much so that my first bite splashed all over my shirt.

Despite this amazing lunch special deal, the restaurant doesn’t get crowded during lunchtime, so I highly recommend giving them a try.

Food is pretty consistent here. We always get the pork soup dumplings and it's very juicy inside. The filet fish soup with sour cabbage (has vermicelli noodles underneath) is very light and perfect for a cold night. The pork belly was very tender and flavorful. The Kung pao chicken had a nice kick but not too spicy. Dining area closes at 10pm but take out goes until midnight.
Staff is friendly and attentive. Food comes out quick, so if you don't want everything too come out at once, then don't order all at once.

Our meal at Dumpling Kingdom was excellent! I really enjoyed our meal here and the service was good. The food was excellent and I highly recommend the flounder and the sesame chicken. Portion sizes were big and the food came out quickly. Highly recommend this place!

You can't get this great of food in New Hampshire.  We can't sing enough praises for this place! Thank you for the great dining experience and amazing food! Definitely would recommend and definitely will come back!

This place has so much to offer! Love their dumplings and scallion pancakes. I’ve been here a lot of times, and haven’t ever had a dish I didn’t like.

Best place for some quick greasy comfort food.
I always order from this place on uber eats but i wanted to try it in person too! Definitely didn’t disappoint. Good atmosphere, fresh food. Delish!

Decent option for Mediterranean fast food in Allston.

Took a couple of visits while looking for a quick meal in the area. The restaurant was mostly empty during my visits, so it was somewhat disappointing to find out that they used pre-carved meats for the Shawarma plate. The kebab plate was served with a made-to-order grilled chicken, so it seemed like the vertical spits, adorned with stacks of beef and chicken, were just there as decorations. While limited in numbers, their sides and salad options were great, but the meats were generally on the drier end.

In terms of pricing, Garlic N Lemons positions itself at the higher end compared to other kebab joints in the city, such as Aceituna. However, the quality of the food, particularly the meats, doesn't notably surpass its competitors. While it may be a solid option in Allston, I’m not sure if I would return.

A solid choice for fast mediterranean food in Allston!

Food: The food was really good - we tried one plate and one wrap. The tastes were there, the veggies tasted fresh and the sauces/dips were really tasty as well (especially the spicy garlic one).
My personal preference was spicy beef, as the chicken was not as great, but that might just be a question of preference. Still, although the meat was precut and loaded to plates from the tray (a little disappointment), it still tasted pretty good.

Service: Communication was a little messy, since the place was almost empty, but it was fast.

Ambiance: It's nothing special. Everytime I pass it by it's half empty, so I assume many people order take out. It's definitely not a place for a date, but for what it is - it's great!

Got some shawarma plates, One was mixed shawarma and other was spicy chicken. The food was delicious and there was lot of meat portions. Loved the salad, hummus and sides too. Mixed meat was so tasty than the spicy chicken. Pita and baklava dessert was great. The flavor was really good and the price was affordable. The food portions was good for the price. Will definitely visit again. Great place to try if you are into Mediterranean foods 👍👍👍🙏🙏🙏🔥🔥🔥

The best spot for Mediterranean food in the Allston area. I have had takeout several times, with the Mix Shawarma plate being the go to everytime. This is a heaping portion and gives you such a great selection at a decent price. All of the meat options are always flavorful and I love the customization options with the dips and salads, making each time feel very unique. Would definitely recommend checking it out.

Great place with a HUGE selection of drinks!! Took the "peach me how to bourbon" (bourbon, peach, honey, and lemon w/ orange slice) and loved it! Amazing nachos as well. Amazing vibe and service too!!

Had dinner outside with a friend. We got buffalo tenders and sweet potato tots. It was all so good. The buffalo sauce was amazing. We also got 5 drinks between the 2 of us. I originally ordered the Comm Ave Cooler because it sounded like a mimosa; pretty good. But my friend had I think it was Ryes Up, which tasted like orange plus sprite. That was amazing and we had 4 total of those! The waitresses were really nice and attentive.
The Avenue Bar Allston was a great, dark, cozy, chill bar. The tacos were amazing and the service is the best around. Would definitely stop in again.

This is a sports bar on Comm Ave with an extensive selection of beverages. The nachos we ordered were not good, the cheese seemed really hard and over baked. The burgers were alright, very average. There is a great selection of beer and inventive cocktails, so I would recommend coming here for drinks. The best part was the cute ketchup bottle on the table, so adorable!

If you’re looking for a dining experience that will make you question your life choices, this place might be just the ticket. Drinks: The Avenue Bar take on the Negroni is both overpriced and an affront to the senses. Overly sweet and very medicinal. Why messing up a good thing? The Espresso Martini? Bland and watery, with about as much kick as a soggy napkin. I also tried the chips and Buffalo chicken dip. The chips were so old, bland and tough, they could have doubled as a new kind of dental torture. The Buffalo chicken dip was a sorry excuse for flavor, more of a ghost of Buffalo chicken than the real deal. Save yourself the agony and find somewhere else to dine.

ChIJyS2haMV544kRV4JTKfWH7lw.address: 66 Harvard Ave # B, Allston, MA 02134, USA

reviews.text: @UNION was a quick walk down the road from our AirBNB. The food, service, and atmosphere were amazing. There was plenty of food and everything came out quickly. It was a quiet weekday morning. There was no wait and plenty of tables open. Our waitress was great! We ended up getting extra coffees to go as we were going to a concert that night.

Solid consistent breakfast items! This spot is great for take out or dine in because the quality is consistent regardless. The French toast and the chicken and waffle from my most recent visit were particularly tasty. The French toast had so many different types of sweetness that you never got fatigued from the sugar. The chicken and waffle was perfectly crispy and the BBQ sauce that was on the chicken even complimented the sweetness from the waffle.

Solid brunch spot. Casual vibes. Was hard to get waitress’s attention at times. Bulgogi benedict was an interesting fusion but not sure if I completely loved it. Would probably come back to try the more basic options.

Came here for brunch on a weekend at 11am and had to wait for 30 mins before we got a table. The food is decent and I enjoyed my omelette a lot. However, the seats are very cramped together and it is so so loud that sometimes it is difficult to have a conversation with others.
Great Bagel sandwich. a complete meal and a bagel. Service was friendly and attentive. However, ignore sign that says coffee is bottomless. Full charge for a second cup of Americano

I tried the (now closed) Providence location and wasn't really impressed, so it took me 5 years to try the Brookline location. They have an online waitlist but you have to be present and ready to order when your name is called. It's quite efficient, which makes sense for a small restaurant with a lot of business!

The best thing I tried was the original chicken karaage -- it was super crispy and juicy with a wonderful ginger flavor. I also tried the extra crispy karaage, which I thought was not as good as the original because it wasn't as juicy. You can get takeout of just the chicken from their sister shop nearby, which I can definitely envision myself doing in the future.

I got the spicy shoyu ramen which was very striking in appearance -- a very bright red-orange. It had a good savory and spicy flavor, but I'm not sure if I'd get it again. It was a bit one note.

I tried a bit of the other ramens that we got and my favorite was the Gantetsu shoyu. It had a thicker broth with a deep smoky flavor. I'm not sure if I could finish an entire bowl of that richness, but that was definitely the most interesting one we tried! The other shoyu and shio ramens we got were pretty standard.

I'm not ready to say that Ganko Ittetsu is one of my favorite ramen places yet, but it's worth a visit just for the karaage...

We've been coming here for years now, and we have not been disappointed at all by this spot. It is consistently one of our favorite ramen spots to travel to and eat or get take-out at.

They currently have a summer deal going on for 3 Gyozas with any ramen, which is a good steal considering the price of the gyoza is nearly triple the price for what they are offering. We decided to dine-in today, rather than get take-out. They take your orders before you are seated, which allows you to get the ramen decently fast after seating.

I typically order the Gankara Miso, but this time I tried the TanTan style. It was nice and creamy, with a little bit of spice but not overwhelming. The noodles were soft and chewy, and the additional toppings helped to elevate the dish. I also got the gyoza, which came with a ponzu sauce that was a little sweet but very savory. The price is average for a ramen establishment, and they do offer add-ons that may start adding up to your total, but are worth adding. I added extra noodles and crunchy garlic, which helped use most of the remaining broth after I finished my bowl.

The only downside of this location is the amount of tables it has. It has consistently grown, including now some "outdoor" seating for the establishment, but we saw many people get turned away or told the wait was going to be very long for a table. I probably wouldn't ever come here with a party larger than 4 people, as you will have to wait a decent amount of time to be seated.
My best ramen restaurant in Boston. It's almost like the ramen you eat in Asia. The karaage is crisp, so you must eat it!

This place was hidden inside of a shopping center so we couldn’t see it from the street.  You order first before being seated in the small dining room. Once we were seated, the food came very quickly.  The bowls are huge and was a very generous amount of ramen.  The spicy miso ramen was very flavorful and delicious.  The Sapporo shio ramen was also yummy.  The broth was not too rich or spicy.  The service was attentive as well.  Would definitely come back to try other flavors.

Their Gyoza’s are fantastic, ramen is so flavorful that it beats any other ramen spot in the entire area. We have tried many, and this place is the best. WORTH THE WAIT if there is one, but they get you in very fast.

html_attributions: Charles Grato - Just a big guy in his Porkpie Hat

reviews.text: cheesesteak was dry and there was barely any cheese. alfredo was half cold. food took forever to be ready.
Delivered via Doordash. Amazing late night pizza. Hit the spot after a concert and a bunch of beers.

Just fine. Considering the limited options for late-night food in Boston, this is okay for 2 AM food around here. Dough was dry and meat was too salty (ordered the Steak Bomb pizza). Can't go wrong with cheesy bread so that was good!

This is a late night food choice, completely gone wrong. I ordered an eggplant and chicken parm calzone with red crushed pepper. The thing was an open pita blob, no crunch. Dough, forget it undercooked to the point where I questioned if I was eating tasteless mozzarella cheese from the topping of the “open faced calzone”. The breading on the eggplant was so bad it was soggy and adding to more sogginess of the calzone overall. The chicken I added on request wasn’t chicken parm it was chopped up chicken breast chunks unseasoned.

reviews.author_name: Charles Grato - Just a big guy in his Porkpie Hat
reviews.text:
Okay, the first time here.

I'm gonna answer my star rating backward

3 Stars for the Atmosphere, it's a pizza shop like any other. 4 or 5 tables, nothing special about the area, no tvs, pizza boxes stacked up.

4 stars for the Service typical late night pizza shop attitude. They all seemed confused, looking at a pizza for about 4 minutes talking about it. It was weird...

3 stars for the food. Keep in mind that I only ordered an XL Pizza.

I ordered a $25 (Supposid) "XL" Pepperoni "Lovers" pizza.

Okay, I got a 14-inch pizza? A normal large pizza anywhere else is 16 inches... how is this pizza an XL???

OKAY, OKAY, price and size aside... I was nothing special... it had a chewy crust on one side and crispy in random places.

Let's talk about the "Pepperoni Lovers" part of this... I took a picture for you to decide.  But... my opinion this did not look up to its meaning... it had an Average amount of Pepperoni...

To the owners of this shop... I watched so much mo ey walk out the door for people looking for slices.  While I stood there, I counted 18 people walk out the door in the time it took for you to make my pizza.

Start selling SLICES... You're in a College Frat house neighborhood.  You're losing out on sooo much business.

Sheri was a waitress what a great personality . She was extremely friendly and explained the menu to us . Matzoh ball soup is a must have! Lots of options for a Healthy breakfast or if you want your regular American breakfast they have that as well. I had avocado toast with salmon with the lemon zest and a salad. My husband had poached egg with salmon with a potato base toast. it was called the Empire. When you come in, you’ll be pleasantly surprised to see all of the desserts at the countertop. Located right in Brookline!

Coming in at 7pm, the 6 of us were seated quickly.

The food was good for some and mediocre for others. My Chicken Matza Ball Soup was decent. Was it worthy of the "World Famous" title? No. Stop lying on your menus, please.

We will return for breakfast, as their bagels looked amazing.

This review is STRICTLY for the Caesar Salad Wrap! The sauce, the lettuce, the use of real croutons and parmesan left us in AWE. Our only notes were more salad and less chicken please :) Now, let’s start talking about the sides… Hands down the best fries we’ve ever had and the potato salad is the second best after my own kitchen.
