The green beans were unbelievably tasty and had the best crisp and texture. Would definitely recommend you order those and try them.

We also got the prosperity noodles with beef and a Kung pao tofu dish, which was my favorite. The tofu was extremely crispy and flavorful, however, there was a few hints of lemongrass which our party did not enjoy. Otherwise, everything had such good flavor. Would 100% recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a good Szechuan style meal in the Boston area.

Open late with delicious and quick bites to eat. In a city that sleeps a little too early for my taste this is a nice offering. Haven't tried much of their menu but had some of their new grilled lamb skewer special... And wow. $2 or $2.50 for a skewer is a great price for a delicious bite to eat. I would get three or four of these and maybe a soup for less than $10 and just be extremely happy at midnight on a weekend.

Can't wait to keep visiting this place.
Will DEF order again for sure!! Ordered on Ubereats, lots of choices, good prices😃

Awesome Chinese food and the service is great! I tried the beef fried rice and they give you a generous portion of beef and veggies. The quality is solid—not greasy or heavy. Definitely bringing my friends next time!!

My friend and I found this restaurant while walking by and had to leave a comment because it was so good! We ordered tomato and egg stir-fry, sesame chicken, and fried shrimp. Every dish was big, reasonably priced, and tasted authentic. Highly recommend! GOOOOOD!

I recently dined at Hongkong Cafe and had a wonderful experience. The atmosphere was inviting, and the service was exceptional. I ordered the General Tsao's Chicken and Chicken Teriyaki, both of which were absolutely delicious. The General Tsao's Chicken had the perfect balance of sweet and spicy, with crispy chicken pieces coated in a flavorful sauce. The Chicken Teriyaki was equally impressive, with tender, juicy chicken and a rich, savory teriyaki glaze. Both dishes were cooked to perfection and served with generous portions. I highly recommend Hongkong Cafe for anyone looking for great food and excellent service. I will definitely be returning soon!

Came here for the first time last night and was pleasantly surprised. They had a special discounted acai bowl that my friends enjoyed, but I opted for the Blue Lagoon bowl. It had fresh blueberries and was super filling.

The service is friendly and the space is bright and clean, making Bare Blends a good stop for some nutritious and yummy bowls and smoothies!

Was in town for business and after a run I wanted to find somewhere to get a protein fix. This place was perfect. The nutter butter bowl was brilliant. I added raisins and extra chocolate protein to it. Could not fault it. I will definitely be coming back when I'm back in town.

I pre-ordered an acai crunch bowl. When I got there I told them I was picking up an order and they told me they were making it right now. 3 people came in after that and also ordered bowls. 2 or them got their orders before I, so I asked about my order and they again said it was being made right now, so I said okay. A few minutes later they gave me an order that did not match what I had ordered, so I asked if it was correct and they then realized that they gave me the wrong one and that my order had been sitting in the fridge, probable for at least 15 minutes as I was waiting there for 20. I got back to my place and went to eat it and realized that they didn't give me the Bananas that were supposed to be on it and there was about 3 small pieces of cut strawberry on it. I am GREATLY disappointed with what I received and will not return or recomend to anyone.

Update - there were 3 slices of banana that sunk to the bottom. Still disappointing and still would not return.

I have just started coming here over the past few weeks.  I have mixed feelings about this place....I have only had one product here, so I cannot remark on the menu as a whole, though I saw a bowl today that looked like a piece of art.  Within the last 2/3weeks, I have ordered their hot Peanut Butter coffee.  If you enjoy these two things, you will possibly be in for a treat.  I ordered this every day for a week....half of the week was delicious; the other half, it tasted as if they had only used 1/3 the amount of pb, so that it was a hint instead of the feature of the beverage.  I enjoy coffee, so I just let it go but it would be nice to have a consistent experience.  The other observation is the customer service...No one was outwardly rude; however, today was the 1st time I walked in and did not feel I was bothering the staff. There also seems to be no way to alert the staff you have entered.   Today, the woman was smiling, was warm and made my coffee in a third of the time it has ever taken.  This is odd because there was an actual line today and she was quicker than when I am the only one there!   I always order Hot instead of iced and once, when I came to pick up, it was Iced.  The employee remarked "most people order Iced because it's hot outside"--I wasn't offended, it just came across as if my choice was illogical as opposed to her mistake due to the weather-related assumption.  The woman today added a tad too much milk that tempered the heat of my coffee, but she was so pleasant and the coffee, at least, tasted the way it should, so I did not even care.  I point it out to illustrate when you have a welcoming demeanor, it can really change an experience even if it was not perfect.

My sister comes here all the time so I decided to give it a whirl. I normally don't drink smoothies but I thought the Green Giant was really filling and flavorful. Excellent customer service and very clean.

Great experience. I ordered Lee burger and my son ordered BLT sandwich and strawberry smoothie. All are supreme. Service was fast despite of many people ordering at kiosk, online or at counter. Place is clean. Price was reasonable (for portion size). Highly recommended.

After a long day I was craving a cheeseburger. Conveniently located almost at the crux of Coolidge Corner, this seemed like a good option.  Non of the specialty burgers seemed attractive to me, so I ordered a regular cheeseburger with lettuce and tomato and some fries. With a fried egg on top.

Let me get the good out of the way: the burger patty was juicy, it was delicious, it was thick and worth the price. The fries also were excellent. I got them with barbecue sauce (which I would not recommend), but by their lonesome they were perfectly fried and seasoned which is impressive considering how thick they were. Really nice job with both the patty and the fries.

I was way less impressed with the toppings. The lettuce was iceberg quality and helpfully fell out in a single piece as I was trying to eat it. The buns were low quality and became essentially mush as I attempted to eat the top tall hamburger (and this was with me removing two toppings). The fried egg was overcooked and extraneous. When I order a fried egg on a burger I expect it to be cooked well, not well done.

That all being said, this is a burger joint and the burger was by far the best part of the meal. Moreover the fries were really good. I think if you’re craving a decent burger in the area you could do worse. But there are definitely better options if you want to venture into Boston.

Disappointed. We have historically gotten the "spicy crispy chicken sandwich" as takeout. It has always been exactly what it says: spicy and crispy... until now.
The past two times, the chicken has been more like the frozen chicken cutlet you get at the supermarket. Absolutely not crispy, flat, and flacid (kind of like the place with the arches). Flavor of spice is still there, just the texture and crunch was a huge miss. We thought it may have been a mistake the last time so we decided to get it again. We were once again disappointed.
We always found the spicy crispy chicken better than that famous place from a southern state, but now it is much further at the bottom in terms of crispy chicken sandwiches.
We wanted a late night snack and Lee's was open.  We ordered at the kiosk which was handy as this was our first visit.  Fast service and tasty food was an overall good experience.
Found this gem while just walking around. Burger was tasty, medium waffle fries were perfect (crispy outside, soft inside) and more than I could finish. Strawberry smoothie went well with the meal!

This is a hidden gem of Coolidge Corner/Brookline. The atmosphere is welcoming and comfortable. The menu is tastefully done, focusing on doing things delicious, not offering everything under the sun. The menu has something for everyone, beef, chicken, seafood and vegan. I had the lemongrass chicken skewers and they were outstanding! The craft cocktail, also a rec’d of my server, was outstanding: Spice Cooler, rum based with a really beautiful pineapple mint. Definitely coming here again!

The grilled beef banh mi was just okay. The bread was crispy and good, but I wish the grilled beef was better. Also the mayo might be too much.
We loved the truffle tater tots. They were crispy and flavorful and not too greasy.

We appreciated how nice the servers were, but the frequency of their check-ins can be a bit uncomfortable.

My friend and I were excited to try this place. The decor is nice, and we enjoyed sitting by the large picture window that opens to the outside. The service was attentive. I get that feeling that many of them were new, so things will probably be more natural with time.

However, the food was disappointing. The papaya salad was too sweet, without the savory flavors of garlic, shrimp, or even chilis. Texture was nice though. The lemongrass chicken was roasted, but felt super crispy. The accompaniments of macaroni salad, rice (a bit mushy) and fruit were underwhelming. We tried the macarons too—nice texture on the outside but super thick cream on the inside. Overall, sad to say but we won’t be back.

Wonderful, eclectic, and creative food and drinks! A delightful set of familiar French, British, and Vietnamese, but all with a bit of a twist. They have different menu items for lunch, dinner, and weekends, so it is worth checking out multiple times. We were very impressed with the Imaginative dishes with excellent presentation and flavor. Staff are super friendly. We highly recommend the bao, bone marrow bahn mi, beef wellington, and even the fries were excellent! For the (sweet) coffee lover, the egg coffee is a must try. Can't wait to try out the other menus!

Lunch menu has amazing butter egg on fluffy milk bread sandwiches!

Esmai's is a Hidden Gem located in the former Hops n Scotch location right in Coolidge Corner. They have a focus on Western dishes with an Asian twist.

The restaurant's first floor boasts a large seating area with a large bar. We came during brunch time, and it was crowded but still had a lot of space for seating upstairs. We were seated almost instantly. The service was exceptional, with them explaining the dishes, checking in on our food throughout the meal, and bringing the food out in a timely manner.

The prices of the dishes are on the average size for the portion, but we really enjoyed the food we got here. We got the Jasmine Tea and the Vietnamese Egg Coffee, both of which were really good and had traditional flavors in them. For our brunch, we got the Souffle Pancakes and the Karaage Chicken with Egg on Milk Bread. The Milk bread sandwich was fluffy and the karaage wasn't too oily, and it came in a decent portion size. The Souffle pancake came with a light syrup that wasn't too sweet. The souffle did look a little deflated, but was still pretty good and fluffy. We also got the truffle fries, which came with a decent portion of truffle, as well as a nice dipping sauce for the fries.

Overall a good place to go to for a brunch out. The dinner menu also looks pretty good and enticing, such as the banh mi & bone marrow charcuterie plate.

I’ve never had a bad experience at this Taco Bell so I was saddened by Taco Bell order. I usually have no issues with my cheesy Gordita crunches however today all 3 of the one in my order were extremely stale and the soft taco was completely off of the crunchy shell, defeating the point of the taco. Further my chicken taco was split all down the bottom before I even unwrapped it. Besides that it all tasted well, and service was good. Hole to have better quality next time.

Literally the worst Taco Bell experience ever. Skimped is an understatement. An actual 5 pieces of chicken in my chalupa and 3 tomatoes like?? It’s cheap food the least you could do is FILL the taco. Quesadilla and classic crunch taco were the same, basically half filled. What waste of money.

Wonderful meal at the Taco Bell in Coolidge Corner. Friendly and helpful staff, and loved the Veggie-only filter on the self check out. The DIY salsa bar was a nice touch. Don’t miss the root beer and the breakfast salsa.

Finally! Taco Bell fills a long standing gap in the culinary space of the Coolidge corner area. If you are craving for a good fast food meal and don’t want to spend a fortune this place is for you. The food somehow tastes better than at other Taco Bell’s, I hope they’ll keep up with the qually. I had a five layer cheesy burrito, and of course a Crunchwrap supreme and boy oh boy it brought back these old memories. Don’t forget to ask for an enormous amount of hot sauce packets which really add to any dish. The place is brand new and clean. I didn’t interact too much with the staff as they have six touch screens where you can put in your order, but the staff was really really nice.
I am a local guide but earth is my hometown, meaning that ive had tacos in many many many very many different restos, and Taco Bell is still always special. A very brave bet to open a Taco Bell in this location but virtue saves the brave.

Nika was working so hard to get the food out fast! There was steam coming off it! Very impressed with my visit. I also had at least 5 swaps/changes to my order and each were executed with precision. My favorite taco bell in Boston by far!

Have dined here many times for dinner. We usually come here when we crave Thai flavors. They do that well here, especially their curries. Their red and yellow curries are great, very comforting and tasty each and every time that we've had them. Their tofu pad Thai is very good. The chicken katsu that you can order with pad Thai is hit or miss though. We've had some that were over fried and very dry.

Their portion sizes are good but can be a bit inconsistent sometimes. The sticky rice with mango dessert and coconut sauce is great though a tag too sweet for me so I skip the sauce. The spring rolls and calamari rings are decent appetizers but portions are on the small side. The ramen and sushi dishes are not the standouts at this restaurant but acceptable for a quick meal. I always get a Thai ice tea here, very refreshing and not too sweet.

Service is friendly and quick. I see families with small children here quite often. This restaurant offers consistently good food at reasonable prices. It is a great addition to the neighborhood.

This restaurant is a delightful surprise! The dishes are fresh and delicious, and the staff is warm and attentive, making you feel right at home. The ambiance is elegant, perfect for gatherings or dates. I highly recommend their signature dishes

Authentic Thai and Tremptatious!

I loved the ground pork stir-fry basil here. Unlike other spots that use big chunks of pork, they use perfectly ground pork, which I prefer. The flavors are spot-on, and the ingredients are top-notch. If you want real Thai taste in Boston, this is the place!

I’ve tried their regular menu and late night menu. The Late Night menu is EXCELLENT! So tasty and it made me feel like I’m in Thailand. Sooooooo exotic and DELICIOUS. The Late Night menu is only available on Sunday, Monday and Tuesday: 10pm-1am. The time is not very convenience but you gotta try it at least once.. The crab fried rice is so yummy.

Had a big group for dinner. Once we stepped inside, it seemed that the AC broke.
We ordered a bunch of dishes. I felt that some of the sushi rolls were sweet. The rolls were ok. It wasn't anything special.

Wow! This place is amazing and reasonably priced! The food was absolutely delicious. I guess the only thing that was concerning was the price of the draft beer compared to the small glass they serve it in. Having said that, they did go out of their way to comp me a "free draft beer" when I brought it to their attention. Well done and "thank you"!

TLTR: Solid 4/5.

Tried this place after a friend recommended them for their gluten-free noodle option.

Not bad. Had their tofu and tuna rolls — unexpectedly good, y’all. (Though I did not appreciate their approach to a hand roll. It was like a seaweed taco. Couldn’t take a clean bite.) The way they got so much flavor into a stick of tofu is admirable. Their spicy tuna was delicious, reminiscent of tuna tartare.

Tried their spicy miso ramen, made with a chicken broth instead of tonkotsu, which I appreciate. Instead of chashu, had the chicken — nice flavor with a hint of ginger. My friend had the chashu, which he said would have been nicer with some charring/ could have used more time in the broiler. Their noodles are *on point.* Cooked just right. It’s either MSG or a novel deliciousness carrier technology — the way those noodles carry flavor is something else. The broth needs further elaboration. A bit too heavy on the salt and superficial on the flavoring. But the foundations are there to make it superb with just a little tweaking. Perfect ajitama.

Their sticky rice is on the sweeter side, with a hint of coconut. Delicious. To me, more enjoyable as dessert. 🤷🏻‍♀️

My friend tried their Thai iced tea. I had their strawberry matcha. Maybe they taste better spiked, but we got them just as tea and they were unremarkable. My strawberry matcha was not milky enough and too sweet. They did seem to use a strawberry purée, which was nice. The boba though — some of the best boba I’ve had, which kept nicely over the couple hours it took me to finish the drink. 😅 (That’s how stuffed I was.)

The place itself is simple, though with a trendy vibe and eclectic music playlist. Varied menu. Appreciate the ceiling feature of hanging 2x4s. Bathrooms were quite clean.

All in all, do recommend you try it out. I’ll def be back to try their pho and other dishes.

Mecha Noodle Bar is a ramen & pho shop located in the heart of Coolidge Corner, with another location in the Seaport District of Boston. It has a very modern interior with an open kitchen, as well as many seating options throughout the restaurant. When we came, it was very crowded, but were seated almost instantly. However, I would probably not come here with a party larger than 4 due to the limited large-group seating and how popular the restaurant is.

The service was phenomenal. They were quick to serve us, as well as had enough waitstaff on hand to keep circulating to take finished dishes away and refill water nearly instantly after it was empty. Even with how busy the restaurant is, it was nice to see they could continue to care for the customers.

We tried the Soft-Shelled Crab Bao and the Shoyu Ramen. The Soft-Shelled Crab Bao came with Pickles and a nice sauce drizzle on it. The soft shelled crab was fried lightly, and it wasn't oily at all. The Shoyu Ramen was pretty good. One minor gripe was with the noodles, it felt a bit too stringy and not like typical ramen noodles, instead more similar to buckwheat or soba noodles , but it was still pretty good and had good flavor. The broth wasn't too salty and was overall a good dish.

A good first experience at this restaurant and would highly recommend checking it out.

I walked past this place so many times, but there are usually too many people, so I did not get in.

Got a chance to try it today.

First off, the server was very polite and helpful. The atmostphere was good, very open, clean, and chilled.

I ordered a tonkotsu ramen. The pork was delicious but came in such a small portion, but given the price (17) this is reasonable.The soup was rich, and the noodle was well cooked.

Visited this place for the first time after hearing many good reviews from our friends. Me and my husband are vegetarians and to our surprise they have a variety of veg dishes. We also aren't a huge fan of mushrooms but we really loved the mushroom dishes here.

We tried a variety of dishes like shitake mushroom baos which were delicious, herbed edmame which was okayish. I loved the tofu banh mi, it was freshly made, crisp and perfectly seasoned. The cold tofu rolls were also not that bad. The kimchi fried rice was tasty too but we felt it had a bit more oil. They could have avoided putting so much oil. That's the only reason giving them 4 stars for food.

Drinks were also nice, we tried the Iron Fist and Eastern bonfire ritual and liked the later one more.

We will definitely visited again, would love to try their veg Ramen and would also love to have a few dishes again!😁

I’ve heard so many good things about this place, so I was a bit disappointed. The food was just okay. The service was super fast, though!

I got veggie dumplings pan fried. The filling was good. It had good texture and taste. Sadly there was a lot more oil that I expected. I do expect some oil with pan fried dumplings, but this was a ton.

The customer service was amazing, but the pork and chive dumplings I got were extremely soggy and the meat tasted sour. The only good part of the dumplings was the soy sauce. I also got a wrap which was pretty good. The dumplings could have been much better if they were fried and the food was fresher tasting.

Portions were small and the only good tasting thing was the pork buns which were actually really good. The Dan Dan noodles just weren’t it…tasted like a weird, very aggressive, expired peanut flavor. Not Dan Dan noodles at all. Ended up not even eating it. But the staff was nice and online ordering was good.

This place is really good. The dumplings are a great size and seared nicely, I wish the dough was a bit thinner. The noodles are a great portion and seasoned/spiced well. The buns are full and soft. The scallion pancakes  are good but super thin: good if you're into that.  The spring rolls are flavored well and the insides are cut and cooked nicely but they are a bit too oily. The brussels are delightful. I look forward to going back.

Ordered for takeout. Did not even have the courtesy to tell us the food was ready.

Food itself was rather middling, the Dan Dan noodle was good with chewy enough noodles but we do prefer more spicy. Dumplings were nothing special, just OK. Fried rice was a bit strange, rice itself not being dry enough and there were raisins inside. Not good enough for me to go back on this one.

I am glad this place is not near my house, or I am will be eating their burritos every day 🔥 The tortilla shell is very chewy and not wet at all. The protein is also well balanced with all the other sides🤩definitely worth trying!

This is my first time eating a burrito if all burritos are this good I might chose to eat burritos forever. The staff were extremely friendly and helpful. And the restaurant itself was very nice and comfortable.
Delicious surf n turf bowl. Reasonably priced as well. Friendly service, I look forward to coming back!
Delicious food and friendly service. I had the spicy chicken burrito and my girlfriend had the Al pastor burrito.

Ordered 2 burritos, shrimp and chicken, and both were bland, even with all the toppings. Not sure how long the food sits in those containers but food didn’t seem fresh. This was a one and done for us.

Fantastic spot for some wonderful food and proper date night vibes. The food is excellent. Tried their salad, broccoli appetizer, burrata pizza for mains and plum cake for dessert. The dessert hits home, the pizza perfectly done and appetizers left us wanting for more. Their cocktails were delicious, I tried their brandy cocktail which blew me away! Their service was exceptional and our waitress was very attentive. Full marks for hospitality. These people know their food and drink. I’m certainly visiting again for more.

Having lived in Brookline for 3 years, I can confidently say Prairie Fire is one of the best restaurants in the Boston area. The food is immaculate, desserts exceptional, and service incredibly friendly. If you’re able to catch a table here I highly recommend. Props to the owners, management, chefs, and front house staff.

Excellent dinner – we started out with the mushroom toast, which was savory and delicious. Pasta was also clearly homemade, albeit a pretty small portion. Service was friendly and attentive and it’s a fun environment. Will definitely go back to try the pizza.

I'd give it a 4.5. Pizzas were 10/10 really amazing. Apps were solid but not great. Sausage was super dry but tasty, brussel sprouts undercooked but has good flavor, cornbread was not that good. Steak had delicious sauce but steak it self was prepared lazily with no seasoning. Good beer selection and really talented bar staff with good cocktails and wines.

Loved their fire pizza. It has a nice ambience and the servers were great. I was immediately seated next to the kitchen door while all the window spaces where available. I thought at the beginning that maybe because our chosen table was for two but then several pairs were seated at these tables which made us question if we were placed there by pure bias. I think customers should be asked where they prefer sitting if the place has empty tables.

Love their gyu don, tonkatsu curry and ebi fry hand roll (so juicy)! Order at the counter and then head to many tables to grab free seating spot while we wait for the dishes made to order. I like their iced green tea as well, brewed just right and served with perfect amount of ice. Order large as medium would definitely leave you wanting for more.. Kids menu is also very well priced with fair portion.

Maruichi Select is a cafe with a small market area that is good for studying. This is located across the street from the Maruichi grocery store, which carries more robust options for groceries.  There are some similarities in products they carry such as Onigiri, but Maruichi Select has a wider focus on meals such as Curry, Ramen, and Katsudon.

The area is very open, with a sizeable amount of seating located in the back, however it does get quite busy and may be difficult to find seating when coming here in the afternoon. The service is quite quick, even with a long line the food still came out within 10-15 minutes.

We tried the Matcha Strawberry Latte, the White Peach Shaved Ice, the Chashu + Egg, Karaage, and Spicy Karaage Onigiri. The Matcha Strawberry Latte was smooth and mixed quite well, and tasted not too sweet. The strawberry at the bottom helped add a bit of sweetness that wasnt too overwhelming. I don't like white peach at all, but the shaved ice was light and fluffy and did have a good peachy flavor. The highlight probably was the Onigiri. Compared to the Onigiri sold at the grocery stores, these ones were much larger, with a decent filling to rice ratio (though a bit more heavy on the rice side) for the price. The spicy karaage was my favorite, as it had a good amount of spices placed on it that weren't too overwhelming but gave it a bit of a kick.

Overall a great experience and I would highly recommend checking it out. They also do have pop-ups and other vendors tabling around the store.

I’ve visited here a few times and would say that the food here is a great value for what you get. However, I’ve noticed that recently the onigiri, hand rolls, and rice bowls are very rice heavy and the onigiri lack on filling. The matcha here is good but not always consistent. Most of the time, the matcha is strong and smooth. However, the last time I got it, the matcha tasted extremely bitter. Even with the addition of sugar, it was hard to mask the taste. I couldn’t finish the drink.
A really stand out place. So glad we took a chance and came in. They had so many awesome Japanese food choices. Everything was great but tje strawberry matcha drink wasnt sweet enough for my liking

This is a cute spot with surprisingly good food.  I like the 2 onigiri + miso + tea combo, but they have lots of other food options like katsu curry.  The hojicha was nice and the karage and salmon onigiri were very fresh.

It can get very busy inside, especially since I was there on a Saturday afternoon.  Seating is limited, and if you cant get a seat you are in trouble if you ordered a lot of items like we did.  I noticed some people lounging around for extended periods of time which isnt super respectful to how busy the place is, but still tables were opening up often enough.

Loved the atmosphere, it was very cute and cozy. Food was average; the soup dumplings were a little bready and not as flavorful as other soup dumplings I’ve had. The chicken dumplings were alright too. I would say the house special hand cut noodles was the best dish, and they were pretty good! Overall I don’t know if I’d come back, but it was pretty solid for a first try.

It was a fun evening all around. Dinner with my daughter, and she picked a new place to go to.

The menu has pics of each dish - what a concept!  The restaurant was much larger inside than we expected; decor was simple, minimalistic, but nice, thoughful; even the individual setups at the table were impressive.

We chose several different items and enjoyed everything. The presentations were engaging, and I followed my daughter's lead on how to handle different dishes before tasting. Again, it was a fun and interactive dining experience - we weren't just eating a steak.

I got the chicken soup dumplings, and the shrimp hand pulled noodle stir-fry. They were both incredible. The dumplings had a really nice soup to meat ratio with the meat being very juicy. noodles were rich in flavor and had a really good texture. I just got takeout tonight, but I thought the inside had a nice vibe and hope to be back for a dine in experience.

Dined here for the first time and general impression is good, some dishes were fairly good and others not so much. Interior has been redone from the Six Po hot pot that was here previously and it looks and feels great, very clean and comfortable.

The pan fried egg/chive bun has very good flavors but the skin had an undercooked texture. The steamed pork dumplings tasted good with a good deal of soup inside. The taro buns were our favorite. They were well made, not greasy, crispy on the outside and not too sweet. The spicy beef noodle soup was only mildly spicy and broth was thin. It lacked flavor and the noodles, I felt, were undercooked in the thick part and overcooked in the thinner part, making the texture strange when chewing. I wouldn't get this again but will try the dry noodles that have a sauce on it, which might have more flavor. We were disappointed by the scallion pancake with beef. The pancake was a bit greasy, which was expected, but there was only 1 small thin slice of beef wrapped inside.

Service was fine. Our waiter was efficient and the server that brought the food was friendly and always had a smile. He asked how we liked the food each time. This new place is a good addition to the neighborhood.

This place is good. I'm not sure it's anything special though for it to be Michelin recommended. I genuinely can't say that the food was bad, but it was like food anyone could find in Chinatown. Maybe we have a really good Chinatown?

The pork buns were well steamed, nice and juicy. The soup dumplings were good, standard. Their hand pulled fried dish was a bit too oily. The noodle soup was good, well seasoned. Reminded me of sullangtang soup base. Their scallion pancake with beef was very small compared to other places. Still, tasty though.

Again, nothing crazy food wise. It's nice that the place seems very clean though!

I've been meaning to try LaMei for a while. The restaurant is quite spacious. We ended up using one pot between 5 people, which I think is close to the reasonable limit that can comfortably use one pot. We got the two flavor broth with bone broth and the spicy premium beef tallow broth. I don't remember if we got mild or medium, but it was very spicy. I didn't end up using any of my sauce because the spicy broth was so strongly flavored.

The highlight for me was definitely the shrimp paste, but I haven't really met a shrimp paste that I don't like. The fish fillet was also pretty good, as was the sliced premium beef (the fatty one). I wouldn't get the ribeye or marinated spicy beef again -- those didn't have good texture.

There were a couple of things for which we weren't sure of the freshness -- the bamboo fungus, for example, had some black spots and didn't taste great. I hope it wasn't mold...

The sauce bar had a good selection, but it did cost $2.95 per person. And if you get the spicy broth, I don't think the sauce is needed. I don't know what it was, but the food was *really* hot which made it a bit hard to eat for impatient people like me.

Overall I liked the shrimp paste, but nothing else was particularly notable. I prefer the broth and meats at Happy Lamb AYCE, so I would definitely go there over here.

This was our first time trying a hot pot and we had an amazing experience.  We tried two broths and happy we went with mild for the hot side.  I can take heat but my heavens it was hot and tasty, both broths were unbelievably flavourful.  For sides we went with beef and pork with a veggie assortment and made our own sauce concoction at the bar.  If you haven’t tried a hot pot I would encourage you to give them a try.
We had the all you can eat hotpot several times. Both the service and food quality are great! It has become our favorite spot for weekend brunch!
Everything is great. Monday - Friday, Buffer All you can eat: 11.30AM-3.30PM. I recommend it.

I recently found this place and absolutely love it! I’ve been eating hot pot across different states, and this spot has quickly become one of my favorites. One thing to note, though, is that the chili powder doesn’t quite taste like the Sichuan powder I’m accustomed to, but it’s still okay

At first we went inside to eat but it was like an oven in there. I'm not sure if they have a/c and it was just broken but we decided to eat outside as it was actually cooler outside. Our server Aimee was wonderful and the food was great. The only disappointment was they were out of dessert as well as the ingredients for a specific drink we wanted. Overall the experience was positive and we look forward to coming back soon.

Terrible meal. Fried spinach was charred and so greasy- not at all edible. Salmon looked deep fried and when I inquired was told it was pan seared...to death, if you ask me. Mashed potatoes, barely warm and not appealing. Waited 45 minutes when there were only 6 people in the entire place? No thanks, too many other options.
Server- Daniel was nice!
I dreamed to try beer Guinness. And I did it. + Had delicious fish and chips

Hamilton Restaurant and Bar is a pretty solid restaurant in terms of food, however, the service was a bit disappointing. Seemed a little disorganized. We had multiple staff members not assigned to our table coming up and asking us about drinks and ordering food, we had someone come with our appetizer that we had already received, servers pacing around the restaurant, and long waits in between receiving the bill and actually paying. At times it felt like they were very attentive but at other times it was like I was invisible. Restaurant wasn't really busy, outdoor seating was empty and indoor seating wasn't too full either, I'm hoping I just came on a bad day. Service wasn't horrible, just a bit concerning and food was good enough that it made up for the shaky hospitality. Would give it a second chance, can't stop thinking about the quick-fried brussels sprouts!
This is a great place for tasty food and watching sports matches. Big screens, delicious burgers, wings, and salads. Good selection of drinks and friendly staff. Perfect for evenings with friends.
Very delicious tuna salad and a lobster roll. Highly recommend 👌
Went there for friend’s birthday party and had such a great dinner. Every dish was elegantly placed and the flavors were so unique and detailed. Amazing new place in the neighborhood!

A new spot in town and we try their lunch.
The food was well presented and service was great. Considering the price point to quality, the food was not exceptional and just decent at best. Food is the most important part of the experience and it failed to hit the mark. Also there was only one option for lunch which surprised us.

I am all for more upgraded, modernized, and sophisticated Korean restaurants, and this is one of them that’s not too fussy or ultra expensive.
Atmosphere: This place is so clean and elegant. Someone really put much thought into it. Pretty table settings and plates, bowls, even the chopstick rests! Nice lighting, nice bathroom..and even the fish they bring your bill in is pretty.
Menu: not your typical Korean bibimbap and other array of typical dishes. Small dishes (“Korean tapas”) include some items that you probably don’t see often in other Korean restaurants (such as grilled chicken gizzards, spicy pork feet, Yun ha Yuk, spicy crab meat, etc.) and a few sharable dishes including simmered beef rib. The portions are small, but the price point is not too high. I’d definitely order a few and share with friends.

Food: I really liked the side dishes. Yes, they do charge $1.5 for additional side dishes, but these are much better than the typical ones you get at other Korean places. (I recently went to another Korean place not too far from here, and I didn’t even touch some of the dishes/ it was expensive and not satisfying.) Spicy potato salad was my favorite and the stewed pork was also good. And their kimchi was served in a manner that I’ve not seen in Korean restaurants in the states for a while- cut fresh, in an elegant manner! It was on a very ripe side, but it was delicious.
The “dduk galbi” was a little sweet and lot a lot of meat.($25). But it was done in a careful way and the presentation was nice. The meat quality was also nice. Him so ($5) was good. They also give you a slice of it as an appetizer. They also give you a sweet cinnamon welcome drink.

Service: very attentive and friendly.

Overall, I enjoyed my food and my time there. It’s more thoughtful, elegant, and refined than a lot of other Korean places. The only thing is that the rice isn’t included in the dishes.($3 extra).

I’d definitely visit again.

The staff gave us such a warm welcome, the prices were reasonable, and the elegant atmosphere made for a perfect dining experience. I especially loved the kalbi jjim, and watching the kimbap being freshly prepared right in front of us was a unique and memorable experience.

I recently visited a newly opened Korean restaurant and had a fantastic experience. I ordered the bulgogi combo, which was perfectly seasoned and tender (a blend of savory and sweet flavors). The side dishes tasted fresh. The servers were friendly and created a warm and welcoming atmosphere.

What stood out most to me was the makguksu (buckwheat noodles). It was a nostalgic treat that immediately reminded me of 할머니 손맛 (grandma’s cooking) back in Korea. The noodles were refreshing (with a rich sauce that transported me right back to childhood family meals). Overall, this restaurant delivers authentic Korean comfort food with great service, and I’ll definitely come back!

We went to Miraku for our anniversary. We enjoyed the laid back atmosphere and friendly service. We ordered the Zangi fried chicken to share and it was tasty without being greasy. The roasted sesame miso ramen was very authentic and reminded me of ramens in Japan. The staff offered us the Hojicha chiffon cake on the house for desserst, which we were very thankful for. Overall, it is a place that we will return frequently and enjoy every meal with friend and family.

Miraku Boston, the new ramen place—I had to check it out and make sure I tried their ramen. What did I like the most? Definitely the Zing Fried Chicken, which deserves 5 stars. It's my favorite dish at this restaurant. We ordered all the ramen they offer: Yaki Shoyu Ramen, Roasted Sesame Miso Ramen, and Spicy Miso Ramen. Here's how I rate them: Yaki Shoyu Ramen > Spicy Miso Ramen > Roasted Sesame Miso Ramen. I think the Yaki Shoyu is the best of the three options. Personally, I’m not a fan of really thick and soft ramen noodles, so this place may not become my new favorite. All three soups were also a bit too salty for me, and I couldn't finish the broth.

On the service side, everything was great—super pleasant, attentive, and customer-focused. If I go back, I’ll definitely order the Zing Fried Chicken again. As for the ramen, I’ll have to think it over, but I’d probably stick with the Yaki Shoyu Ramen.

The yaki shoyu ramen was so insanely good! I loved the noodle soup. Went on a pretty rainy day and the line was way out the door, so clearly speaks to how amazing the place is! Our food was a little delayed apparently (we only waited 15 minutes for it), but they gave us a free fried chicken for that, which was so nice! They also handed out little ramen stickers and pins, which was adorable and a nice touch :)

It's a lovely location for one. Nice, quiet and elegant. The location is walkable from the Green line. The service was excellent, the ramen is excellent like it was during their pop-up with the Kombu providing a lovely flavor that can't be found anywhere. My only wish is that the bowls were bigger. This place is here to stay and I don't think you can go wrong eating their ramen. Try the fried chicken with the sauce, it's a hit.

Woah! This new and upcoming ramen spot hit the spot on the first try. Service was amazing. The broth was so simple, but flavorful. Good spot for yourself, a couple, or a group of people. Check it out before word gets out and it gets even busier.

Saw a picture of Tangsu yuk and had to try it. Tried few other dishes and they were authentic with flavors on point, but somewhat lacking ..
Pork tangsu yuk $28 came with tangsu sauce poured over already, but quickly became dry and very hard, perhaps too much starch in their batter. Tangsu sauce was good.
Jjajang myeon $14 Jjajang sauce flavor was good but again drier than typical jjajang sauce and left noodles not moist even after sauce was mixed in.
Tteok bokki $14 Thoroughly enjoyed! Full flavor and just right amount of spicy kick.
Seating was like the wood church pew chairs, hard as rock , so uncomfortable.
Vibe seemed perfect for solo diners to come and enjoy comfort foods.

Compared to other many other Korean restaurants (in the US and Korea) the beef bulgogi was ok/pretty average; not too special but pretty tender. The portion was also very large. However the chicken bibimbap was bland and flavorless. The chicken was boiled, dry snd unseasoned, just like the rice. There was no sesame oil on the egg, rice, or vegetables, which is a staple in bibimbap.

Ttukbaegi bulgogi soup was flavorful and had a good assortment of vegetables, noodles and rice cakes (over cooked, but may be due to takeout). The mul nangmyeon was very watery. Even if the ice in the soup melted because we got takeout, it was watery to a point where there was almost no flavor (regardless, the ice should have been made out of soup rather than water). The only source of flavor came from the vegetable toppings  (cucumber and radish).

The banchan (side dishes) were very small and included pickled radish, kimchi, and boiled broccoli. The rice was very stale and resembled cheap takeout rice rather than the type of rice typically served in Korean restaurants.

Overall, the soup and beef were pretty good, the nangmyeon was bland (may be due to takeout) and the bibimbap was bland. 2.5/5

Delicious Korean Food at Bap!

I recently tried Bap, and it was fantastic! The jjajangmyeon (black bean noodles) was so tasty, and the fried chicken was crispy and flavorful. But the scallion kimchi pancakes were the real highlight - super crispy and packed with flavor. The staff was friendly and made the experience even better. If you're looking for great Korean food, Bap is the place to go!

Came by for brunch today, and the food was delicious. I had the kimchi jigae, and the soup was very flavorful and not too spicy and/or salty. The perfect combination of everything inside the kimchi jigae. The seafood pancake could be a tad more crispy, as it was slightly soggy. The japchae was good, and the mandu 🥟 was good. Overall, I'll come back to try other food.

Good was very good and felt very authentic. High quality. Loved the tteokboki with cheese and the grilled mackerel. Make sure you get the hot stone bibimbap and not the regular. Ours had too much rice and not enough protein.

ChIJ99tZ9Ax644kRF96OnpZdQY8.name: Fairmont Copley Plaza Boston
ChIJ99tZ9Ax644kRF96OnpZdQY8.address: 138 St James Ave, Boston, MA 02116, USA

reviews.text:
Huge spacious room with great firm beds. Lots of space to walk around. Although a very old property, only the doors show their age. Our door was a little stuck and we mentioned it to the front desk in the morning. When we came back from brunch it was fixed. Excellent responsive service.

Every morning we were greeted by smiling faces. A huge plus for us.

The bathroom was a little dated but luxurious. I wished there was more space on the countertop for the toiletries. The shower stall was bright and clean. The shampoo, soap and conditioner were filled and dispensers worked. I highlight this point because it has been quite a frequent problem with many hotels.

Would stay here again on the next trip to Boston. Location was great too. Very short walking distance from the Back Bay station and the Prudential shopping mall.

The building and main area are beautiful, the room was acceptable, the restaurant food was really good and the restaurant staff were friendly like maybe it has separate management.

I have to be honest. My wife has speech challenges with PPA. We came through the hotel with a tour group, and the first night and last night were here at this beautiful hotel.

The first night was a welcome party, and the wait staff was very rude towards my wife because of her speech problems. I had a conversation with the staff member, and that was a waste because the gentleman refused to apologize even when the whole table witnessed.

On our way back through, we checked in, and it was the same rudeness with the front desk.

I would never recommend this place. Rudeness from service people is unacceptable for any price, and at 400 a night, you expect a level of service that this place just doesn't offer.

Never again.

Edit Sept 7 2024 - no one ever contacted me.

DO NOT STAY HERE!! I usually don’t make reviews but the state of this hotel has caused me to make a review for the first time. Unfortunately the only good things about here are the service, lobby and location. The rooms are very worn down and old. They did give me a complementary upgrade but based on the state of the rooms they probably do it a lot. It is sad and unfortunate that this hotel is considered a 4 star hotel and part of the Fairmont brand.

This hotel is TIRED. Lobby is beautiful, but the rooms are drab and smell a bit moldy.  Rooms need updating for simple things like easily accessible bedside outlets. Also, there was barely any room to put toiletries in the bathroom as my bathroom had a small pedestal sink. The hotel is very large so your room could be quite far from the elevators.

Poor Customer Service.

I am writing this review to formally express my dissatisfaction with my ongoing stay at this hotel. I have been staying here for 3 nights, and unfortunately, I have encountered an issue that has made my stayvery uncomfortable. The room I am currently staying in has a strong smell of cigarettes, which I find unacceptable, especially in a non-smoking hotel environment. I addressed this issue with the receptionist, kindly explaining that I have been staying for three nights and that I cannot tolerate the condition any longer.

Additionally, I have reserved three other rooms for my company members, and I would expect that, as a loyal customer, my concerns would be taken seriously. However, the receptionist has not provided a satisfactory resolution. Instead, I was informed that I would have to keep my luggage outside of the room for approximately five hours until a different room becomes available and she was objecting and making derogatory personal opinions about me. This lack of urgency and consideration has left me deeply unsatisfied.

I would like to express my extreme disappointment with both the condition of the room and the poor service I have received from the front desk staff, particularly the receptionist in question. This experience does not meet the standard I expected from your hotel, and I believe it needs immediate attention.

I kindly request that you address this issue promptly and provide a suitable resolution for my discomfort or I will be forced to leave. I also expect a formal response regarding the service and I hope the owner of this hotel will take customer service seriously going forwards.

Must truly compliment the amazing staff and service- there are many good restaurants in Boston- the service here is the best I’ve seen in a long time. The food was better than anticipated- of all the places I’ve dined in Boston now, this is where I’ll want to return to first. It is deservedly busy/noisy- but it’s a good energy.

A very nice location and setting.  However, that was about the only wow factor.  Our party of 5 all agreed on the experience.  The French Onion Soup was mediocre at best and required a hard stir to get flavor off the bottom.  The calamari were cooked nicely but had very little seasoning and the marinara was bland.  Those of us that had steaks all agreed, they were very salty and all three came out at the same temp even though we ask for one to be medium rare plus.  I guess the plus was hard to achieve.  We ended with a very nice coconut cake and espresso martinis.  The cakeI would definitely recommend.

Great service and delicious food. The French Onion was good. Not the best I've had, but it was very good. The A5 Top Serlion was the best A5 we've had, according to my wife.  We paired it with a lobster tail that tasted just like you expect a lobster tail to taste. But frankly could have been presented better. The creamed spinach was absolutely fantastic! Conner was our server and he was Great!

My wife and I had a splendid meal to celebrate our sixth wedding anniversary. I had been to Grill 23 once over fifteen years ago and remembered their dry aged New York strip to be the best steak I'd ever had, and it still has not been topped for me. Portions were much larger than other fine dining establishments and we left feeling like we'd just had a Thanksgiving meal! The creme brulee topped off a magical dining experience, with a thin dish to maximize the caramelized topping and a lovely addition of fresh fruits and a wafer cookie. Not the kind of place we could afford on the regular, but for times when you've got to pull out all the stops it's the best in the city.

Expected a bit more from a high end steak house.  Ribeye was good but have enjoyed better.  The lobster bisque could have had a bit more flavor but the large pieces of lobster didn't hurt.  While the warm baked chocolate chip cookies were $14...they were worth it!!  Service was fantastic!  Tables are tight but that's understandable.  Very good experience.

I can’t believe I haven’t written a review for this place yet. I’ve been several times so I will upload pictures from all of my visits. This is such a magical place. It feels like being transported to a 1930’s jazz club, drinking drinks you shouldn’t and listening to music that moves you. It is such a beautiful experience you can’t find anywhere else. The food has been phenomenal for us every time and the entertainment is just unreal. The service is minimal but in an appreciate way. They check in regularly and notice when you need new drinks but don’t hover and a manager has always checked in to see how our experience is going. The service makes sense for the atmosphere. It feels like the food and entertainment are the focal point and the service is there to support those things without getting in the way. I don’t know I just really love this place and wish I lived closer so I could come more often.

This is like a local pub but so much more character, an amazing, large space. The bartenders are friendly and creative, especially Angela. Made us a dessert martini that tasted like tiramisu. The food is transcendent. We had the cauliflower app and lamb gnocchi. Music is great. Not too loud. This place has character and charm. I'm a new regular.

I have dined here several times with my family and friends. The jazz music is always excellent, and we have a great time. The atmosphere is wonderful too. The food is alright but not particularly memorable. However, the service is not great. The waiters seem to be a bit aloof and are not knowledgeable about the menu, and the prices are a bit too high for the mediocre quality of the food. They seem to have very few grain-free options. We came here today for brunch and had a pleasant meal listening to an amazing jazz set. We ordered a frittata, some cocktails, and a slice of cheesecake. They did not have any to-go cups for my son to take apple juice with him. It can also be quite difficult to find parking anywhere nearby.

Highly recommend popping in for a weekend brunch at this spot. They've got a live band playing, which sets a fantastic, relaxed vibe, and the staff are super chill, adding to the laid-back weekend feel. The food is decent; I usually go for the eggs Benedict, but I decided to switch it up this time, and I wasn't disappointed.

Also, don't skip the coffee cake—it might sound a bit odd to have dessert as an appetizer, but trust me, it really works here. And of course, you can't go wrong with ordering a Bloody Mary to round off the perfect brunch experience. Great atmosphere, good food, and lively music make for an enjoyable weekend outing.

Great atmosphere, live music and ambience.
Their tuna ceviche and mushroom risotto was amazing, the cheeseburger was only ok. The waitress was friendly and super accommodating.
The band was spot on! Overall it was a good time.

Amazing, amazing time! Went here with a large party and did the family style meal. Reservations were easy to make. The service was great; our server was friendly and knowledgeable about the menu. We met the owner/manager (unsure which) and he was so nice. We had a shellfish allergy and they assured us there would be no cross contamination. The food was so good, it was easy to eat the large portions provided. Would definitely go again.

Absolutely delicious authentic Italian!!! The restaurant itself is gorgeous!! Lots of space! Private party rooms available too. The charcuterie board starter was sooooo good. I could have just eaten that 🤣 This was our first time, but we will be back!

Went to Maggiano's for dinner after my boyfriend proposed! Patrick was our server and he went out of his way to make sure that our dinner was memorable! Patrick honestly made this experience a 10/10! Portions are very big and worth the price. Would definitely dine here again and ask for Patrick! You can tell her actually enjoys what he does and cares about the guests and wants to make their dining experience a good one!

I have been coming to Maggiano’s since I was a little kid and will continue to do so but I wanted to leave a review of honest constructive feedback. (This review is not intended to be “ill mannered or disrespectful)
Pros of the night-
Friendly greeting of host and manager
Atmosphere
The ribeye
Lobster tail
Chopped salad

Cons-
No greeting at table or welcome from the waiter (I’m old school, I enjoy when the waiter or waitress introduce themselves)
Not asking for preference of water and just assuming I wanted tap which I did not.
Waiting 10 minutes for my beer
Receiving my clam chowder luke warm borderline cold after the waiter went into the kitchen 3 times to check the soup of the day because he did not know.
My waiter forgetting my salad and had to ask for it 30 minutes later.
Removing the water bottle when it was still half full.
Packing my appetizers left overs to go at the table.
Serving main courses while table is still messy from apps with food and dirty dishes on the table.

I understand the restaurant business is hard and has high turnover BUT it is so disappointing that a place like Maggiano’s that has great food, very very reasonable prices, large portions, beautiful atmosphere/ large space - seems to (I say “seem” because I don’t want to be too assumptive) Not focus on training their staff on proper steps of service better. Last night I pity tipped 20% because the waiter and manager were kind and respectful about my concerns about the evening but I honestly wanted to tip 10% (I did not).

Overall experience was a 6/10

The mushroom ravioli is fantastic and one of a kind, with a rich and complex mushroom flavor. Otherwise the food is just decent relative to the prices, making it a pretty typical fine dining style American Italian restaurant.

Great dishes: mushroom ravioli, tiramisu

Alright dishes: The calamari and the chef's special truffle lobster carbonara were alright.

Other notes: Our server was helpful, and their $6 take out entree does seem like great value.

Would I come here again, or recommend a friend here? No, not for the price.

Had a great brunch outside recently and it was flawless. Great vibes, great food, amazing service.

Would highly recommend. Food is top notch, great quality, with amazing portion sizes.

It's in the heart of Newbury in the best location and very easy to get to (very walkable).

Definitely make a reservation, too. It can get pretty busy given how popular Newbury is.

Stephanie’s on Newbury is a wonderful spot for casual yet upscale dining, offering classic American comfort food with a twist. It has a cozy and stylish atmosphere, perfect for brunch, lunch, or dinner. Their menu is diverse. The outdoor seating is a great option during warmer months, allowing you to enjoy the lively Newbury Street vibe. It’s an excellent place for both locals and visitors to relax and enjoy a good meal in the heart of Boston.

Food was OK at best. We came at a very busy time (breakfast on a weekend) but was able to get a table for 4 outdoors with no wait time. Price was decent. Waiter was fine up until she did not accept our tip bc it wasn’t enough. I definitely took my tip money back with no hesitation.

Tried this place out while on Newbury this Tuesday. Was pleased with our experience, pitcher of water for table at no request which is always pleasant. Service wasnt insanely fast but  we were seated outside with only 1 other table and it was a bit after lunch so we were unbothered.

Food was great, apps were pricey but the meals were great portions and not obnoxiously expensive.

Will definitely swing by the one in Terminal E the next time I fly internationally! I have never used my Chase Sapphire Credit their yet and now im alittle bummed

We had a great meal here and Sophie (Sophia?) was an excellent server. The wagyu hot dog was giant and delicious. The wedge salad was huge and delicious, the sirloin(?) with it was mid, should probably be tenderloin tips or a higher grade meat than it was

Overall I thought the food was very salty.  It wasn’t bad but I’ve had better.  We drank like 2-3 bottles of water because of this.

The atmosphere is nice and our waiter was fantastic.

I was hoping the clam chowder would be better since is was supposedly rated one of the best but I guess everyone has different tastes

Would I go back ?  Maybe maybe not since I feel there are so many other good restaurants.

Went there with my wife and son and a friend. We ordered a salad, fried calamari and a lobster bisque for starters and 2 orders of sole and 2 orders of steamed lobster with broccoli and Asparagus as sides. The bisque was very good, the calamari and salad were OK. The sole was excellent but I have had better lobster. The service was slowish and the place was super full. Worth the experience for one time.

So worth the drive from NH! We came here on a Saturday lunch reservation but ran terribly late due to traffic (barely 3 miles away!) and then 25 minutes of musical chairs underground the Boston Commons. Despite all of that and more, the hostess Marianna was very understanding and found us a small booth 🙏 her kindness began our 1st experience at the Atlantic Fish Company.

André was our server. His attentive service and energetic candor made for a spectacular evening! I especially appreciated his detailed knowledge of the food ingredients and impeccable timing on checking up on our table. Our water glasses and prosecco were never empty or waiting.

We ordered 2 appetizers; the tuna tartare and crispy calamari Milano. The tartare was my favorite, very subtle, and soft flavor of horseradish and wasabi. My partner enjoyed the extremely light batter of the calamari; the hot peppers add a nice zing!

For entrees, we had the Halibut with spinach & mushrooms, and the Chilean Sea bass. The sea bass had the fish taste I was craving for! The Halibut was cooked to perfection and is a hefty portion, I couldn't finish it. Speaking of which, the 2 sides are VERY generous portions as well. My taste buds say YES, but my stomach capacity pleaded Nooo.

However, there is always room for dessert; we had cappucinos with the Special of the Day Bread Pudding, and a creme brulee. The bread pudding comes with vanilla ice cream, tasted like an autumn pie ☺️ and I loved how fresh the fat blueberries were on top of the smooth creme brulee!

The only disappointment was the limoncello; theirs was a creamy type instead of it being light and bright.

Side note: The inner front door is in dire need of lubrication... that shrieking squeaking dissonance absolutely ruins the atmosphere. It seemed frivolous at first, but upon talking to the Manager (turquoise tie), he apologized and acknowledged the issue. I appreciated his temporary solution of keeping the door open. With the popularity and value of this establishment, I would hope that the Owner resolves that with the proper tools ASAP. I was tempted to pick up a silicone WD40 and apply it for them good grief.

Unexpectedly pleased! We were in town for a conference and decided to walk to find food. I was tired of walking so we decided to stop for a drink.

The restaurant is beautiful! The hostess was very helpful and we took a seat at the bar. Our drinks were delicious so we decided to order some food.

We shared an appetizer and entree which they divided up for us. Our total was $109 so this place is not for those on a tight budget. Technically, we paid for one meal and 2 drinks so you can easily spend hundreds here. The food was exceptional!

The bathroom was clean. This is always important to me. Plenty of space in the stalls and a foot handle on the door.

The bartenders and wait staff were very accommodating. I am happy to have found this place and would certainly recommend it for a date night or hanging out with friends.

No doubt the best clam chowder in Boston. I’ll be back time and time again to eat it. The beet salad is large and perfectly balanced with a big hunk of fried goat cheese. The bread basket is very generous and actually great bread. 10/10 all around!

We went here for some casual eats on our first night in Boston. The service was great and everyone was friendly. I recommend the espresso martini! It was perfection! I had the clam chowder, which was amazing and a side salad. The ranch dressing was terrible but the salad itself was large and very fresh. My son enjoyed the turkey BLT and the truffle fries were to die for! We also had a steak sandwich with very crispy and delicious onion rings. They have some outdoor dining but it was raining that day.

I had a good experience at Back Bay Social in Boston. The waiter, whose name was either David or Daniel, was extremely nice and polite. The wings were very crisp and fresh, and the salad was good. However, the quinoa salad was plain and flavorless. The prices are on the expensive side.
It was very nice atmosphere but the food was so-so. Nice young crowd. Great for families. Price is reasonable. The salads were good, the clam chowders not. The pizza was ok.

Decent food and great location being right across from prudential.

The vodka sauce pasta is good, as are the burgers.  Our staff was helpful and the ambiance was nice, had a dj going downstairs even though there werent many people down there.

They ID ofc but if you are going for dinner time you can go in just to get food

Had an awesome time here on a Wednesday night in June visiting from Australia! Enjoyed the cauliflower bites with nice friendly service. Went downstairs afterwards and experienced Celtics winning Game 3 on the big screen with some drinks and pizza. Nice atmosphere and plenty of room and comfortable vibes. Thank you!

ChIJq6fQJ3R644kRMUtn9lkTzOw.name: Legal Sea Foods - Park Square
ChIJq6fQJ3R644kRMUtn9lkTzOw.address: 79 Park Plaza at The Heritage on the Garden, Boston, MA 02116, USA

reviews.text:
We are from out of town and met some friends here for a catch up dinner. The service was a bit slow, which was concerning because we had tickets for the theater and it became a little bit stressful. It was a little surprising that they couldn’t get our food out more quickly because it was an early dinner and there were very few tables occupied.

Having said that, everybody seemed to enjoy their food. This is a small chain that I understand was recently acquired by a private equity firm. Usually private equity investors are focused on cutting expenses, and that could explain why there was not enough staff to effectively operate the restaurant.  Our server was quite pleasant and she was trying hard. We ate indoors because it was a little bit warm outside and we had a comfortable booth toward the back, which was quiet and good for our conversation. I think in Boston, you probably have a lot of superior options for seafood, but this was close to our theater and it fit the bill.

This restaurant legitimately had some of the worst service I've ever received. I'm from down south and any Waffle House would have better service than this place.

Service was extremely slow, and our whole table ordered clam chowders which only came out after we got our entrees, which took nearly an hour. Our waiter seemed to have just forgotten about us considering we had to ask about where our food and drinks were before they brought them out? The waiter also gave our entrees out to the wrong people, and deflected blame for it onto us after we started giving our entries to who actually ordered them instead of just not saying anything
Another amazing facet of service was I finished my water cup at the beginning of the meal after we ordered, and the only time my water was refilled was at the end of the meal after we were already done eating. Only 2/6 of people even got that water refill at the end too, and the waiter was basically sloshing the water out of my cup too?

The food we ordered was alright, but I doubt it is worth it compared to literally anywhere else that sells the same stuff with the level of service that we received.

A visit to Legal Sea Foods is almost mandatory whenever we visit the Boston area. They never disappoint, and our latest visit was even better than most for two reasons. First, they had a special promotion on a steamed lobster dinner (oh yeah!). Plus, the service and suggestions from our server Martin made this visit exceptional. Get the Boston Cream Pie for dessert!! Thank you Martin, and great job Legal Sea Foods!

This review is only for the server Oumaia (I hope I’m spelling his name correct),one of the most humble human I’ve met today, he really notched our experience at this restaurant. He was warm and courteous to all our additional request.I even spilled water by mistake and he didn’t make me feel embarrassed and was smiling throughout and was empathetic. Talking about food I ordered the lobster roll, which lacked flavor and was mediocre and pricey however the service provided compensated it.

Brought my friend here for the first time to try the chain while in Boston, with the impression that this was a popular and well-credited establishment. The appetizers we ordered were not good at all (tuna nachos in particular were horrible), and the drinks weren’t good either. The reason we came in the first place was for the lobster mac and cheese, but the server completely forgot about it. We didn’t care to remind her because the appetizers were extremely sub par and not worth the price at all. I would highly recommend finding another place to dine. This chain has gone downhill over the years, and are there are numerous other great seafood restaurants in the area that will be much more worth your time and money.

Stopped in for a quick lunch while visiting Boston. Healthy  salad and pasta options, enjoyed the baked wings. Reasonably prices, fresh/quality ingredients, great proportions for the cost. Great summer salad, not a huge fan of the cheese but that's just personal preference. Also tried the vanilla ice cream, highly recommend the ice cream. Would visit again for sure.

I recently visited Picco in the West End while in town for a business conference, and it was a phenomenal experience. This place serves some of the best pizza on this side of Boston, and the service was impressively quick. Our server was attentive and on top of everything. From our table, we could see the pizza oven and watch the chefs make everything from scratch, which added to the wonderful atmosphere. The combination of great food, efficient service, and a vibrant setting makes Picco a must-visit. I'll definitely be coming back again.

We are visiting from out of town and decided to try Picco for dinner as Take out. We're staying within walking distance and it sounded good.  We ordered a Small pizza with chicken,  onions,  olives,  sauce and fresh Mozzarella cheese.  We also got a salad with Boston lettuce, Apples, walnuts, bacon and gouda cheese with Lemon poppyseed dressing. Everything was hot fresh and delicious.  Highly recommend this place.

Looked up best pizza in Boston & this place was on the list. Since it was close to work, I went for a quick bite.
It was just after 6 on a Saturday, so busy, yet not crowded. I was able to grab a seat at the bar without delay.
I chose the burrata and meatball appetizers. HAVE MERCY!!!! The strawberry rhubarb jam was such a burst of brightness in my mouth. The crunch of pistachios made a great change in texture. The biscuits are adorable, open faced, grilled biscuits (that are incredible). The meatballs are what you would expect at a fave pizza spot. Plenty of flavor, just enough sauce... mmmm.
I placed a to go order for pizza. Half pepperoni and half sausage/fennel/ ricotta. Heated a slice of each the next day for lunch. Now I see why Picco is on the best pizza list in Boston. Even reheated leftover is delicious.
It's located in a prime area on Tremont St, so don't expect street parking. There is a public parking garage you drive into from the back of building, but walk out on the front (conveniently at the door for Picco).
They have a nice ice cream selection that I passed on. However, I saw plenty of people ordering dessert.

I was craving pizza and what better place than Boston to satisfy my hunger? Picco popped up on my search for gluten-free pizza, so we decided to give it a go. Atmosphere was lively, our server was fun to banter with and the food was fantastic. Picco also makes ice cream and sorbet in-house — dairy-free dark chocolate and raspberry sorbet made a super combination to top off the meal. Wish the place stayed open later. Note to our server: I should have ordered that second pizza!

Drinks and bartenders were fantastic! Didn’t eat food here but the decor was beautiful and loved the vibe. Sort of a dark and sexy speak easy type of place, with Latin music and artwork. Highly recommend, seems like a great date night spot or fun girls night out.

This was the first dinner spot on our trip to Boston. It was a great time and the waiter was friendly, professional and extremely courteous.  Everything was delicious and trust me we tried a lot of things off the menu.  A must have for sure is the street corn.  Omg you will LOVE it!

Dropped a point for service, a consequence of their high popularity as no one seemed interested in attending to us until we made a point of it...forgiven.
Food portion wise is at the lighter end but the quality is very high! Great flavours...
The atmosphere is without comparison, obviously relative to my own experience, but Lolita's have put impressive emphasis on their theme, and they've nailed it.
My Pork Nachitoes very very tasty.

We ate dinner here last Saturday night.  The weather was nice and we ate outside.  The waitress described it as a tapas bar but I don’t think that was correct.  We did order food to share based on her recommendation.  The food tasted great but some of the portions were very small.  For example, the street tacos were orders of two tacos.  Almost $20 for two small tacos seemed a bit pricey.

The atmosphere outside was fine but after I walked through the restaurant to use the bathroom.  The inside was pretty cool.
The food tasted really good. The theme of the restaurant is also different and interesting.  Everything is black themed. The crispy fish sandwich was delicious and will definitely order again.

ChIJz-Zu_Q1644kR3B-r8ffJeF0.name: The Cheesecake Factory
ChIJz-Zu_Q1644kR3B-r8ffJeF0.address: 115 Huntington Ave Suite 181, Boston, MA 02199, USA

reviews.text:
LOVE LOVE LOVE
Fav Place in the US. The Boston restaurant is such a feast for the eyes, beautiful inside. The food was amazing! The cakes are scrumptious and full of flavours - love the Fall range.
Our server Jairo deserves to be the Employee of the Month - he was absolutely attentive, proactive and very approachable.

Only feedback - we waited 30 minutes for a table. This despite at least 15 tables we saw visibly available.  We went to the bathrooms and could see so many available spots. The front desk hosts were so laid-back with no sense of urgency or care to have people seated.  This would deter us but after all it's the Cheesecake Factory!

Everything you would expect from the CF. Ordered a salad, pot stickers and Nachos for starters and burger, jamkaicanpepper shrimp (with chicken) and tacos for mains... We were stuffed and could not order dessert... Good food

Randy, our waiter was tremendously disappointing. After a day with my 2 granddaughters & daughter, we looked forward to a good meal. Once we were seated, we waited 15 minutes to get our drink order & another 5 for menus.   Two attractive ladies arrived were seated, and you can imagine how irritated I was that Randy went to their table first to take their order. He was engaged in some very long personal conversation as I saw him looking at pictures on one lady's cellphone.   There is nothing worse than good food with bad service.

I’ve had a few meals at this Cheesecake Factory, and while the food doesn’t taste bad, it’s not good for you—a 2000-calorie salad? That’s concerning, and the rest of the menu isn’t much better. The restaurant itself is huge and cute, making it an enjoyable place to visit. It’s worth trying once for the experience, but I wouldn’t recommend dining here regularly.

Excellent experience 👏, the staff was very friendly and quick on their feet.
Very nice atmosphere, and the menu is impressive! The food was tasty and well presented. The strawberry cheesecake was magic 🎩 ✨️

Really phenomenal dinner.  The host was wonderful even though one of the party members was quite delayed.  The waiter made everything so smooth. He was the highest of professionals.  So calm just making sure the meal was perfect.

Ordered the bacon wrapped squash as an appetizer and it was phenomenal.  The mustard sauce was the perfect wrapper.  I'd order it again.

For the main I went with Veal Diane au gratin potatoes and brussel sprouts.  Absolutely perfectly prepared and seasoned.   A spectacular success.

No room for dessert but I'm sure it would have been a bow on the experience.

If I had to have any complaints I'd say that the som being busy could be it but it wasn't a game changer.  Also was a bit loud for business conversation but it's a Friday night I really shouldn't complain.

Valet was a bit disorganized but also not that big of a deal.

Went there with my wife and son for lunch. Ordered ceaser salad to start and 2 orders of usda prime striploin and a chicken club sandwich. The steak was cooked perfectly and seasoned well and the sandwich was also excellent.... Loved it. I will go there again.

Timeless, classic, elegant. They take their wine and their steaks very seriously without feeling stuffy. Very nice wine by the glass list and a prime ribeye that will make you cry tears of joy. Anyways an excellent choice to grab lunch at the bar or bring out of town guests to impress.

We had a table for 6 and it was close to the sofa seats, the waiters basically walking right behind me and my husband, and bumped into us quite often.
One of the water glasses has a chip, my boneless ribeye had a piece of bone in (not sure if it is a common thing), but for the price I was expecting a better service.
Cocktails are fine, but steaks and sides are good, the desserts are the best.

Absolutely phenomenal! Hands down, one of my favorite restaurants. Even though it is classified as a steakhouse, they have some amazing seafood dishes as well. My favorites being the lobster club and the jumbo crab meat cocktail. Great quality, fresh, nicely seasoned food. The service is always great as well. You won't regret it!

I had an incredible dining experience at Davio's! The ambiance was warm and inviting, making it the perfect place for a special evening out. The menu offered a wide variety of delicious options, and every dish we tried was perfectly cooked and full of flavor.

A special thank you to our server, Daniel, who truly made our night exceptional. He was attentive, knowledgeable, and made great recommendations throughout the evening. His friendly and professional service really added to the overall experience.

I highly recommend Davio’s for anyone looking for an outstanding meal with top-notch service. We’ll definitely be returning!

I recently dined at Davio's Northern Italian Steakhouse in Boston with my family, and while the food was decent, the experience overall was quite enjoyable. The restaurant offers a nice blend of Northern Italian cuisine with American steakhouse staples, though nothing really stood out on the menu.

What made the visit special was how accommodating they were with kids. The staff was friendly and attentive, making it a relaxed dining experience for the whole family. The atmosphere was upscale yet welcoming, and they provided options that were kid-friendly, which is always appreciated.

Overall, it's a great place for a family dinner in a nice setting, especially if you're dining with little ones.
