This restaurant is on Newbury St in Boston, so there is only street parking available, and there is free street parking after 8 pm, and on Sundays.

ChIJz5lekXR644kRd_eEcvbMeN0.name: Bacco's Fine Foods
ChIJz5lekXR644kRd_eEcvbMeN0.address: 31 St James Ave, Boston, MA 02116, USA

reviews.text: I was treated badly. It was my firs time there. I went to buy a couple of food items. I tried ordering a Mediterranean style sandwich in the menu and the guy who works there preparing the sandwiches insulted me for no reason. I could not believe it. Never have been treated that way. If he was having a bad day, he should have stayed at home. Why would I want to keep spending money there? If I could give it 10 negative stars, I would. I'm not going back there as long as the rude sandwich guy works there. If you happen to visit there, remind the rude sandwich guy to treat his customers better.

This place is phenomenal. Exceptional selection, and really fantastic tastings every weeknight of interesting wines, beers paired with cheeses / dips. Super friendly and knowledgeable staff (ask for Hugh) - never snobby even though they really should be given the quality of their selection. Go-to neighborhood spot when we want the perfect bottle or two for a Friday evening. 6 stars.

The staff is friendly and the deli person prepared a most excellent wrap.The Bob ganooch was fresh , flavorful and stuffed to just the right size.
An all around good visit!

Outstanding Sandwiches. Went every day of the convention, Sometimes multiple times a day. Sandwiches great value for cost, ingredients delicious and fresh, and so much variety. On top of that, fantastic selection of wines and cheeses and beers. A little lacking in the general grocery department, But I loved it Nonetheless. Will be back every single time I visit Boston, For sure!
Staff is always friendly, nice selection of gourmet cookies and crackers, as well as fruit.

First time here and will definitely be coming back. Loved the vibe of this place and the music and drinks were great. Waiter was cool and really explained the menu very well and tried some really great options. Had Apps, dinner and dessert and was so happy with all the items. It's a little pricey but the quality of the food you cannot beat. Will be recommending this place to family and friends to come on by and get some awesome food!

This is the second time coming here. Love the decor and atmosphere of the place. It is loud and energetic, so it may be hard to have a quiet conversation with someone. I got the Chicken Enchiladas with mole sauce; love the sauce! Very cool speak easy entrance to the restaurant and it's bigger than it looks at first glance when you walk down to the reception area.

This was a good experience. Nothing to really write home about. The chips, salsa and margaritas were all good. Our main courses were a bit bland. The portions were decent but definitely pricey for the quality of the dishes. I have definitely had better Mexican food and would probably only come back for a drink and appetizers. The service was good and our waiter was very friendly. Not a bad experience at all but it was really just in the middle of the road.

Honestly loved this place. The vibes are very cute and cozy. A great place to go for after work margaritas or with friends. The camarones al Diablo were SO good. Creamy, decadent, and filling. My friends pulled pork dish was also great. The passion margarita I had was perfect too. Service was efficient and attentive but not overly so. The only downside is I do think it’s a bit expensive. I’ll definitely be back though!

I'm not sure why Google lists this as $$ because it should be $$$, which you can tell just from the fancy atmosphere of the place when you go inside. It has a weird speakeasy feel at the beginning - like it's just this random door in a back alley and you have to go underground. But it really is a hidden gem. Obviously a bit pricey, but not too bad, and we all enjoyed our food a lot. Portions were perfect size for dinner. I was surprised it wasn't busier - we were one of the only tables in there.

Sweetgreen is one of my top places for a great salad. I always get the Kale Caesar, and it never disappoints. The service is fast, and the staff is consistently friendly. Definitely recommend for a quick, healthy meal.

Sweetgreen is always reliable for a fast and healthy lunch. They have bowls and salads to choose from, but you can also build your own. Ton of options for vegans and vegetarians. Outdoor and indoor seating. Space is a little tight and it was very busy during lunch time, but the staff were very fast and friendly.

I really liked that restaurant but now they have completely changed the staff and what they are now the truth is they don't know how to provide a good service. Unfortunately, that sweetgreen doesn't work. I don't recommend it

I’ve previously been to the seaport location, so I thought to give this place a try as well. Tight seating, but the interior was clean. Ordered the Ranchy chicken+rice kids meal since I wasn’t feeling too hungry. Unfortunately the rice was inedible because it was almost raw. Tiny pebbles in my mouth. Either a bad batch or inexperienced staff. The chicken was also a tad dry, but my girlfriend’s green goddess salad wasn’t too bad.
Amazing selection with lots of options for every diet including vegan, highly recommended!

Clean, airy lovely place with high ceilings that is very conveniently open early for morning commuters and office workers.

Matcha latte a little weak. Yogurt parfait is solid though!

Really nice friendly staff. Good pricing!

OMG The best homemade lemonade I've ever tasted! The perfect combination of sugar. Delicious desserts that are not super sugary. Delicious pies. If you, like me, are not a fan of high sugar content in desserts, so that it grips on your teeth, then this is exactly the place for you.

I ate the Avocado toast and my female friend ate the baked French Toast. The following day we ordered takeout and I had an opportunity to eat the baked French Toast.
On both occasions the food was tasty, however the dining experience at this establishment is expensive.

We’ve been to the Clarendon St location several times during our visit to the city and have all been impressed with the consistency of the food and service here. There are plenty of sweet and savory options for all tastes. The espresso drinks we had were delicious. Seating was aplenty both indoor and outdoor. A great alternative to Tatte when in Boston.
sooo delicious with casual vibes. they had a lot of sandwich and baked good choices. if you don’t have a big appetite, there’s even an option to just order half a sandwich.

Was lucky that hunger strikes earlier than usual dinner time, else i think i will be in the queue with the rest. So since arrival to Cheers was around 4ish to 5, managed to get a decent place to have a nice dinner. Service is definitely good.  Food is great. Atmosphere is superb.

My expectations were low but it was a great place to visit! The clam chowder and chilli were delicious! It was a bit crowded but they were fast and friendly. We ate upstairs and shopped the gift shop. The upstairs bathrooms are tiny but didn't bother me! What a great time to reminisce on the beloved show Cheers!

Total nostalgia! The bar set from the show is the upper level dining room. The lower level is the bar it was actually based on. Giftshop areas on both levels. We stopped in for drinks and appetizers & loved it. You check in downstairs so you get to walk those iconic steps (there is an elevator, I think, from the upper level). We were seated in the lower level, the service was excellent, and the food tasted great. We will definitely be back on our next visit to Boston.

I did not have high expectations because I just thought it would be a super long wait with only marginal food, but I was excited to ask experience the setting. I was wrong.... the burger was amazing! My husband had the clam chowder and said it was really good. We went around 3pm on a Sunday and there was only a short wait but it was well worth it. I'd recommend!

I wanted to take in something that just "said" Boston. So, why not Cheers! It was a unique little spot that was a bit tight in space but big in character. Staff and patrons alike were friendly and quite helpful. Service is slow and a bit unorganized when it comes to needing to order food, but the Bartender Dave did his best to keep up. He was awesome with the drinks, and that in itself kept him hopping.
The food was pretty good. We had the Quesadillas, Clam Chowder, and Sam's Turkey Sandwich. I even got to sit at Norm's corner seat! I was also able to snag a cute Christmas Ornament in the  cute little gift shop.

We had an amazing time! It was so delicious and a really cool experience…I’ve never been so full. Benjamin was an awesome server and we’d go back just for him. We told him we were visiting from Canada, and it was our first time there. He made sure we had extra special desserts, which I super appreciated. If we’re ever back in Boston, this is for sure where we’ll be going for dinner!

The service, food, and drinks at this establishment were exceptional. We dined here for two consecutive days, and both experiences were equally outstanding. Gabby, Coiah, Jennifer, and Dennis delivered top-notch customer service, ensuring all our needs were met. I previously believed this level of service was exclusive to the South, but these professionals proved me wrong. I will definitely return on my next visit.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Fogo de Chão in Boston, and the highlight of the evening was the outstanding service provided by Alexander Mateo. Alexander made us feel incredibly welcome with his warm character and attentiveness. He served us a variety of beef that we fell in love with at the first bite, including our chosen Wagyu beef, which truly exceeded our expectations. Alexander’s enthusiasm and commitment to excellence made the experience even more special. His genuine passion for what he does left a lasting impression on our family, and his marvelous service transformed an already fantastic meal into an unforgettable evening. Additionally our waiter Ariel, provided an excellent service through his efforts of being attentive without being intrusive and made sure every detail was perfect, from offering insightful recommendations to ensuring our glasses were never empty. Thank you, Alexander, and Thank you, Ariel, for making our night so memorable—we’ll definitely be back!

The steaks were great but could have been more soft and juicy. The lamb chops were delicious. The service is amazing as they kept bringing different types of meat constantly. Interestingly, we were told the meat is Halal.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Fogo de Chão Brazilian Steakhouse, and it was an outstanding experience! The manager, Coiah, was very attentive and ensured everything was perfect. Our waitress, Tatiana, provided excellent service, making sure we had everything we needed. Anibal, one of the servers, brought us a perfectly cooked steak at just the right temperature. The food was delicious, and the atmosphere was fantastic. I highly recommend this place for anyone looking for a great dining experience!

ChIJHbJ_wxZ644kRJM8ZX-deYYM.address: 563 Columbus Ave APT 2, Boston, MA 02118, USA

reviews.text: There is so much to learn about coffee. I just had a cup of coffee that blew me away! This Ethiopian pour over coffee tastes like Lipton tea. It tastes just like tea, not like coffee at all. WOW 5 Stars! Earned it!

Great espresso, great pour over, great atmosphere.
I found this place randomly and I loved it. Servers were very polite and I really enjoyed coffee and my time there. I will go back there for sure.
Render Coffee in South End, Boston, is a fantastic spot! The place is nice, with a clean restroom and a great selection of yummy food. Highly recommend for a casual coffee break.

Over my four years in boston, this coffee shop has remained my #1 out of all the ones I’ve tried. If you get there before 11 or on a less busy day, the atrium tables are the best study spot. Render’s coffee is great, and their breakfast sandwiches are my absolute favorites. The baristas are always super nice and efficient as well

Great little coffee shop! My pourover was great, and the vibe was real. I had heard that the atrium seats were highly coveted, and this proved to be true, as they were all taken. So get there early and enjoy it. I want to come back during warmer months and relax on the patio.

Wowwwwwwww im so impressed!!! The pizza crust was perfectly cooked and everything was so amazing!!!!
The board was delicious as well i was continually digging it.

The atmosphere is cozy and nice. Open kitchen concept so you get to see the doughs tossed around. They said they take Apple Pay but it failed when I tried to pay (like not even registering) so that was weird.

The food was awesome so will definitely be back for more! I highly recommend this place if you’re around the area
I loved the pizza we had in the Salty pig! The pizza tasted amazing. The amount of salt, crispy bread, cooked dressing and everything was fantastic.

TLDR: Chill little place with some fantastic food at an affordable price.

Ordered the polpette (meatballs) and the titular Salty Pig pizza. Both were absolutely delicious. Meatballs were nice and well salted, which made them even better with the slices of sourdough. The Salty Pig pizza was very savory with the various cuts of cured pork but also sweet from the caramel drizzle. Cannot recommend this place enough!

The total came out to $34, but it was definitely an amount to be shared. Left with half a pizza for tomorrow.
The food menu is exceptionally... short. With that, each dish I have tried (meatballs, pizza, and even just a plate of salad) were very tasty. And I loved their bread!!

I am genuinely surprised with how good the food is. You know one of those movies where someone becomes a chef because they wanna make people happy with food? I wanna say that this chef did it. We had the salty pig pizza, it tasted so good on every bite. And I’m not someone who usually leaves review

Perfect weekend brunch options. Tasty food and relaxing atmosphere. Accessible by public transit. Great location to take a walk before and after the meal in South End, surrounded by great architecture and greens. Server is a bit new
Best French cuisine we've had in Boston this far! Food delivered across the board - from escargot all the way to our creme brulee! Will definitely be back.

Our daughter chose Petit Robert to celebrate her Masters Graduation with a select group. We were early, so they sat us outside for lattes & a pastry basket, "just to stay in shape," as Eck would say.
We moved inside for our early afternoon meal, and the fun really started!
Our selected drinks were across the board - more lattes, wine, a mocktail, and black coffee. The Amande Douce was a delightful combo of orgeat [almond syrup], lemon juice, and orange juice.
A few of us shared the escargot, which were a treat, but maybe a tad over salted. The extra sauce was wonderful for bread dipping, while the brightness of the mocktail was a match for the hearty garlic.
Once again, we gave the menu a thorough workout as our selections ranged from a beautiful onion soup, French toast, mushroom crepes to both smoked salmon and prosciutto mortadella waffles.
We shared tastes and thoroughly enjoyed our selections! Several boxes were required to bring the delicious remains home to extend our gourmet feast to another day.
Unfortunately, we were much too full for even a glance at the amazing desserts. We observed a variety delivered to neighboring tables, but, alas, not this time.
Ahhhhh. Gastronomic Satisfaction.
Merci, Petit Robert!

Great food, but we ordered when we sat down and it took over 45 minutes to receive one quiche plate... No explanation given from our server. It also took 30 minutes to receive then process the check. Very very slow service, with our server nowhere to be seen for most of the meal. I would recommend the food though, it was delicious when it finally arrived.
Good service, decent atmosphere but seating is a bit tight. Potato waffles were OK. I got the smoked salmon option and thought it was a bit plain. If I returned, I wouldn't order it again.

I went there for lunch during the dining out week. This is one of the restaurants that offers regular items for the dining out special menus.

All dishes are very tasty. The most impressive dish was the beets salad. Beets are not in my regular diet, but this dish is amazing that I’m glad I took a try. Different kinds of beets were slight sweet and had different textures, balanced well with the crunch walnut and sweet strawberry. It had a tiny biscuit on top as well. A very creative and memorable dish. Highly recommend.

I ordered a latte to pair with my chocolate mousse in the end. To my surprise, the latte is only around $5. I would consider it very affordable for a French restaurant. Good coffee as well.

Got sat at the far right part of the bar.
Service is poor.   Bartenders were too busy to check on food.
Ordered the duck medium.  Came out medium rare.
In fairness,  they provided 50% discount on food.

Far seat on the bar is the worst: near the bathroom,  near the sink where they're constantly emptying drinks.

Did not enjoy the experience,  food,  service or ambience.
La Volaille is a must to have! Everything is so perfect here. Authentic French cuisine and the staff here are so nice. They even give us champagne when we finished. Will come back soon!

I was in Boston for a day trip & decided to come here for a solo lunch. I chose the 3-Course Lunch. The restaurant provides a very generous amount of food for $49. Everything was delicious & the service staff was very kind & attentive. There was cozy outdoor seating. Expect some birds to casually drop by your table ❤️✨

Where to start for this iconic mainstay on Newbury Street.  Let’s with the ambiance.  Stepping into this very extraordinary space, one notices the true French vibe immediately with a rich veneer of burgundy and oak gracing everything from the booths to the classy chairs.  French revelry is what comes to mind, especially when you come to the bar, which purportedly has the original Zinc top from its namesake in Marseilles.  Very unique and elegant.  And if you like the art and allure of B&W prints, the owner’s (an accomplished photographer) works graces the walls, with stars from yesteryear like Steve McQueen etc.

I happened to stop by on a recent Saturday evening, and while it was very busy, the very gracious and charming host, Heaven, managed to get me the one remaining spot at the bar.  Right from that amazingly warm entrance to an equally welcoming manager, Ilham, I felt transported to a very relaxed atmosphere of an authentic French bistro.

An even more pleasant experience was having Alejandra at the bar, a very able and gregarious person.  Her experience and zeal manifests in amazing creations, such as the La Poire Royale, an amazing blend of cognac, brandy, orange liqueur, lime and sparkling wine.  This is her signature cocktail, very unique, strong and enjoyable. There is also a great selection of wines, especially French, which stands to reason.  For starters I had outstanding French Onion soup (where else but here), but the main course of the Dover Sole seared in brown butter, with capers and a side of truffled mashed potatoes was just delectable.  The fish had to be deboned first, and Alejandra did a masterful job at it.  The very moist, flaky and flavorful fish was one of the best I have ever had.  The meal was just very special and a delight, made possible  with the amazing service and the congeniality of the staff.

This is a great place to have a very different experience and cuisine on Newbury Street, whether it be a special occasion or an evening out with friends.  I will definitely be returning.

Update:  On a subsequent trip with a friend tried the Escargots and Foie Gras appetizers and they were just outstanding.  But the main course, once again, was just very mouthwatering and well balanced.  The Loup de Mer (Bass) and the Sole Meunière hit the spot, capped off by a must-try Lile Flottante (French Meringue) dessert.  An accompanying bottle of delicate Sancerre, made for another very satisfying gastronomic experience.

ChIJQw3LKG5644kRevjN1DTlXWE.name: J.J. Foley's Cafe
ChIJQw3LKG5644kRevjN1DTlXWE.address: 117 E Berkeley St, Boston, MA 02118, USA

reviews.text: Spent the day visiting historical sites and pubs. This was by far the best pub along my journey. It is still family run (going on 5th Gen) and extremely friendly and inviting. Prices are good, beer is cold, and atmosphere is great. A little out of the way, but well worth the trip!

Stopped here for a short while for drinks and apps on a hot summer afternoon. This place was so nice and comfortable. We were greeted very warmly. Also, we were in a rush because we had to go to a show nearby, but the apps and drinks were ready in less than 5 mins. I loved my slane whiskey iced tea cocktail, my bf loved his Guinness and we enjoyed our loaded nachos. Will visit again when in the area!

This was my first visit and I'll be back. I was hoping for a comfortable Irish bar and JJ Foley's delivered. Prompt service, great food and clam chowder, and excellent draft beer (clean glasses and tap lines). I don't always feel comfortable as a lone woman at a beer bar, but the patrons and bartenders were friendly and nice to chat with. Good atmosphere amd decor as well. I was well fed and felt like a neighbor - a proper pub.

The food is excellent. My friends and I had the bacon tots and I had Smithwicks. Excellent customer service. The bartenders were Irish that was cool. This is the oldest Irish bar in Boston. The area, though, yikes! Just lock your doors. Otherwise, great bar. I would return next time I'm in Massachusetts.

We happened upon this place after visiting the SoWa open market and had a lovely mother's day lunch. The service was really good, the waiter offered my mother a sampler of beer when she couldn't decide, which was really helpful and she loved the ones he suggested. We split the pizzaiolo steak sandwich which was absolutely delicious. Plenty of leftovers too!

We enjoyed the food, ambiance and service.   Not an exceptional choice, but nothing disappointing.  Grilled Salmon was good.   Plenty of pizza and pasta choices.   Kids choices are also good and nominal price.   Lettuce wrap also worth trying, but felt salty to me.

Entering the restaurant I was greeted right away.  The server arrived quickly and had my beverage within minutes.  The restaurant was clean and the location was great.  The only issue was with the pizza itself.  I went for the Works pizza without olives.  It looked great, but when I ate it all I got was vegetable and meat tastes.  There was not a lot of sauce at all and for me that’s what makes the pizza.  I will try them again, but this time the pizza was not like the regular pies I get at other CPK’s.

As you can see we ordered a bunch of food, But overall, it was very disappointing.

First of all the drinks: I ordered the watermelon drink that was limited edition and the flavor had a little hint of watermelon which it was very watery.

Second, the pizza: the spicy pepperoni pizza was delicious 😋 but the Thai Chicken pizza was absolutely disgusting. The topping and the sauce did not belong on the pizza which as a family of 6 with a big appetite, 3/4 of the pizza was left on the table.

Third, the Pasta:
Chicken Pasta Fettuccine(⭐️⭐️) had noodles that were undercooked. Really felt I was just chewing on cooked flour. And the flavor overall was very watery.

Shrimp Scampi Zuccini(⭐️⭐️⭐️) also had noodles that were undercooked. Although the shrimp and zuccini was ok, the portion was smaller compared to other pastas and the flavor did not wow me.

Bolognese sphagetti(⭐️): don't let the fancy description get you, this is just a too plain sphagetti that everybody had more than once in their life. To be honest my elementary school served better sphagettis with more meat and sauce. It was to bland; barely any sauce or meat chunks(which makes the sphagetti THE sphagett).

Fourth, the salad: Classic Caesar(⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️): The chicken breast was tender with the hint of smokiness, and what could you hate about a salad? Anyways very disappointing how this restaurant is very pricey and is apparently known for their pizza but the most o-kay dish was the salad ..

Last but not least, the customer service(⭐️⭐️): First of all when our family entered the restaurant I don't understand how we were welcomed with side eyes??? Not only that when the foods were served the waitress did not even come once to ask of the foods alright or it fits our taste. This was very disappointing.

Overall, my family spend about 300$ in this restaurant and I could say with complete sureness that we are never coming to this place again in Boston.

The parking's free though. 🤷‍♀️ The free parking and caesar salad was the best here....
Very delicious salads, fries and burgers + very friendly staff! Restaurant is clean and nice!

A great place for pizza that taste like real good fresh pizza! We have had to wait for 20 min to get a table so maybe book in advance if possible. We had guacamole which was super delicious, spinach’s artichoke dip was also super delicious. Unfortunately not much options for vegetarians, would love to see more inclusion by adding maybe halal or kosher meat/ chicken options for those who appreciate having protein along with their 🍕

The service was ok .  We ordered drinks they were good.  The waitress was rushing us to finish , so we could order more drinks . (Because it was 45 minutes until closing.  )  They were also drinks made in blender with ice ,  So it was difficult . They had music , and a public  bathroom .  The parking on the street is impossible but they have a pricey parking garage across the street .  It’s pricey and the portions are ok.

This place is such a vibe.  The food, service and atmosphere is Top of the Line.  Definitely a hidden Gem 💎 in Back Bay.  I honestly can’t believe I hadn’t been here before tonight.  Some of the best sushi I’ve had in a while. The lady serving was such a sweetheart and when above and beyond.  She had a genuine smile the whole time and for me that goes a long way.

Lots of great seafood options and drinks had us eating here two days in a row. The sushi especially stood out as delicious, going beyond the basic options and into interesting rolls with sauces and lightly seared fish. Tiki style drinks are on the sweeter side.

The drinks are amazing and well worth it. Service is great and the atmosphere is great, far superior than most of the common sports bars in the area. The food is great and reasonably priced, it’s not gourmet, but it doesn’t claim to be. Highly recommend typhoon if you are in the area, don’t listen to the negative reviews, they are probably from tourists or college kids.

The staff is incredibly kind and friendly, the ambience is amazing and perfect for a romantic dinner. The food is insanely good. They have classic dishes and ones with a newer twist to them. Price is worth it! Definitely recommend!!

I recently visited this cafe and found it to be a mixed experience. The price for an iced mocha oat milk latte was quite high at $7.50, which felt excessive. The drink itself was a bit disappointing—too much chocolate made it taste more like a chocolate smoothie rather than a balanced mocha latte. While the drink wasn’t terrible, I expected better for nearly $8.

On a positive note, the cafe has a charming rustic ambiance and offers a cozy coffeehouse experience. The staff were also friendly and helpful. Overall, while the atmosphere and service were commendable, the drink and its price left something to be desired.

Pavement is a good place to get some fresh coffee and some pastries. The coffee have a great taste I got an Americano with cream, was very hot! And I got a sesame seed bagel with egg and cheese , was very good! .
The ambience was good, clean but small space and busy in the morning.
Is an option better than Starbucks!

The coffee isn’t my favorite, especially for the price, but their bagels are absolutely delicious. They’re perfectly spongey and crispy, not at all dry. If you can snag a spot on their patio, it’s just lovely.
This place has my favorite bagel. It’s so stuffed and delicious. It usually takes a while to get your order, but it’s always fresh and worth the wait.
Stellar coffee and good bagels next to Newbury Street. Appreciate the charitable fundraisers and music events that are posted on the bulletin board and sense of social community

The menu has not been updated on the website and there is no way to call in an order.
I'm staying in the Sheraton hotel, so it was easy enough for me to go down and look at the menu.
I ordered the Bacon Cheeseburger which comes with lettuce tomato and purple onion. It also comes with crinkle cut fries.

The bacon cheeseburger was very good and the brioche bun was toasted with butter.
The fries were not very good, a bit under cooked for my taste.

We also ordered a bowl of clam chowder, which is a bacon clam chowder.
It was tasty, but only filled about 3/4 of the cup.

The bacon cheeseburger was $18 and the chowder was $12, with tax the total was $32.10.

I stayed in Sheraton during Christmas, and on 25th nothing on the street was opening, so I ate here. The food was pretty good. I had steak and my friend had burger. Three star because there is a strange waiter who complained my tip is too low. "All my income depends on the tip, and that is the rule of US here. " Eh, excuse me? I know I am a traveler from a country with no habit of tips, but if I am not happy, I am not urged to give you tips. Plus the waiter does not appear to be in good mood at the start. A bit too unhappy to serve me.

Amazing service! "Tran the Man" as he told us was his name, went above & beyond to entertain & keep us happy! Never a dull moment there, especially if the game is on! The food is incredible & the drinks are strong! All the bar tenders were so nice & very helpful!

I stayed at the Sheraton for a conference a few weeks ago. I ate in the restaurant once, and had drinks with friends once. When I ate, it was lunch and I had a burger. The burger was good, but it took a very long time to get my food.  The waiter wasn't exactly rude, but seemed agitated and not very helpful. And the burger was $18. Kind of expensive. The second time I went, I met 8 or 9 friends and we had drinks.  The same waiter was very rude this time and absolutely refused to split the tab so we could all pay for our drinks individually. I understand they add gratuity for groups, and we were fine with dividing that onto each bill, but he still refused, and got angry and down right hostile when we objected. Luckily there were only a couple of us that weren't carrying cash so we were able to chip in and pay the bill. I have NEVER been to a bar that refused to give individual tabs. If I'm ever back in Boston, I won't be returning. You're probably thinking we were being a bunch of Karen's, but most of the group was Canadian. Do you have any idea how hard it is to make Canadian's mad?  That waiter succeeded. Lol.

It's a hotel restaurant, so I didn't expect much. And that's what I got. Very few options for vegetarians. I got the cauliflower hummus. It was pretty basic with basic pita. If "it was food" is an ok review for you, go for it. It was also really expensive, which is to be expected for a downtown hotel. But pretty disappointing for what you get.

ChIJayHyyGx644kRA1vLAU-Bmtk.address: 57 W Dedham St, Boston, MA 02118, USA

reviews.text: We love everything about this restaurant. Great customer service and the flavors of food was amazing.

We love coming here because of their authentic puertorrican food. Everything is delicious. I've tried multiple drinks from here. However, my favorite will always be the passionfruit mojito. Please do make reservations when coming to have a guaranteed table. The environment is amazing, with some good puertorrican music playing in the background.

For apps, we got the canoa which was very delicious in terms of texture, temp, and flavor. The Chuleta Kan Kan was definitely presented well. However, it was a bit dry for us. The fried plantains were a bit under seasoned in our opinion. The malanga puree was great and super filling. The sauteed beef entree was nicely seasoned and perfectly cooked. Overall, we could've just ordered the canoa and Kan Kan for two people and been nicely full.

We had such a good Puerto Rican 🇵🇷 lunch!
All what we ordered was delicious and the passion fruit mojitos was on of the best. Alcapurrias, Canoa and the shrimp ceviche all dishes were 10 out of 10!

Very disappointed this time, we only order appetizers which not only all came cold and the tostones, yuca frita and calamari were frozen items. Not worth it at all. The Sangria pitcher was all ice and all juice. Never again!
